Mukhale osangalala, Popita masikuwa;
Dziko liri m’cisoni, Misozi ndi maliro;
Thandiza obvutika, Popita masikuwa.

Zotimanga tizisiya, Popita masikuwa;
Modzi ndi mmodzi atsala, Popita masikuwa
Zabwino tidzakhala, ponse ponse zimera;
Tidzakhala okondwa, Popita masikuwa.

M’mayesero anga, Tate mndisunge;
Ndisakukaneni, Kukusiyani,
Pondenguma ine, Kumbukireni,
Nsalekene nanu, Musanditaye.

Za dziko nzacabe, Ndisatengeke
Cuma ca poyera, Cisandikope
Kusunga kwani sisi, Ndikubvomera
Ndikana zoipa zolakalaka.

Matsoka si anu, Zolabadira;
Zowawa zikadza Kusokonzeza;
Zikumphanitu Ndisacimwe bi;
Nkhawa zanga zonse, Ndikupatsani.

Kwa Inu YEsu ndilira; Wopanda Inu ndidzafa;
Mundipulumutse Mbuye Mundilandiretu.

Ndine wocimwa kwambiri, Koma munafera ine;
Mutha konse kundikonza, Mundilandiretu.

Sinditha kudzikonzatu, Ndingodzipereka ndekha;
Ndipulumutseni nokha, Mundilandiretu.

Ndigwadira nsisi zanu, Ndioneni Ambuyanga;
Yayambidwa ntchito yanu Mundilandiretu.

Kwao Mkristu kwa ulemu, Ndi malo a mpumulo;
Mpulumutsi anapita komwe Mtima ufuna

Akundimangira nyumba  Idzakhala muyaya
Ndidzakhalitsatu uko, M’dzikolo la cimwemwe.

Zowawa sizidzalowa, Cisoni kulibenso;
Koma m’kati mwa mtendere, Ndidzabvala korona

Imfa idzamarizidwa, Tsoka lidzacotsedwa;
Adzapfuula mokondwa Pa tsiku la mdzukiro

Yimbani olowa m’Mwamba, Yimbani cigonjetso,
Mukadzalowa m’ziyoni, Khoma mudzaliona.

Ambuye ali pafupi kudza, Ndikumvaconcodi,
Ndiponso nyenyezi zikuzima, Tsopano ndi mbanda kucatu

Zizindikiro za mlengalenga Zilalikiradi;
Ndi za pa dziko zinena kuti Ambuye wayandikira

Ndi nthawi yoti kunyada kuthu Mu mpingo wonsewo;
Ukhale wofulumira ntchito, Ukhale woyang’aniratu

Pitani msanga kukalalika Kwa osaukawo;
Ndi kwa omveka a dziko lino; Onsewo afulumirenso.

E, Mzimu wa Mulungu, ’Nu, Mukhale m’mtimanga;
Ndi zangazo ndipatsatu Kwa Inu, Mbuyanga

Ndifunatu kucitadi Kufuna kwanuko;
Sin’funa kanthu kena bi, Mndidzaze, mtimamo,

Ndilibe kanthu kabwino, Kopatsa Inuyo;
Mutsuke Mtima wangawo, Ndi mwazi wanuwo.

Atate muwapenye Anzathu onsewo;
Abvomereza dzina La Yesu Kristuyo;
Alonjezetsa lero Kutsata Mbuyeyo,
Mwathangatire iwo Asabwererenso.

Onsewa afa ndithu M’zoipa zawozo;
Tsopano aikidwa Ndi Kristu m’mandamo;
Auke iwo onse Kuyenda nayeyo;
Aphe nthawi zonse Ndi kudya mauwo.

Muwalimbitse, Mbuye, Kuyenda m’njirayi,
Ndi kugonetsa mdani Masiku onsewo;
Muwathangate iwo Kukopa enawo,
Amene ali kufa M’zoipa zawozo.

Lemekeza Mlungu ’tate, Lemekeza Mwananso,
Lemekeza, Mlungu Mzimu, Mlungu Mmodzi mkuruyo;
Lemekeza, lemekeza, Mlungu wathu yemweyo.

Mlemekeze, anaconda, Natisuka m’mtimamo,
Anatiombola ife, Tikhale nayeyo;
Lemekeza, lemekeza, Yesu Mbuye nsembeyo.

Lemekeza Mfumu yathu, Mfumu, Mlengi wathuyo,
Apambana anthu onse, Pansi ndi kumwambako;
Lemekeza, lemekeza, Mfumu ya mafumuyo.

Utsegule pa khomo, kuti Yesu alowe;
Ndi ngati ulola ’dzacotsa chimo
Tsegula mtimawo

Watch, ye saints, with eyelids waking;
          Lo! The powers of heeav’n are shaking;
       Keep your lamps all trimm’d and burning,
       Ready for your Lord’s returning.    

        Kingdoms at their base are crumbling,
       Hark! His chariot wheels are rumbling;
        Tell, O tell of grace abounding,
        Whilst the seventh trump is sounding.    

        Nations wane, tho’ proud and stately;
       Christ his kingdom hasteneth greatly,
        Earth her latest pangs is summing; 
        Shout, ye saints, your Lord is coming.    

        Sinners, come, while Christ is pleading;
       Now for you he’s interceding;
        Haste,ere grace and time diminished,
        Shall proclaim the mystery finished.

Lift up the trumpet, and loud let it ring;
    Jesus is coming again!
   Cheer up ye pilgrims, be joyful and sing;
    Jesus is coming again!

    Echo it, hilltops, proclaim it, ye plains; 
   Jesus is coming again!
     Coming in glory, the Lamb that was slain;
    Jesus is coming again!

   Sound it, old ocean, in each mighty wave;
    Jesus is coming again!
     Break on the sands of the shores that ye lave;
 Jesus is coming again!

    Hearings of earth, tell the vast, wond’ring throng; 
    Jesus is coming again!
    Tempests and whirlwinds, the anthem prolong;
    Jesus is coming again!

    Nations are angry, by this we do know;
    Jesus is coming again!
    Knowledge increases, men run to and fro; 
    Jesus is coming again!

Shall we gather at the river,
        Where bright angel feet have trod;
        With its crystal tide forever,
         Flowing by the throne of God?    

        On the margin of the river, 
Washing up its silver spray;
         We will walk and worship ever,
All the happy golden day.    

         Ere we reach the shining river;
          Lay we ev’ry burden down;
          Grace our spirits will deliver,
        And provide a robe and crown.    

          Soon we’ll reach the shining river,
Soon our pilgrimage will cease;
         Soon our happy hearts will quiver,
         With the melody of peace.

hymns.chorus:
Yes, we’ll gather at the river,
         The beautiful, The beautiful river; 
          Gather with the saints at the river;
          That flows by the throne  of God.

hymns.lyrics:
I will follow thee, my Saviour,
Wheresoe’er my lot may be;
          Where thou goest I will fallow;
          Yes, my Lord, I’ll follow thee.        

Tho’ the road be rough and thorny,
Trackless as the foaming sea;
Thou hast trod this way before me,
And I’ll gladly follow thee.        

Tho’ I meet with tribulations,
   Sorely tempted tho’ I be;
I remember thou wast tempted,
   And rejoice to follow thee.        

Though thou lead’st me thro’ affliction,
 Poor, forsaken, though I be;
Thou wast destitute afflicted,
And I only follow thee.        

  Though to Jordan’s rolling billows;
   Cold and deep, thou leadest me;
Thou hast crossed the waves before me,
     And I still will follow thee.

hymns.chorus:
I will follow thee, my Saviour,
Thou didst shed thy blood for me;
And tho’ all men should forsake thee,
 By thy grace I’ll follow thee;

hymns.lyrics:
Lord Jesus I long to to be perfectly whole;
   I want Thee forever to live in my soul;
   Break down every idol,cast out every foe;
   Now wash me and I shall be whiter than snow.

 Lord Jesus, look down from Thy throne in the skies,
And help me to make a complete sacrifice;
I give up myself, and whatever I know;
Now wash me and I shall be whiter than snow

Lord Jesus for this I most humbly entreat;
  I wait,blessed Lord,at Thy crucified feet
  By faith,for my cleansing;
  I see Thy blood flow;
  Now wash me and I shall be whiter than snow

Lord Jesus, Thou seest I patiently wait;
Come now, and within me a new heart create;
To those who have sought Thee, Thou never said`st No;
Now wash me, and I shall be whiter than snow

Hear the pennies dropping! Listen while they fall.
Every one to Jesus, -He will get them all.

Dropping, dropping ever, From each little hand;
`Tis our gift to Jesus, From his little band.

Now, while we are little, Pennies are our store;
But, when we are older, Lord, we’ll give thee more.

Tho` we’ve little money, We can give him love;
He will own our off`ring, Smilling from above.

Jesus loves me! This I know, For the Bible tells me so;
Little one to Him belong, They are weak but  He is strong

Jesus loves me! He who died, Haven’s gates will open wide;
He will wash away my sins. Let His little child come in.

Jesus loves me! Loves me still, when I’m sad or weak and ill;
From His shinning Throne on high,
 Comes to watch me where I lie.

Jesus loves me! He will stay, Close beside me all the way,
If I love Him, by and by He will take me home on high.

`Tis love that makes us happy, `Tis love that smoothes the way;
      It helps us “mind “,it makes us kind to others everyday

This world is full of sorrow, Of sickness, death and sin;
    With loving hearts we’ll do our part, And try some soul to win.

And when this life is over, And we are called above,
Our song shall be eternally, Of Jesus and his love.

My soul, be on thy guard! Ten thousand foes arise;
The hosts of sin are pressing hard, To draw thee from the skies.

O, watch and fight and pray! The battle ne`er give o`er;
Renew it boldly ev`ry day, And help divine implore.

 Ne`er think the victory won, Nor lay thine armor down;
Thy arduous task will not be done Till thou obtain the crown

Awake my soul! Stretch every nerve, and press with vigor on;
A heavenly race demands thy zeal, and an immortal crown.

Tis God’s all animating voice, That calls thee from on high;
`Tis he whose hand presents the prize, to thine aspiring eye.

A cloud of witnesses around, hold thee in full survey;
Forget the steps already trod, and onward urge thy way.

Blest saviour, introduced by the, our race have we begun;
And, crown with victory, at thy feet, we’ll lay our trophies down

Lord, I hear of show`rs of blessing,
    thou art scattering full and free;
    Show`rs the thirsty soul refreshing;
    Let some drop now fall on me;

    CHORUS
    Even me, even me, let some drops fall on me.

    Pass me not, O gracious Father!
    Sinful though my heart may be;
    Though mightest leave me,
    but the rather let thy mercy rest on me.

    Have I long in sin been sleeping? 
    Long been sighting, grieving thee? 
    Has the world my heart been keeping? 
    O forgive and rescue me!.

    Pass me not, O Holy Spirit!
    Thou canst make the blind to see;
    Testify of Jesus` merit;
    speak the word of peace to me.

Hover o`er me, Holy spirit,
     Bathe my trembling heart and brow;
     Fill me with thy hallow`d presence,
     Come, O come and fill me now.

     CHORUS
     Fill me now, fill me now, Jesus come and fill me now.
     Fill me with thy hallow`d presence, Come, O come and fill me now.

     Thou canst fill me gracious Spirit,
     Tho` I can not tell thee how;
     But I need thee, greatly need thee,
     Come, O come and fill me now.

     I am weaknes, full of weakness;
     At thy sacred feet I bow;
     Blest, divine, eternal Spirit,
     Fill with love and fill me now.

     Cleanse and comfort, bless and save;
     Bathe, O, bathe my heart and brow;
     Thou art comforting and saving,
     Thou art sweetly filling now.

I need thee every hour, Most gracious Lord;
    No tender voice like Thine can peace afford?

    CHORUS
    I need Thee, O I need Thee!
    Every hour I need Thee;
    O bless me now, my Saviour!
    I come to Thee.

    I need Thee every hour; Stay Thou near by;
    Temptations lose their pow`r, when Thou art nigh.

    I need Thee every hour, in joy or pain;
    Come quickly and abide, Or life is vain.

    I need Thee every hour, Most Holy One;
    O make me Thine indeed, Thou blessed Son

All to Jesus I surrender, All to him I freely give;
    I will ever love and trust Him, in his presence daily live;

   CHORUS
    I surrender all; I surrender all;
    All to Thee my blessed Saviour,
    I surrender all.

    All to Jesus I surrender, humbly at his feet I bow;
    Worldly pleasures all forsaken take me Jesus, take me now;

    All to Jesus I surrender, make me Saviour, wholly Thine;
    Let me feel the Holy Spirit, truly know that Thou art mine;

    All to Jesus I surrender, now I feel the sacred flame.
    O the joy of full salvation! Glory, glory to his name!

Take time to be holy, speak soft with the Lord;
    Abide in him always, and feed on his word;
    Make friends of God’s children; help those who are weak, 
    Forgetting in nothing, his blessing to seek.

    Take time to be holy, the world rushes on; 
    Spend much time in secret with Jesus alone;
    By looking to Jesus, like Him thou shalt be; 
    Thy friends in thy conduct, His likeness shall see. 

    Take time to be holy, let Him be thy guide,
    And run not before him, whatever betide; 
    In joy or in sorrow, still follow thy Lord,
    And looking to Jesus, still trust in his word. 

    Take time to be holy, be calm in thy soul,
    Each tho`t and each motive beneath his control; 
    Thus led by the Spirit to fountains of love,
    Thou soon shall be fitted for service above.

Abide with me! Fast falls the even-tide;
    The darkness deepens; Lord with me abide!
    When other helpers fail and comforts flee,
    Help of the helpless, O, abide with me.

Swift to its close ebbs out life’s little day;
    Earth’s joys grow dim; its glories pass away;
    Change and decay in all around I see;
    O thou who changest not, abide with me

Not a brief glance I ask nor passing word,
But as thou dwell`st with thy disciples, Lord,
Familiar, condensing, patient, at no cost,
Come, not to so-journ, but abide with me.

I need thy presence ev`ry passing hour;
    What but thy grace can foil the tempter’s pow`r:
    Who, like thyself, my guide and stay can be?
   Thro` cloud and sunshine, Lord, abide with me.

hymns.chorus:
On Christ, the solid Rock, I stand;
All other ground is sinking sand,
All other ground is sinking sand.

hymns.lyrics:
God be with you till we meet again;
By his counsels guide uphold you
       With his sheep securely fold you;
God be with you till we meet again.

God be with you till we meet again; 
‘Neath his wings protecting hide 
     you, Daily manna still provide you,
 God be with you till we meet again

God be with you till we meet again;
 When life’s perils thick confound 
     you, Put his arms unfailing round you;
God be with you till we meet  again.

God be with you till we meet again;
Keep love’s banner floating o’er  you,
Smite death’s threat’ning wave before you;
 God be with you till we meet again

When my life-work is ended, and I cross the swelling tide,
       When “this mortal puts on immortality;” 
       I shall know my Redeemer When I reach the other side,
       And his smile will be the first to welcome me.

O, the soul-thrilling rapture when I view his blessed face,
   And the luster of his kindly beaming eye;
   How my full heart will praise him for the mercy, love, and grace
   That prepares for me a mansion in the sky.

O, the dear ones departed! How the tender mem’ries come,
   As the farewell at the river I recall;
   In the sweet vales of Eden we shall meet no more to roam;
   But I long to see my Saviour first of all.

Thro’ the gates to the city, in a robe of spotless white,
   He will lead me where no tears shall never fall; 
   In the glad song of ages I shall mingle with delight;
   But I long to meet my Saviour first of all.

Sing then over again to me, Wonderful words of life;
       Let me more of their beauty see, Wonderful words of life;
       Words of life and beauty, Teach me faith and duty.

Christ the blessed One, gives to all, Wonderful words of life;
       Sinner, list to the loving call, Wonderful words of life;
       All so freely give, Wooing us to heaven,

Sweetly echo the gospel call, Wonderful of words life;
       Offer pardon and peace to all, Wonderful words of life;
       Jesus, only Saviour, Sanctify forever,

Come, thou fount of every blessing,Tune my heart to sing thy grace;
Streams of mercy, never ceasing, call for songs of loudest praise.
Teach me ever to adore thee, may I still thy goodness prove,
        While the hope of endless glory, Fills my heart with joy and love.                Here I raise my Ebenezer, hither by thy help I’ve come;
        And I hope by thy good pleasure, Safely to arrive at home.
        Jesus sought me when a stranger, Wand’ring from the fold of God;
        He to rescue me from all danger, Interposed his precious blood                O, to grace how great a debtor, daily I’m constrained to be!
        Let thy goodness like a fetter; Bind me closer still to thee;
        Prone to wander, Lord I feel it, Prone to leave the God I love,
        Here’s my heart, O, take and seal it; Seal it for thy courts above.

I’ve wandered far away from God, now I’m coming home;
    The paths of sin too long I’ve trod, Lord, I’m coming home.    

    I’ve wasted many precious years, Now I’m coming home;
    I now repent with bitter tears; Lord, I’m coming home.

    I’m tired of sin and straying, Lord, Now I’m coming home;
    I’ll trust Thy love, believe Thy word; Lord, I’m coming home.    

    My only hope, my only plea, Now I’m coming home;
    That Jesus died, and died for me; Lord, I’m coming home.

”Whosoever heareth”, shout, shout the sound!
      Send the blessed tidings all the world around;
      Spread the joyful news wherever man is found;
     “Whosoever will may come.”    

     “Whosoever cometh need not delay,
      Now the door is open, enter while you may;
      Jesus is the true, the only Living Way;
     “Whosoever will may come.”    

“Whosoever will,” the promise secure,
    “Whosoever will,” for ever must endure;
    “Whosoever will,” Tis life for ever more;
    “Whosoever will may come.”

All hail the pow’r of Jesus’ name! Let angels prostrate fall;
     Bring forth the royal diadem, And crown Him Lord of all;
     Bring forth the royal diadem, And crown Him Lord of all.    

     Ye chosen seed of Israel’s race, A remnant weak and small;
     Hail Him who saves you by His grace, And crown Him Lord of all.
     Hail Him who saves you by His grace, And crown Him Lord of all.    

    Let ev’ry kindred, ev’ry tribe, On this terrestrial ball;
    To Him all majesty ascribe, And crown Him Lord of all;
    To Him all majesty ascribe, And crown Him Lord of all.    

    O that with yonder sacred throng, We at His feet may fall;
    We’ll join the everlasting song, And crown Him Lord of all;
    We’ll join the everlasting song, And crown Him Lord of all.

Jesus, lover of my soul, Let me to Thy bosom fly;
    While the billows near me roll, While the tempest still is high!
    Hide me, O my Saviour hide, Till the storm of life be past;
    Safe into the haven guide, Oh, receive my soul at last!

    Other refuge have I none. Hangs my helpless soul on Thee;
    Leave, O leave me not alone, Still support and comfort me;
    All my trust on Thee is stayed, All my help from Thee I bring;
    Cover my defenceless head, With the shadow of Thy wing.

    Thou, O Christ, art all I want, More than all in Thee I find;
    Raise the fallen, cheer the faint, Heal the sick and lead the blind;
    Just and holy is Thy name; I am all unrighteousness;
    Vile and full of sin I am,nThou art full of truth and grace.

    Plenteous grace with Thee is found, Grace to cover all my sin;    Let the healing streams abound, Make and keep me pure within;    Thou of life the fountain art, Freely let me take of Thee;    Spring Thou up within my heart, Rise to all eternity!

My Jesus, I love thee, I know thou art mine;
       For thee all the follies of sin I resign;
       My gracious Redeemer, my Saviour art thou,
       If ever I loved thee, my Jesus ‘tis now.

I love thee because thou hast first loved me;
       And purchased my pardon on Calvary’s tree;
I Love thee for wearing the thorns on thy brow;
 If ever I loved thee, my Jesus, ‘tis now.

I’ll love thee in life, and I’ll love thee in death;
     I’ll praise thee as long as thou lendest me breath;
     And say when the death-dew lies cold on my bro
   If ever I loved thee, my Jesus ‘tis now.

In mansions of glory and endless delight;
       I’ll ever adore thee in heaven so bright;
       And sing with the glittering crown on my brow;
       If ever I loved thee, my Jesus ‘tis now.

What can wash away my sin?
Nothing but the blood of Jesus;
       What can make me pure within?
 Nothing but the blood of Jesus.

For my cleansing this I see;
Nothing but the blood of Jesus;
       For my pardon this my plea;
Nothing but the blood of Jesus.

Hot-ing can for sin atone; 
        Nothing but the blood of Jesus;
Naught of good that I have done;
       Nothing but the blood of Jesus.

This is all my hope and peace; 
Nothing but the blood of Jesus;
       This is all my righteousness; 
Nothing but the blood of Jesus.

Glory! Glory! thus I sing;
          Nothing but the blood of Jesus;
       All my praise for this I bring; 
         Nothing but the blood of Jesus.

‘Tis so sweet to trust in Jesus,
 Just to take Him at His word;
       Just to rest upon His promise; 
Just to know, ”Thus saith the Lord.”

O how sweet to trust in Jesus,
      Just to trust His cleansing blood;
       Just in simple faith to plunge me,
      ‘Neat the healing, cleansing flood.

Yes, ‘tis sweet to trust in Jesus,
        Just from sin and self to cease;
       Just from Jesus simply taking,
    Life, and rest, and joy, and peace.

I’m so glad I learned to trust Thee,
     Precious Jesus, Saviour, Friend;
And I know that Thou art with me, 
Wilt be with me till the end.

hymns.chorus:
Jesus, Jesus, how I trust Him; 
   How I’ve prov’d Him o’er and o’er! 
Jesus, Jesus, precious Jesus!       O for grace to trust Him more!

hymns.lyrics:
Redeemed! How I love to proclaim it!
 Redeemed by the blood of the lamb;
   Redeemed thro’ his infinite mercy
 His child and forever I am.

Redeemed! And so happy in Jesus!
 No language my rapture can tell;
  I know that the light of his presence,
With me doth continually dwell.

I think of my blessed Redeemer, 
 I think of him all the day long;
  I sing; for I cannot be silent;
 His love  is the theme of my song.

I know I shall see in his beauty,
The King in whose law I delight;
  Who lovingly guardeth my footsteps,
 And giveth songs in the night.

I know there’s a crown that is waiting,
 In yonder bright mansion for me;
   And soon, with the spirits made perfect,
 At home with the Lord I shall be.

Work, for the night is coming,
Work thro’ the morning hours;
       Work while the dew is sparkling,
Work ‘mid springing flowers,
       Work while the day grows brighter, 
Under the glowing sun; 
       Work for the night is coming,
When man’s work is done.     

        Work for the night is coming,
Work through the sunny noon; 
       Fill brightest hours with labor,
Rest comes sure and soon;
       Give every flying minute,  
 Something to keep in store;
       Work, for the night is coming,
When man works no more.     

        Work, for the night is coming, 
 Under the sunset skies; 
       While their bright tints are glowing,
Work, for the daylight flies;
       Work till the last beam fadeth, 
 Fadeth to shine no more; 
       Work while the night is darkening, 
When man’s work is o’er.

Father, we come to thee,
No other help have we, 
       Thou wilt our refuge be, On thee we call;
       Earth is but dark and drear,
Without thy presence near;
       Be thou our comfort here, Father of all.     

        Save from our many foes,
  Save from our earthly woes,
       Be thou our soul’s repose, In time of need; 
Fearful are we and weak,
To us sweet courage speak; 
       Thy mighty arm we seek, For strength indeed.     

        Give us thy grace divine, Seal us forever thine, 
       Our wayward feet incline, From sin to flee;
       O guide us we implore, ‘Till weary life is o’er,
       And on a brighter shore, We dwell with thee.

Watch, for the time is short;
         Watch while ‘tis called today;
       Watch lest the world prevail; 
  Watch, Christian, watch and pray; 
       Watch, for the flesh is weak; 
      Watch, for the foe is strong;
   Watch lest the Bridegroom come; 
        Watch, though he tarry long     

        Chase slumber from thine eyes,
 Chase doubting from thy breast;
       Thine is the promised prize,
Of heaven’s eternal rest; 
   Watch, Christian, watch and pray; 
        Thy Saviour watched for thee,
Till from his brow there poured,
 Great drops of agony.     

Take Jesus for thy trust;
        Watch while the foe is near;
       Gird well the armor on;
     Watch till thy Lord appear,
       Now when thy sun is up, 
      Make thou no more delay,
          In this accepted time, Watch, 
   Christian, watch and pray.

hymns.chorus:
O watch and pray, O watch and pray;
     O watch in the darkness,
      and watch is the day;
Christian, watch and pray.

hymns.lyrics:
We have heard a joyful sound,
Jesus saves, Jesus saves;
Spread the gladness all around,
Jesus saves, Jesus saves;
       Bear the news to ev’ry land,
Climb the steeps and cross the waves,
  Onward ‘tis our Lord’s command, 
 Jesus saves, Jesus saves.    

     Waft it on the rolling tide,
 Jesus saves, Jesus saves;
      Tell to sinners, far and wide, 
 Jesus saves, Jesus saves; 
      Sing, ye islands of the sea, 
     Echo back, ye ocean caves; 
      Earth shall keep her jubilee, 
Jesus saves, Jesus saves.    

          Sing above the battle’s strife,
 Jesus saves, Jesus saves;
          By his death and endless life,
Jesus saves, Jesus saves;
 Sing it softly through the gloom,
  When the heart for mercy craves;
        Sing in triumph o’er the tomb,
 Jesus saves, Jesus saves.    

        Give the winds a mighty voice, 
    Jesus saves, Jesus saves; 
          Let the nations now rejoice, 
     Jesus saves, Jesus saves; 
 Shout salvation full and free,
      Highest hills and deepest caves; 
      This our song of victory, 
      Jesus saves, Jesus saves.

Jesus is tenderly calling thee home,
 Calling today, calling today;
      Why from the sunshine of love wilt thou roam,
Farther and farther away?     

        Jesus is calling the weary to rest,
 Calling today, calling today;
      Bring him thy burden, and thou shalt be blest;
 He will not turn thee away.     

        Jesus is waiting, oh, come to Him now,
 Waiting today, waiting today;
      Come with thy sins, at His feet lowly bow; 
Come, and no longer delay.     

        Jesus is pleading, oh, list to His voice,
 Hear Him today, Hear Him today; 
      They who believe on His name shall rejoice;
 Quickly arise and away.

hymns.chorus:
Jesus paid it all, All to him I owe;
       Sin had left a crimson stain;
    He washed it white as snow.

hymns.lyrics:
Father, I stretch my hands to Thee;
No other help I know; 
       If Thou withdraw Thyself from me,
Ah, whither shall I go?

         On thy dear Son I now believe,
      O let me feel Thy power; 
       And all my varied wants relieve, 
In this accepted hour.

 Author of faith! To Thee I lift, 
 My weary, longing eyes; 
       O let me now receive that gift, 
My soul without it dies

Nearer, still nearer, close to Thy heart,
 Draw me, my Saviour, so precious thou art 
       Fold me, O fold me close to Thy breast,
Shelter me safe in that “Heaven of Rest,”
       Shelter me safe in that “Heaven of Rest.”

    Nearer, still nearer, nothing I bring,
Naught as an offering to Jesus my King;
  Only my sinful now contrite heart,
 Grant me the cleansing Thy blood doth impart;
       Grant me the cleansing Thy blood doth impart.

    Nearer, still nearer, Lord, to be Thine,
 Sin, with its follies, I gladly resign; 
       All of its pleasures, pomp and its pride;
Give me but Jesus, my Lord crucified;
       Give me but Jesus, my Lord crucified

      Nearer, still nearer, while life shall last,
 Till safe in glory my anchor is cast; 
       Thro’ endless ages, ever to be, 
     Nearer, my Saviour, still nearer to Thee;
       Nearer, my Saviour, still nearer to Thee.

Not I, but Christ, be honored, loved, exalted;
    Not I, but Christ, be seen, be known, be heard;
    Not I, but Christ, in every look and action,
       Not I, but Christ, in every thought and word.    

        Not I, but Christ, to gently soothe in sorrow;
       Not I, but Christ, to wipe the falling tear;
       Not I, but Christ, to lift the weary burden,
       Not I, but Christ, to hush away all fear.    

        Christ, only Christ! No idle words e’re falling;
       Christ, only Christ, no needless busting sound;
       Christ, only Christ, no self important bearing, 
       Christ, only Christ, no trace of “I” is found.    

        Not I, but Christ, my every need supplying;
       Not I, but Christ, my strength and health to be;
       Christ, only Christ, for body, soul, and spirit,
       Christ, only Christ, here and eternally.

More like Jesus would I be;
  Let my Saviour dwell with me,
      Fill my soul with peace and love,
         Make me gentle as a dove;
       More like Jesus while I go,
Pilgrim in this world below; 
       Poor in Spirit would I be,
    Let  My Saviour dwell in me.

        If he hears the raven’s cry;
If his ever watchful eye,
       Marks the sparrows when they fall, 
  Surely he will hear my call; 
       He will teach me how to live,
         All my simple thoughts forgive;
       Pure in heart I still would be,
    Let my Saviour dwell in me.

          More like Jesus when I pray,
    More like Jesus day by day;
 May I rest me by his side,
        When the tranquil waters glide;
      Born of Him, through grace renewed,
    By his love my will subdued,
    Rich in faith I still would be,
   Let my Saviour dwell in me,

O let me walk with thee, my God,
     As Enoch walked in days of old;
     Place thou my trembling hand in thine,
 And sweet communion with me hold;
       E’en tho’ the path I may not see, 
      Yet, Jesus, let me walk with thee.

       I can not, dare not walk alone;
The tempest rages in the sky;
       A thousand snares beset my feet,
         A thousand foes are lurking nigh;
       Still thou the raging of the sea;
        O Master, let me walk with thee.

         If I may rest my hand in thine,
I’ll count the joys of earth but loss,
       And firmly, bravely journey on; 
         I’ll bear the banner of the cross, 
       Till Zion’s glorious gates I see;
 Yet, Saviour, let me walk with thee.

O where are the reapers that garner in,
 The sheaves of the good from the fields of sin?
       With sickles of truth must the work be done,
And no one may rest till the “harvest home”    

        Go out in the highways and search them all,
The wheat may be there, though the weeds are tall;
       Then search in the highway, and pass none by;
 But gather from all for the home on high,    

        The fields are all rip’ning, and far and wide;
The world now is waiting the harvest tide;
But reapers are few, and the work is great,
 And much will be lost should the harvest wait.    

        So come with your sickles, yes sons of men,
 And gather together the golden grain;
Toil on till the Lord of the harvest come,
Then share ye his joy in the “harvest home.”

Lord, for tomorrow and its needs, I do not pray;
 Keep me from ev’ry stain of sin, Just for today
       Let me no wrong or idle word, Unthinking say;
 Set Thou a seal upon my lips, Just for today.

    I would both diligently work, And duly pray;
 I would be kind in word and deed, Just for today;
       O make me strong to do Thy will, Swift to obey,
 Willing to sacrifice my self, Just for today.

   And if today this life of mine, Should ebb away;
 O may Thy promises divine, Still be my stay.
       So for tomorrow and its needs, I do not pray;
O keep me, guide me, hold me Lord, Just for Today.

Watchman, tell me, does the morning,
Of fair Zion’s glory dawn? 
      Have the signs that mark His coming,
Yet upon thy pathway shone? 
       Pilgrim, yes! Arise, look round thee;
 Light is breaking in the skies;
       Gird thy bridal robes around thee,
 Morning dawns, Arise! Arise!    

        Watchman, see, the light is beaming,
 Brighter still upon thy way; 
       Signs through all the earth are gleaming,
 Omens of the coming day; 
       When the Jubal trumpet, sounding, 
 Shall awake from land and sea; 
       All the saints of God, now sleeping,
Clad in immortality.    

       Watchman, hail the light ascending,
 Of the grand Sabbatic year; 
       All with voices loud proclaiming,
 That the kingdom now is near;
       Pilgrim, yes, I see just yonder,
Canaan’s glorious hights arise;
       Salem, too, appears in grandeur,
      Tow’ring ‘neath its sunlit skies.    

        Watchman, in the golden city,
Seated on his jasper throne;
       Zion’s King, arrayed in beauty,
Reigns in peace from zone to zone; 
       There on sunlit hills and mountains,
 Golden beams serenely glow; 
       Purling streams and crystal fountains,
     On whose banks sweet flowers blow.    

       Watchman, see, the land is nearing,
 With its vernal fruits and flow’rs;
       On, just yonder, O how cheering! 
 Bloom forever Eden’s bow’rs,
       Hark! The choral strains are ringing,
Wafted on the balmy air;
       See the millions, hear them singing,
 Soon the pilgrims will be there.

t may not be on the mountain’s height,
Nor over the stormy sea;
       It may not be at the battle’s front,
My Lord will have need of me;
       But if by a still, small voice he calls,
 To the paths that I do not know;
       I’ll answer, dear Lord, with my hand in thine,
     I’ll go where you want me to go.

    CHORUS:
  I’ll go where you want me to go, dear Lord,
 Over mountains, or plain, or sea;
       I’ll say what you want me to say, dear Lord,
 I’ll be what you want me to be.

    Perhaps today there are loving words,
Which Jesus would have me speak;
   There may be now in the paths of sin,
 Some wand’rer whom I should seek;
       O Saviour, if thou wilt be  my guide
Tho’ rugged and dark the way;
       My voice shall echo thy message sweet, 
I’ll say what you want me to say.

        There’s surely somewhere a lowly place,
 In earth’s harvest fields so wide;
          Where I may labor thro’ life’s short day,
 For Jesus, the crucified;
       So trusting my all to thy tender care,
 And knowing thou lovest me;
       I’ll do thy will with a heart sincere,
         I’ll be what you want me to be.

Oh, to be “Kept for Jesus!” 
Kept, by the power of God;
       Kept, from the world unspotted,
Treading where Jesus trod.

     Oh, to be “Kept for Jesus!”
 Serving as He shall choose;
 “Kept” for the Master’s pleasure;
 “Kept” for the Master’s use.

     Oh, to be “Kept for Jesus!”
 Kept from the world apart; 
 Lowly in mind and spirit,
 Gentle and pure in heart.

     Oh, to be “Kept for Jesus!”
Oh, to be all His own;
 Kept, to be His forever,
 Kept to be His alone!

I have a Friend so precious,
So very dear to me; 
       He loves me with such tender love, 
He loves so faithfully;
       I could not live apart from Him,
 I love to feel Him nigh;
       And so we dwell together,
My God and I.

    I tell Him all my sorrows,
 I tell Him all my joys; 
       I tell Him all that pleases me,
 I tell Him what annoys;
       He tells me what I ought to do,
 He tells me how to try;
       And so we talk together,
 My Lord and I.

    He knows that I am longing,Some weary soul to win;       And so He bids me go and speak,The loving word for Him;       He bids me tell His wondrous love, And why He came to die;       And so we work together, my Lord and I.

All the way my Saviour leads me;
What have I to ask beside?
       Can I doubt His tender mercy,
Who through life has been my guide?
       Heav’nly peace, divinest comfort,
Here by faith in Him to dwell!
       For I know whate’er befall me,
 Jesus doeth all things well;
       For I know whate’er befall me,
 Jesus doeth all things well.

   All the way my Saviour leads me;
   Cheers each winding path I tread;
   Gives me grace for every trial,
   Feeds me with the living bread;
   Though my weary steps may falter,
   And my soul a-thirst may be,
   Gushing from the Rock before me,
   Lo! A spring of joy I see;
   Gushing from the Rock before me,
   Lo! A spring of joy I see.

  All the way my Saviour leads me;
Oh, the fullness of His love!
       Perfect rest to me is promised,
In my Father’s house above;
       When I wake to life immortal,
Wing my flight to realms of day,
       This my song through endless ages,
 Jesus led me all the way;
       This my song through endless ages,
Jesus led me all the way.

The Lord is my shepherd, no want Shall I know;
I feed in green pastures, safe-folded I rest;
       He leadeth my soul where the still waters flow,
 Restores me when wand’ring, redeems when oppressed.

   Tho’ the valley and shadow of death tho’ I stray,
Since thou art my guardian, no evil I fear;
       Thy rod shall defend me, Thy staff be my stay,
 No harm can befall with my Comforter near.

   In the midst of affliction my table is spread,
With blessings unmeasured my cup runneth o’er;
       With perfume and oil thou annointest my head;
O, what shall I ask of thy providence more.

   Let goodness and mercy, my bountiful God,
Still follow my steps till I meet thee above;
       I seek by the path which my fore fathers trod,
Thru’ the land of their sojourn, thy kingdom of love.

Heir of the Kingdom, O why dost thou slumber?
Why art thou sleeping so near thy blest home? 
       Wake thee, arouse thee, and gird on thine armor,
Speed, for the moments are hurrying on.

   Earth’s mighty nations, in strife and commotions,
Tremble with terror, and sink in dismay;
       Listen, ‘tis naught but the chariot’s loud rumbling; 
Heir of the kingdom, no longer delay.

    Stay not O stay not for earth’s vain allurements,
See how its glory is passing away;
       Break the strong fetters the foe hath bound o’er thee;
Heir of the kingdom, turn, turn thee away

   Keep the eye single, the head upward lifted;
Watch for the glory of earth’s coming King; 
       Lo! O’er the mountain-tops light is now breaking,
 Heir of the kingdom, rejoice ye and sing.          "

Saviour, like a shepherd lead us;
Much we need thy tender care;
       In thy pleasant pastures feed us,
For our use thy folds prepare;
       Blessed Jesus, blessed Jesus,
Thou hast bought us, thine we are;
       Blessed Jesus, blessed Jesus,
Thou hast bought us, thine we are.  

       We are thine, do thou befriend us,
Be the Guardian of our way; 
       Keep thy flock, from sin defend us,
Seek us when we go astray,
       Blessed Jesus, blessed Jesus, Hear, 
O hear us, when we pray;
       Blessed Jesus, blessed Jesus, Hear,
O hear us , when we pray.  

      Thou hast promised to receive us,
 Poor and sinful though we be;
       Thou hast mercy to relieve us,
Grace to cleanse, and power to free,
       Blessed Jesus, blessed Jesus,
We will early turn to thee;
       Blessed Jesus, blessed Jesus, 
We will early turn to thee.

hymns.chorus:
He will come.     (He will come)
 Let us watch and be ready;
He will come…   (He will come) 
       Hallelujah! Hallelujah!
       He will come in the clouds,  of his Father’s bright glory; 
    But we know not the hour.

hymns.lyrics:
Lord we have met again;
In this thine house of prayer.
Come Holy Spirit, later rain;
 And fill us with thy power.  

Our hearts to Thee we give;
That we may be like Thee.
Our souls, our minds dear Lord revive;
 Our spirits yearn for Thee.  

And when Thy word is read;
Thy call to us is made.
May we in gratitude respond;
To Thy sweet voice above.  

Prepare for us a place;
In Thy dear heav’n above.
Where all is peace, and joy, and love; 
That we may rest in peace.

Chief of sinners though I be,
Jesus shed His blood for me;
       Died that I might live on high,
Died that I might never die;
       As the branch is to the vine,
I am His and He is mine.  

    O the height of Jesus’ love!
Higher than the heaven above;
       Deeper than the deepest sea,
Lasting as eternity;
       Love that found me wondrous thought!
 Found me when I sought him not.  

    Chief of sinners though I be,
Christ is all in all to me;
       All my wants to Him are known,
 All my sorrows are His own; 
       Safe with Him from earthly strife,
He sustains the hidden life.

We’ve no abiding city here;
Sad truth, were this to be our home;
       But let this thought our spirits cheer,
 We seek a city yet to come,
       We seek a city yet to come.  

    We’ve no abiding city here;
We seek a city out of sight;
       Zion its name the Lord is there, 
It shines with everlasting light,
       It shines with everlasting light.  

    O sweet abode of peace and love,
Where pilgrims, freed from toil, are blest!
       Had I the pinions of a dove,
I’d fly to thee, and be at rest,
       I’d fly to thee, and be at rest.  

    But hush, my soul! Nor dare repine;
The time my God appoints is best;
       While here, to do His will be mine,
 And His to fix my time of rest,
       And His to fix my time of rest.

hymns.chorus:
Glory to his name, Glory to his name;
       There to my heart was the blood applied,
Glory to his name.

His pow’r can make you what ought to be;
       His blood can cleanse your heart, and make you free; 
       His love can fill your soul, and you will see,
       ‘Twas best for Him to have His way with thee.

Love at home, love at home;
Time doth softly, sweetly glide,
When there’s love at home.

hymns.lyrics:
Lonely? No, not lonely,
While Jesus standeth by;
       His presence always cheers me; 
I know that he is nigh,
       Friend-less? No, not friend-less, 
For Jesus is my Friend; 
       I change, but he remaineth, 
The same unto the end. 

     Weary? No, not weary,
While leaning on his breast;
       My soul hath full enjoyment,
 In His eternal rest;
       Helpless? Yes, so helpless;
But I am leaning hard;
       On the mighty arm of Jesus,
And he is keeping guard. 

     Waiting? Yes, I’m waiting; 
He bids me watch and wait, 
       I only wonder often, 
What makes my Lord so late,
       Joyful? Yes, so joyful,
With joy too deep for words;
       A precious, sure foundation, 
The joy that is my Lord’s.

hymns.chorus:
No, never alone, -- no, never alone;
He has promised never to leave me,
Never to leave me alone 
          No, never alone, -- no, never alone;
 He has promised never to leave me,
 Never to leave me alone

hymns.lyrics:
The Homeland! O the Homeland!
The land of the freeborn!
       There’s no night in the Homeland,
But aye the fadeless morn;
       I’m sighing for the Homeland,
My heart is aching here;
       There is no pain in the Homeland,
To which I’m drawing near;
       There is no pain in the Homeland,
To which I’m drawing near. 

     My Lord is in the Homeland,
With angels bright and fair;
There’s no sin the Homeland,
And no temptation there;
       The music of the Homeland,
Is ringing in my ears;
       And when I think of the Homeland,
My eyes are filled with tears;
       And when I think of the Homeland,
 My eyes are filled with tears. 

     The dwellers in the Homeland,
Are beck’ning me to come,
       Where neither death nor sorrow
 Invades their holy home;
       O dear, dear native country!
 O rest and peace above!
       Christ bring us all to the Homeland,
Of Thy redeeming love;
       Christ bring us all to the Homeland,
 Of Thy redeeming love.

O Christian, awake! ‘tis the Master’s command;
With helmet and shield, and a sword in thy hand,
       To meet the bold tempter, go, fearlessly go,
And stand like the brave, with thy face to the foe.    

        Whatever thy danger, take heed and be-ware,
 And turn not thy back, for no armor is there;
   The legions of darkness, if thou wouldst o’er-throw,
Then stand like the brave, with thy face to the foe.    

        The cause of thy Master with vigor defend;
Be watchful, be zealous, and fight to the end; 
Wherever he leads thee, go, valiantly go,
 And stand like the brave, with thy face to the foe.    

        Press on, never doubting, thy Captain is near,
With grace to supply, and with comfort to cheer;
       His love, like a stream in the desert will flow,
 Then stand like the brave, with thy face to the foe.

hymns.chorus:
Praise Him! Praise Him!
Tell of His excellent greatness;
       Praise Him! Praise Him ever in joyful song!

hymns.lyrics:
Who is on the Lord’s side? Always true;
There’s a right and wrong side,
 Where stand you?   

     Thousands on the wrong side, Choose to stand;
   Still ‘tis not the strong side, True and grand.  

Come and join the Lord’s side;
 Ask you why? ‘Tis the only safe side, By and By.

hymns.chorus:
Just now, your doubtings give o’er;
 Just now reject Him no more;
   Just now, throw open the door;
       Let Jesus come into your heart.

hymns.lyrics:
Again the day returns of holy rest,
Which, when he made the world, Jehovah blest;
When, like his own, he bade our labor’s case,
And all be piety, and all be peace.

    Let us devote this consecrated day,
To learn his will, and all we learn obey;
       So shall he hear, when fervently we raise,
 Our supplications, and our songs of praise.

    Lord of all worlds, incline thy gracious ear;
Thy children’s voice in tender mercy hear;
       Bear thy blest promise, fixed as hills, in mind,
And shed renewing grace on lost mankind.

    Father in heaven in whom our hopes confide,
Whose power defends us, and whose precepts guide;
       Through life our surest guardian, and friend,
 Glory supreme be thine till time shall end.

Arise, my soul, arise,
 Shake off thy guilty fears;
The bleeding Sacrifice,
 In my behalf appears;
       Before the throne my Surety stands,
 Before the throne my Surety stands,
 My name is written on his hands

    He ever lives above,
 For me to intercede;
His all redeeming love,
His precious blood to plead;
       His blood was shed for all our race,
 His blood was shed for all our race,
 And sprinkles now the throne of grace.

    Five bleeding wounds he bears,
Received on Calvary;
They pour effectual prayers,
 They strongly speak of me;
       “Forgive him, O, forgive!” they cry,
 “Forgive him, O, forgive!” they cry,
“Nor let the contrite sinner die!”

    The Father hears him pray, His dear, anointed One;
       He would not turn away, The presence of his Son;
       His Spirit answers to the blood,
 His Spirit answers to the blood,
 And tells me I am born of God.

hymns.chorus:
Glory! glory! how the angels sing;
Glory! glory! how the loud harps ring;
       ‘Tis the ransomed army, like a mighty sea,
 Pealing forth the anthem of the free.

Only trust him, only trust him, Only trust him now;
    He will save you, he will save you,
    He will save you now.

hymns.lyrics:
See, Israel’s gentle shepherd stands, With all engaging charms;    Hark, how He calls the tender lambs, 9And folds them in His arms!    

   ‘Permit them to approach,” He cries “Nor scorn their humble name;
    For ‘twas to bless such souls as these, The Lord of angels came.”

    We bring them, Lord, in thankful hands, And yield them up to Thee;
    Joyful we ourselves are Thine, Thine let our off spring be.

O, God our help in ages past, Our hope for years to come;
    Our shelter from the stormy blast, And our eternal home!

    Under the shadow of Thy throne, Thy saints have dwelt secure;
    Sufficient is Thine arm alone, And our defence is sure.

    Before the hills in order stood, Or each received her frame;
    From everlasting Thou art God, To endless years the same.

    A thousand ages in Thy sight, Are like an ev’ning gone;
    Short as the watch that ends the night, Before the rising sun.

Jesus, I will follow Thee,
      For I hear Thee calling me;
      Loving, trusting, glad I come,
      To let Thee lead me home. 

      Little eyes might lose the way,
      Little feet might go astray;
      I might weak and weary be,
      But Thou art strong for me. 

      Grief and want may be my foes;
      Foolish sins my way oppose;
      Full of courage I will be,
      Whene’er I follow Thee.

Master the tempest is raging!
      The billows are tossing high!
      The sky is o’er shadowed with blackness;
      No shelter or help is nigh;
      Carest Thou not that we perish? 
      How canst Thou lie asleep,
      When each moment so madly is threatening,
      A grave in the angry deep. 

      Master with anguish of spirit,
      I bow in my grief today;
      The depths of sad hearts are troubled;
      O, waken and save I pray!
      Torrents of sin and of anguish,
      Sweep o’er my sinking soul;
      And I perish! I perish dear Master;
      O hasten, and take control. 

      Master, the terror is over,
      The element sweetly rest;
      Earth’s sun is in the calm lake is mirrored,
      And heaven’s within my breast;
      Linger O blessed Redeemer,
      Leave me alone no more;
      And with joy I shall make the blest harbor,
      And rest on the blissful shore.

I have a Saviour, he’s pleading in glory,
      A dear, loving Saviour, tho’ earth-friends be few;
      And now he is watching in tenderness o’er me,
      And O that my Saviour were your Saviour too. 

      I have a Father ; to me He has given,
      A hope for eternity, blessed and true;
      And soon He will call me to meet Him in heaven,
      But oh that He’d let me bring with me, too. 

      I have a robe; ‘tis resplendent in whiteness,
      Awaiting in glory my wondering view;
      Oh, when I receive it, all shining in brightness,
      Dear friend, could I see you receiving one, too. 

      To me has been given a peace like a river;
      A peace that the friends of this world never knew;
      And Christ is the Author, and Christ is the Giver,
      And O that his peace might be given to you. 

      When Jesus has found you, tell others the story,
      That my loving Saviour is your Saviour too;
      Then that your Saviour will bring them to glory,
      And prayer will be answered, ‘twas answered for you

O heart bowed down with sorrow! O eyes that long for sight!
      There’s gladness in the believing; In Jesus there is light. 

      Earth’s fleeting gain and pleasure, Can never satisfy;
      ‘Tis love our joy doth measure, For love can never die. 

      Divinest consolation, Doth Christ the Healer give;
      Art thou in condemnation? Repent, believe, and live. 

      His peace is like a river, His love is like a song;
      His yoke’s a burden never; ‘Tis easy all the way.

Hark! Ten thousand harps and voices,
 Sound the note of praise above;
       Jesus reigns, and heav’n rejoices,
 Jesus reigns, the God of love; 
       See, he its on yonder throne;
 Jesus rules the world alone,
       Hallelujah! Hallelujah! Hallelujah! Amen. 

      King of glory, reign forever,
 Thine an everlasting crown;
       Nothing from thy love shall ever,
 Those whom dost seal thine own;
       Happy objects of thy grace, 
 Destined to behold thy face, 
       Hallelujah! Hallelujah! Hallelujah! Amen. 

     Saviour, hasten thine appearing;
Bring, O bring, the glorious day;
       When the awful summons hearing,
 Heav’n and earth shall pass away!
       Then with golden harps, we’ll sing,
 “Glory, glory to our King.”
       Hallelujah! Hallelujah! Hallelujah! Amen.

Worthy, worthy, is the Lamb,
 Worthy, worthy, is the Lamb;
       Worthy, worthy, is the Lamb,That was slain. 

     Saviour, let Thy kingdom come!
 Now  the power of sin consume; 
       Bring Thy blest millennium, 
Holy Lamb. 

     Thus may we each moment feel,
Love Him, serve Him, praise Him still;
       Till we all on Zion’s hill, See the Lamb.

Sound the battle cry, See! The foe is nigh;
Raise the standard high for the Lord;
       Gird your armor on, Stand firm every one,Rest your cause upon His holy word. 

      Strong to meet the foe, Marching on we go,
 While our cause we know  must prevail;
       Shield and banner bright, Gleaming in the light,
 Battling for the right, we ne’er can fail. 

      O Thou God of all Hear us while we call,
Help us one and all, by Thy grace;
       When the battle’s done, And the victory won, 
 May we wear the crown before Thy face.

hymns.chorus:
Lead me, lead me, Saviour, lead me, lest I stray; 
       Gently down the stream of time,
Lead me Saviour, all the way.

hymns.lyrics:
We gather together to ask the Lord’s blessing;
He chastens and hastens His will to make known;
The wicked oppressing now cease from distressing
Sing praises to His name; He forgets not His own.

Beside us to guide us, our God with us joining,
Ordaining, maintaining His kingdom divine;
So from the beginning the fight we were winning;
Thou, Lord, wast at our side; all glory be Thine!

We all do extol Thee, Thou Leader triumphant,
And pray that Thou still our Defender wilt be.
Let Thy congregation escape tribulation;
Thy name be ever praised! O Lord, make us free!

The God of Abraham praise,
Who reigns enthroned above;
Ancient of everlasting days,
And God of love;
Jehovah! Great I AM!
By earth and heaven confessed;
I bow and bless the sacred name,
Forever blest.

The God of Abraham praise,
At whose supreme command
From earth I rise, and seek the joys
At His right hand;
I all on earth forsake,
Its wisdom, fame, and power;
And Him my only portion make,
My shield and tower.

The whole triumphant host
Give thanks to God on high;
“Hail, Father, Son, and Holy Ghost”
They ever cry;
Hail, Abraham’s God and mine,
I join the heavenly lays;
All might and majesty are Thine,
And endless praise.

All people that on earth do dwell,
Sing to the Lord with cheerful voice;
Him serve with mirth, His praise forth tell,
Come ye before Him and rejoice.

Know that the Lord is God indeed;
Without our aid He did us make;
We are His folk, He doth us feed,
And for His sheep He doth us take.

O enter then His gates with praise,
approach with joy His courts unto;
Praise, laud, and bless His name always,
For it is seemly so to do.

For why the Lord our God is good,
His mercy is forever sure;
His truth at all times firmly stood,
And shall from age to age endure.

Praise the Lord! you heavens, adore Him;
Praise Him, angels in the height;
Sun and moon, rejoice before Him;
Praise Him, all you stars of light.
Praise the Lord, for He has spoken;
Worlds His mighty voice obeyed;
Laws which never shall be broken
For their guidance He has made.

Praise the Lord! for He is glorious;
Never shall His promise fail.
God has made His saints victorious;
Sin and death shall not prevail.
Praise the God of our salvation!
Hosts on high, His power proclaim;
Heaven and earth and all creation,
Laud and magnify His name.

Worship, honour, glory, blessing,
Lord, we offer as our gift.
Young and old, Your praise expressing,
Our glad songs to You we lift.
All the saints in heaven adore You,
We would join their glad acclaim;
As your angels serve before You,
So on earth we praise Your name.

hymns.chorus:
O Saviour, stay this night with me;
Behold, ’tis eventide!
O Saviour, stay this night with me;
Behold, ’tis eventide.

hymns.lyrics:
Abide with me; fast falls the eventide;
The darkness deepens; Lord, with
me abide!
When other helpers fail, and comforts flee,
Help of the helpless, O abide with me!

Swift to its close ebbs out life’s little day;
Earth’s joys grow dim, its glories pass away;
Change and decay in all around I see;
O Thou, who changest not, abide with me!

I need Thy presence every passing hour;
What but Thy grace can foil the tempter’s power?
Who like Thyself my guide and stay can be?
Through cloud and sunshine, O abide with me!

I fear no foe, with Thee at hand to bless;
Ills have no weight, and tears no bitterness:
Where is death’s sting? Where, grave, thy victory?
I triumph still if Thou abide with me!

Jesus, tender Shepherd, hear me,
Bless Thy little lamb tonight;
Through the darkness be Thou near me;
Watch my sleep till morning light.

All this day Thy hand has led me,
And I thank Thee for Thy care;
Thou hast clothed me, warmed and fed me;
Listen to my evening prayer.

God be with you till we meet again;
By His counsels guide, uphold you,
With His sheep securely fold you;
God be with you till we meet again.

God be with you till we meet again;
’Neath His wings protecting hide you,
Daily manna still provide you;
God be with you till we meet again.

God be with you till we meet again;
When life’s perils thick confound you,
Put His arms unfailing round you;
God be with you till we meet again.

God be with you till we meet again;
Keep love’s banner floating o’er you,
Smite death’s threatening wave before you;
God be with you till we meet again.

Lord, make us more holy;
Lord, make us more holy;
Lord, make us more holy
Until we meet again.

Lord, make us more faithful;
Lord, make us more faithful;
Lord, make us more faithful
Until we meet again.

Lord, make us more humble;
Lord, make us more humble;
Lord, make us more humble;
Until we meet again.

Lord, make us more loving;
Lord, make us more loving;
Lord, make us more loving
Until we meet again.
Like Jesus, the Saviour,
Until we meet again.

Praise ye the Father for His loving kindness
Tenderly cares He for His erring children;
Praise Him, ye angels, Praise Him in the heavens;
Praise ye Jehovah!

Praise ye the Saviour, great is His compassion,
Graciously cares He for His chosen people;
Young men and maidens, ye old men and children,
Praise ye the Saviour!

Praise ye the Spirit, Comforter of Israel,
Sent of the Father and the Son to bless us;
Praise ye the Father, Son, and Holy Spirit,
Praise the Eternal Three!

For God so loved us, He sent the saviour:
For God so loved us, and loves me too.

He sent the Saviour, the blest Redeemer;
He sent the Saviour to set me free.

He bade me welcome, O word of mercy;
He bade me welcome, O voice divine.

Glory and honour, O Love eternal;
To Him be given while life shall last.

Before Jehovah’s awful throne,
Ye nations, bow with sacred joy;
Know that the Lord is God alone;
He can create, and He destroy.

His sovereign power, without our aid,
Made us of clay, and formed us men;
and when like wandering sheep we strayed,
He brought us to His fold again.

We’ll crowd His gates with thankful songs,
High as the heavens our voices raise;
And earth, with her ten thousand tongues,
Shall fill His courts with sounding praise.

Wide as the world is His command,
Vast as Eternity His love;
Firm as a rock His truth shall stand,
When rolling years shall cease to move.

God the omnipotent! King, who ordainest,
Great winds Thy clarions, the lightnings Thy sword;
Show forth Thy pity on high where Thou reignest,
Give to us peace, O most merciful Lord.

God the all-merciful! earth hath forsaken
Thy precepts holy, and slighted Thy word;
Bid not Thy wrath in its terrors awaken;
Give to us peace, O most merciful Lord.

God the all-righteous One! man hath defied Thee;
Yet to eternity standeth Thy word;
Falsehood and wrong shall not tarry beside Thee;
Prosper the right, O most merciful Lord.

So shall we render Thee thankful devotion,
For Thy deliverance from peril and sword,
Singing in chorus from ocean to ocean,
“Thine is the power and the glory, O Lord.”

hymns.chorus:
Then sings my soul, my Saviour God to Thee;
How great Thou art, how great Thou art!
Then sings my soul, my Saviour God to Thee;
How great Thou art, How great Thou art!

hymns.lyrics:
Angels from the realms of glory,
Wing your flight o’er all the earth;
Ye, who sang creation’s story,
Now proclaim messiah’s birth;
Come and worship, Come and worship,
Worship Christ, the newborn King.

Shepherds, in the field abiding,
Watching o’er your flocks by night,
God with man is now residing;
Yonder shines the Infant Light;
Come and worship, Come and worship,
Worship Christ, the newborn King.

Sages, leave your contemplations,
Brighter visions beam afar;
Seek the great Desire of nations;
Ye have seen His natal star;
Come and worship, Come and worship,
Worship Christ, the newborn King.

Saints, before the altar bending,
Watching long in hope and fear,
Suddenly the Lord, descending,
In His temple shall appear;
Come and worship, Come and worship,
Worship Christ, the newborn King.

Songs of thankfulness and praise,
Jesus, Lord, to You we raise,
Manifested by the star
To the sages from afar;
Branch of royal David’s stem
In Your birth at Bethlehem;
Anthems be to You addressed,
God in man made manifest.

Manifest at Jordan’s stream,
Prophet, Priest, and King supreme;
And at Cana, wedding guest,
In Your Godhead manifest;
Manifest in power divine,
Changing water into wine;
Anthems be to You addressed,
God in man made manifest.

Manifest in making whole
Palsied limbs and fainting soul;
Manifest in valiant fight,
Quelling all the devil’s might;
Manifest in gracious will,
Ever bringing good from ill;
Anthems be to You addressed,
God in man made manifest.

Grant us grace to see You, Lord,
Mirrored in Your holy Word;
May we imitate Your way,
And be pure, as pure we may,
That we like to You may be
At Your great epiphany;
Let us praise You, ever blest,
God in man made manifest.

Go to dark Gethsemane,
Ye that feel the tempter’s power;
Your Redeemer’s conflict see;
Watch with Him one bitter hour;
Turn not from His griefs away;
Learn of Jesus Christ to pray.

See Him at the judgement hall,
Beaten, bound, reviled, arraigned;
See Him meekly bearing all;
Love to man His soul sustained;
Shun not suffering, shame, or loss;
Learn of Christ to bear the cross.

Calvary’s mournful mountain climb;
There adoring at His feet,
Mark that miracle of time,
God’s own sacrifice complete;
“It is finished!” hear Him cry;
Learn of Jesus Christ to die.

Now the green blade rises from the buried grain,
Wheat that in dark earth many days has lain;
Love lives again, that with the dead has been;
Love is coming again like wheat arising green.

In the grave they laid Him, love by hatred slain,
Thinking that He would never wake again,
Laid in the earth like grain that sleeps unseen;
Love is coming again like wheat arising green.

Forth He came in triumph, like the risen grain,
He that for three days in the grave had lain;
Raised from the dead, my living Lord is seen;
Love is coming again like wheat arising green.

When our hearts are wintry, grieving, or in pain,
Your touch can call us back to life again,
Fields of our hearts that dead and bare have been;
Love is come again like wheat arising green.

hymns.chorus:
Jesus paid it all,
All to Him I owe;
Sin had left a crimson stain;
He washed it white as snow.

All that thrills my soul is Jesus;
He is more than life to me;
And the fairest of ten thousand,
In my blessed Lord I see.

hymns.lyrics:
Tell it to every kindred and nation,
Tell it far and near;
Earth’s darkest night will fade with the dawning,
Jesus will soon appear.

Nations again in strife and commotion,
Warnings by the way;
Signs in the heavens, unerring omens,
Herald the glorious day.

Children of God look up with rejoicing;
Shout and sing His praise;
Blessed are they who, waiting and watching,
Look for the dawning rays.

Seek ye first the kingdom, ’Tis your Father’s will.
So the voice of Jesus bids us follow still.
Saviour, we would hear Thee, Follow, find, and see;
And in life’s adventure Thy disciples be.

As for hidden treasure, or for matchless pearl,
When at last discovered, some will sell their all:
So, when breaks the vision of that kingdom fair,
Ours shall be its riches And its beauty rare.

As the silent leaven works its secret way,
Or as grows the seed grain through the night and day;
Lord, so be the increase, peaceable but sure,
Of Thy word within us, And Thy kingdom’s power.

As the tender seedling grows up tall and strong
And the birds of heaven to its branches throng;
So shall all God’s children, from the east and west;
Gather to His kingdom, In its shadow rest.

Humblest shall be greatest, poor in spirit reign;
Home shall come the childlike, born through Thee again;
Eager hearts arrive there on the pilgrim’s road,
Hail! the kingdom glorious Of the living God!

Christ, whose glory fills the skies,
Christ, the true, the only light,
Sun of Righteousness, arise,
Triumph o’er the shades of night;
Dayspring from on high, be near;
Daystar, in my heart appear.

Dark and cheerless is the morn
Unaccompanied by Thee;
Joyless is the day’s return
Till Thy mercy’s beams I see;
Till they inward light impart,
Cheer my eyes and warm my heart.

Visit, then, this soul of mine;
Pierce the gloom of sin and grief;
Fill me, Radiancy divine;
Scatter all my unbelief;
More and more Thyself display,
Shining to the perfect day.

Christ is the world’s Light,
He and none other;
Born in our darkness, He became our brother.
If we have seen Him, we have seen the Father:
Glory to God on high!

Christ is the world’s Peace,
He and none other;
No one can serve Him and despise another.
Who else unites us one in God the Father?
Glory to God on high!

Christ is the world’s Life,
He and none other;
Sold once for silver, murdered here, our brother,
He who redeems us reigns with God the Father.
Glory to God on high!

Give God the glory,
God and none other;
Give God the glory, Spirit, Son, and Father;
Give God the glory, God in Man my brother;
Glory to God on high!

Jesus, Thou joy of loving hearts!
Thou fount of life! Thou light of men!
From the best bliss that earth imparts,
We turn unfilled to Thee again.

Thy truth unchanged has ever stood;
Thou savest those that on Thee call;
To them that seek Thee Thou art good,
To them that find Thee, all in all.

We taste Thee, O Thou living Bread,
And long to feast upon Thee still;
We drink of Thee, the Fountainhead,
And thirst our souls from Thee to fill!

Our restless spirits yearn for Thee,
Where’er our changeful lot is cast;
Glad, when Thy gracious smile we see,
Blest, when our faith can hold Thee fast.

O Jesus, ever with us stay;
Make all our moments calm and bright;
Chase the dark night of sin away,
Shed o’er the world Thy holy light!

Come, my Way, my Truth, my Life:
Such a Way, as gives us breath;
Such a Truth, as ends all strife;
Such a Life, as killeth death.

Come, my Light, my Feast, my Strength:
Such a Light, as shows a feast;
Such a Feast, as mends in length;
Such a Strength, as makes His guest.

Come, my Joy, my Love, my Heart:
Such a Joy, as none can move;
Such a Love, as none can part;
Such a Heart, as joys in love.

Praise Him! praise Him! Jesus, our blessed Redeemer!
Sing, O Earth- His wonderful love proclaim!
Hail Him! hail Him! highest archangels in glory;
Strength and honour give to His holy name!
Like a shepherd, Jesus will guard His children,
In His arms He carries them all day long;

Praise Him! praise Him! Jesus, our blessed Redeemer!
For our sins He suffered, and bled and died;
He- our Rock, our hope of eternal salvation,
Hail Him! hail Him! Jesus the Crucified.
Sound His praises! Jesus who bore our sorrows,
Love unbounded, wonderful, deep and strong;

Praise Him! praise Him! Jesus, our blessed Redeemer!
Heavenly portals, loud with hosannas ring!
Jesus, Saviour, reigneth forever and ever;
Crown Him! crown Him! Prophet, and Priest, and King!
Christ is coming over the world victorious,
Power and glory unto the Lord belong;

Ye servants of God, your Master proclaim,
And publish abroad His wonderful name;
The name all victorious of Jesus extol;
His kingdom is glorious, He rules over all.

God ruleth on high, almighty to save;
And still He is nigh- His presence we have;
The great congregation His triumph shall sing,
Ascribing salvation to Jesus our King.

“Salvation to God, Who sits on the throne,”
Let all cry aloud, and honour the Son;
The praises of Jesus the angels proclaim,
Fall down on their faces, and worship the Lamb.

Then let us adore, and give Him His right,
All glory and power, all wisdom and might;
All honour and blessing with angels above,
And thanks never ceasing, for infinite love.

Hover o’er me Holy Spirit,
Bathe my trembling heart and brow;
Fill me with Thy hallowed presence,
Come, O come and fill me now.

Thou canst fill me, gracious Spirit,
Though I cannot tell Thee how;
But I need Thee, greatly need Thee;
Come, O come and fill me now.

I am weakness, full of weakness;
At Thy sacred feet I bow;
Blest, divine, eternal Spirit,
Fill with love, and fill me now.

Cleanse and comfort, bless and save me;
Bathe, O bathe my heart and brow;
Thou art comforting and saving,
Thou art sweetly filling now.

Spirit of God! descend upon my heart;
Wean it from earth; through all its pulses move;
Stoop to my weakness, mighty as Thou art,
And make me love Thee as I ought to love.

I ask no dream, no prophet ecstasies;
No sudden rending of the veil of clay;
No angel visitant, no op’ning skies;
But take the dimness of my soul away.

Hast Thou not bid us love Thee, God and King?
All, all thine own, soul, heart, and strength, and mind;
I see Thy cross, there teach my heart to cling:
O let me seek Thee, and O let me find!

Teach me to feel  that Thou art always nigh;
Teach me the struggles of the soul to bear;
To check the rising doubt, the rebel sigh;
Teach me the patience of unanswered prayer.

Teach me to love Thee as Thine angels love,
One holy passion filling all my frame;
The baptism of the heav’n-descended dove,
My heart an altar, and Thy love the flame.

Break thou the bread of life,
Dear Lord, to me,
As Thou didst break the loaves
Beside the sea;
Beyond the sacred page
I seek Thee, Lord;
My spirit pants for Thee,
O Living Word.

Bless Thou the truth, dear Lord,
To me, to me,
As Thou didst bless the bread
By Galilee;
Then shall all bondage cease,
All fetters fall;
And I shall find my peace,
My all in all.

Thou art the bread of life,
O Lord, to me;
Thy holy Word the truth
That saveth me;
Give me to eat and live
With Thee above;
Teach me to love Thy truth,
For Thou art love.

Spirit and life are they,
Words Thou dost speak;
I hasten to obey,
But I am weak;
Thou art my only help,
Thou art my life;
Heeding Thy holy Word
I win the strife.

Heavenly Father, bless us now;
At the cross of Christ we bow;
Take our guilt and grief away;
Hear and heal us now, we pray.

Now, O Lord, this very hour,
Send Thy grace and show Thy power;
While we rest upon Thy word,
Come, and bless us now, O Lord!

Mercy now, O Lord, we plead
In this hour of utter need;
Turn us not away unblest;
Calm our anguish into rest.

O Thou loving, blessed One,
Rising o’er us like the sun,
Light and life art Thou within:
Saviour, Thou, from every sin!

I’ve wandered far away from God,
Now I’m coming home;
The paths of sin too long I’ve trod;
Lord, I’m coming home.

I’ve wasted many precious years,
Now I’m coming home;
I now repent with bitter tears;
Lord, I’m coming home.

I’m tired of sin and straying Lord,
Now I’m coming home;
I’ll trust Thy love, believe Thy word;
Lord, I’m coming home.

My only hope, my only plea,
Now I’m coming home;
That Jesus died, and died for me;
Lord, I’m coming home.

I need His cleansing blood I know,
Now I’m coming home;
O wash me whiter than the snow;
Lord, I’m coming home.

hymns.chorus:
Coming home, coming home
Nevermore to roam;
Open wide Thine arms of love;
Lord, I’m coming home.

hymns.lyrics:
Nearer, still nearer, close to Thy heart,
Draw me, my Saviour, so precious Thou art;
Fold me, O fold me close to Thy breast,
Shelter me safe in that haven of rest,
Shelter me safe in that haven of rest.

Nearer, still nearer, nothing I bring,
Nought as an offering to Jesus my King-
Only my sinful now contrite heart;
Grant me the cleansing Thy blood doth impart,
Grant me the cleansing Thy blood doth impart.

Nearer, still nearer, Lord, to be Thine;
Sin, with its follies, I gladly resign,
All of its pleasures, pomp and its pride;
Give me but Jesus, my Lord crucified,
Give me but Jesus, my Lord crucified.

Nearer, still nearer, while life shall last;
Till safe in glory my anchor is cast;
Through endless ages, ever to be,
Nearer, my Saviour, still nearer to Thee,
Nearer, my Saviour, still nearer to Thee .

In the blood from the cross
I have been washed from sin;
But to be free from dross,
Still I would enter in.

Day by day, hour by hour,
Blessings are sent to me;
But for more of His power
Ever my prayer shall be.

Near to Christ I would live,
Following Him each day;
What I ask He will give;
So then with faith I pray.

Now I have peace, sweet peace,
While in this world of sin;
But to pray I’ll not cease
Till I am pure within.

I am coming to the cross;
I am poor, and weak, and blind;
I am counting all but dross;
I shall full salvation find.

Long my heart has sighed for Thee;
Long has evil reigned within;
Jesus sweetly speaks to me,
“I will cleanse you from all sin.”

Here I give my all to Thee -
Friends, and time, and earthly store;
Soul and body Thine to be,
Wholly Thine forevermore.

Jesus comes! He fills my soul!
Perfected in Him I am;
I am every whit made whole-
Glory, glory to the Lamb!

hymns.chorus:
I am trusting, Lord, in Thee,
O Thou Lamb of Calvary;
Humbly at Thy cross I bow;
Save me, Jesus, save me now.

hymns.lyrics:
I would be, dear Saviour, wholly Thine;
Teach me how, teach me how;
I would do Thy will, O Lord, not mine;
Help me, help me now.

What is worldly pleasure, wealth, or fame,
Without Thee, without Thee?
I will leave them all for Thy dear name,
This my wealth shall be.

As I cast earth’s transient joys behind,
Come Thou near, come Thou near;
In Thy presence all in all I find,
’Tis my comfort here.

All to Jesus I surrender,
All to Him I freely give;
I will ever love and trust Him,
In His presence daily live;

All to Jesus I surrender;
Humbly at His feet I bow,
Worldly pleasures all forsaken;
Take me, Jesus, take me now;

All to Jesus I surrender;
Make me, Saviour, wholly Thine;
Let me feel the Holy Spirit,
Truly know that Thou art mine.

All to Jesus I surrender,
Now I feel the sacred flame.
O the joy of full salvation!
Glory, glory, to His name!

Earthly pleasures vainly call me;
I would be like Jesus;
Nothing worldly shall enthrall me;
I would be like Jesus.

He has broken every fetter,
I would be like Jesus;
That my soul may serve Him better,
I would be like Jesus.

All the way from earth to glory,
I would be like Jesus;
Telling o’er and o’er the story,
I would be like Jesus.

That in heaven He may meet me,
I would be like Jesus;
That His words “Well done” may greet me,
I would be like Jesus.

hymns.chorus:
Lest I forget Gethsemane;
Lest I forget Thine agony;
Lest I forget Thy love for me,
Lead me to Calvary.

hymns.lyrics:
Lord Jesus, I long to be perfectly whole;
I want Thee forever to live in my soul;
Break down every idol, cast out every foe;
Now wash me, and I shall be whiter than snow.

Lord Jesus, look down from Thy throne in the skies,
And help me to make a complete sacrifice;
I give up myself, and whatever I know;
Now wash me, and I shall be whiter than snow.

Lord Jesus, for this I most humbly entreat;
I wait, blessed Lord, at Thy crucified feet,
By faith, for my cleansing; I see Thy blood flow;
Now wash me, and I shall be whiter than snow.

Lord Jesus, Thou seest I patiently wait;
Come now, and within me a new heart create;
To those who have sought Thee, Thou never said’st No;
Now wash me, and I shall be whiter than snow.

My Jesus, I love Thee, I know Thou art mine;
For Thee all the follies of sin I resign;
My gracious Redeemer, my Saviour art Thou;
If ever I loved Thee, my Jesus, ’tis now.

I love Thee because Thou hast first loved me,
And purchased my pardon on Calvary’s tree;
I love Thee for wearing the thorns on Thy brow;
If ever I loved Thee, my Jesus, ’tis now.

I’ll love Thee in life, I will love Thee ’til death,
And praise Thee as long as Thou lendest me breath;
And say when the death dew lies cold on my brow,
If ever I loved Thee, my Jesus, ’tis now.

In mansions of glory and endless delight;
I’ll ever adore Thee in heaven so bright;
I’ll sing with the glittering crown on my brow,
If ever I loved thee, my Jesus, ’tis now.

Jesus, I my cross have taken,
All to leave and follow Thee;
All things else I have forsaken;
Thou from hence my all shalt be.
Perish every fond ambition,
All I’ve sought, or hoped, or known;
Yet how rich is my condition,
While I prove the Lord my own.

Let the world despise and leave me -
They have left my Saviour, too;
Human hearts and looks deceive me -
Thou art faithful, Thou art true.
O, ’tis not in grief to harm me,
While Thy love is left to me;
O, ’twere not in joy to charm me,
If that love be hid from me.

Soul, then know thy full salvation;
Rise o’er sin, and fear, and care;
Joy to find in every station
Something still to do or bear.
Think what Spirit dwells within thee;
Think what Father’s smiles are thine;
Think that Jesus died to win thee;
Child of Heaven, canst thou repine?

Haste thee on from grace to glory,
Armed by faith and winged by prayer;
Heaven’s eternal day’s before thee;
God’s own hand shall guide thee there.
Soon shall close thy earthly mission,
Soon shall pass thy pilgrim days;
Hope shall change to glad fruition
Faith to sight, and prayer to praise.

hymns.chorus:
Silently now I wait for Thee,
Ready, my God, Thy will to see;
Open my eyes, illumine me, Spirit divine!

hymns.lyrics:
Take the world, but give me Jesus;
All its joys are but a name,
But His love abideth ever,
Through eternal years the same.

Take the world, but give me Jesus,
Sweetest comfort of my soul;
With my Saviour watching o’er me,
I can sing, though billows roll.

Take the world, but give me Jesus;
Let me view His constant smile;
Then throughout my pilgrim journey
Light will cheer me all the while.

Take the world, but give me Jesus;
In His cross my trust shall be,
Till, with clearer, brighter vision,
Face to face my Lord I see.

God is my strong salvation,
What foe have I to fear?
In darkness and temptation,
My Light, my Help, is near:
Though hosts encamp around me,
Firm in the fight I stand;
What terror can confound me,
With God at my right hand?

Place on the Lord reliance;
My soul with courage wait;
His truth be thine affiance,
When faint and desolate.
His might thy heart shall strengthen,
His love thy joy increase;
Mercy thy days shall lengthen;
The Lord will give thee peace.

hymns.chorus:
Praise the Lord, praise the Lord,
Let the earth hear his voice;
Praise the Lord, praise the Lord,
Let the people rejoice;
O come to the Father, through Jesus the Son,
And give Him the glory, great things He hath done.

hymns.lyrics:
O Zion, haste, thy mission high fulfilling,
To tell to all the world that God is light;
That He who made all nations is not willing
One soul should perish, lost in shades of night.

Proclaim to every people, tongue, and nation
That God, in whom they live and move, is love;
Tell how he stooped to save His lost creation,
And died on earth that man might live above.

Give of thy sons to bear the message glorious;
Give of thy wealth to speed them on their way;
Pour out thy soul for them in prayer victorious;
And all thou spendest Jesus will repay.

He comes again; O Zion, ere thou meet Him,
Make known to every heart His saving grace;
Let none whom He hath ransomed fail to greet Him,
Through thy neglect, unfit to see His face.

Rescue the perishing,
Care for the dying;
Snatch them in pity from sin and the grave;
Weep o’er the erring one,
Lift up the fallen,
Tell them of Jesus, the mighty to save.

Though they are slighting Him,
Still He is waiting,
Waiting the penitent child to receive.
Plead with them earnestly,
Plead with them gently;
He will forgive if they only believe.

Rescue the perishing,
Duty demands it;
Strength for thy labor the Lord will provide;
Back to the narrow way
Patiently win them;
Tell the poor wanderer a Saviour has died.

Lift Him up, ’tis He that bids you,
Let the dying look and live;
To all weary, thirsting sinners,
Living waters will He give;
And though once so meek and lowly,
Yet the Prince of heaven was He;
And the blind, who grope in darkness,
Through the blood of Christ shall see.

Lift Him up, this precious Saviour,
Let the multitude behold;
They with willing hearts shall seek Him,
He will draw them to His fold;
They shall gather from the wayside,
Hastening on with joyous feet,
They shall bear the cross of Jesus,
And shall find salvation sweet.

Lift Him up in all His glory,
’Tis the Son of God on high;
Lift Him up, His love shall draw them,
E’en the careless shall draw nigh;
Let them hear again the story
Of the cross, the death of shame;
And from tongue to tongue repeat it;
Mighty throngs shall bless His name.

O then lift Him up in singing,
Lift the Saviour up in prayer;
He, the glorious Redeemer,
All the sins of men did bear;
Yes, the young shall bow before Him,
And the old their voices raise;
All the deaf shall hear hosannah;
And the dumb shall shout His praise.

Work, for the night is coming;
Work through the morning hours;
Work while the dew is sparkling;
Work ’mid springing flowers;
Work while the day grows brighter,
Under the glowing sun;
Work, for the night is coming,
When man’s work is done.

Work, for the night is coming;
Work through the sunny noon;
Fill brightest hours with labor,
Rest comes sure and soon;
Give every flying minute;
Something to keep in store;
Work, for the night is coming,
When man works no more.

Work, for the night is coming:
Under the sunset skies,
While their bright tints are glowing,
Work for daylight flies;
Work till the last beam fadeth,
Fadeth to shine no more;
Work, for the Lord is coming,
When man’s work is o’er.

All things are Thine; no gift have we,
Lord of all gifts, to offer Thee;
And hence with grateful hearts today,
Thine own before Thy feet we lay.

Thy will was in the builder’s thought;
Thy hand unseen amidst us wrought;
Thro’ mortal motive, scheme and plan,
Thy wise, eternal purpose ran.

No lack Thy perfect fullness knew;
For human needs and longings grew
This house of prayer- this home of rest.
Here may Thy saints be often blessed.

In weakness and in want we call
On Thee, for whom the heav’ns are small;
Thy glory is Thy children’s good,
Thy joy Thy tender Fatherhood.

O Father! deign these walls to bless;
Make this the abode of righteousness,
And let these doors a gateway be
To lead us from ourselves to Thee!

“Go, preach My gospel”, saith the Lord;
“Bid the whole world My grace receive;
He shall be saved who trusts My word,
And they condemned who disbelieve.”

I’ll make your great commission known,
And ye shall prove My gospel true
By all the works that I have done,
By all the wonders ye shall do.

“Teach all the nations My commands;
I’m with you till the world shall end;
All power is vested in My hands;
I can destroy, and I defend.”

He spake, and light shone round His head;
On a bright cloud to heaven He rode;
They to the farthest nations spread
The grace of their ascended Lord.

Let us break bread together on our knees;
Let us break bread together on our knees.

Let us drink wine together on our knees;
Let us drink wine together on our knees.

Let us praise God together on our knees;
Let us praise God together on our knees.

hymns.chorus:
Cover with His life, whiter than snow;
Fullness of His life then shall I know;
My life of scarlet, my sin and woe,
Cover with His life, whiter than snow.

In His glory, I shall see the King,
And forever endless praises sing;
’Twas on Calvary Jesus died for me;
I shall see the King some day.

hymns.lyrics:
The homeland! O the homeland!
The land of the freeborn!
There’s no night in the homeland,
But aye the fadeless morn;
I’m sighing for the homeland,
My heart is aching here;
There is no pain in the homeland
To which I’m drawing near;
There is no pain in the homeland
To which I’m drawing near.

My Lord is in the homeland,
With angels bright and fair;
There’s no sin in the homeland,
And no temptation there;
The music of the homeland
Is ringing in my ears;
And when I think of the homeland
My eyes are filled with tears;
And when I think of the homeland
My eyes are filled with tears.

The dwellers in the homeland
Are beckoning me to come,
Where neither death nor sorrow
Invades their holy home;
O dear, dear native country!
O rest and peace above!
Christ bring us all to the homeland
Of Thy redeeming love;
Christ bring us all to the homeland
Of Thy redeeming love.

There’ll be no night in heaven,
In that blest world above;
No anxious toil, no weary hours;
For labor there is love.

There’ll be no grief in heaven;
For life is one glad day,
And tears are those of former things
Which all have passed away.

There’ll be no sin in heaven;
Behold that blessed throng
All holy in their spotless robes,
All holy in their song.

I’m a pilgrim, and I’m a stranger;
I can tarry, I can tarry but a night;
Do not detain me, for I am going
To where the fountains are ever flowing.

There the glory is ever shining!
O, my longing heart, my longing heart is there;
Here in this country so dark and dreary,
I long have wandered forlorn and weary.

There’s the city to which I journey;
My Redeemer, my Redeemer is its light!
There is no sorrow, nor any sighing,
Nor any tears there, or any dying.

I’m but a stranger here,
Heaven is my home;
Earth is a desert drear,
Heaven is my home;
Danger and sorrow stand
Round me on every hand;
Heaven is my Fatherland,
Heaven is my home.

What though the tempest rage,
Heaven is my home;
Short is my pilgrimage,
Heaven is my home.
Time’s cold and wintry blast
Soon will be overpast;
I shall reach home at last;
Heaven is my home.

There at my Saviour’s side,
Heaven is my home;
I shall be glorified,
Heaven is my home.
There’ll be the good and blest,
Those I love most and best,
There, too, I soon shall rest;
Heaven is my home.

Long upon the mountains weary,
Have the scattered flock been torn;
Dark the desert paths, and dreary;
Grievous trials have they borne.
Now the gathering call is sounding,
Solemn in its warning voice;
Union, faith, and love, abounding,
Bid the little flock rejoice.

Now the light of truth they’re seeking,
In its onward track pursue;
All the ten commandments keeping,
They are holy, just, and true.
On the words of life they’re feeding,
Precious to their taste so sweet;
All their Master’s precepts heeding,
Bowing humbly at His feet.

In that light of light and beauty,
In that golden city fair,
Soon its pearly gates they’ll enter,
And of all its glories share.
There, divine the soul’s expansions;
Free from sin, and death, and pain;
Tears will never dim those mansions
Where the saints immortal reign.

Soon He comes! with clouds descending;
All His saints, entombed arise;
The redeemed, in anthems blending,
Shout their vict’ry thro’ the skies.
O, we long for Thine appearing;
Come, O Saviour, quickly come!
Blessed hope! our spirits cheering,
Take Thy ransomed children home.

Together let us sweetly live;
I am bound for the land of Canaan.
Together love to Jesus give;
I am bound for the land of Canaan.

Together let us watch and pray;
I am bound for the land of Canaan.
And wait redemption’s joyous day;
I am bound for the land of Canaan.

Our songs of praise shall fill the skies;
I am bound for the land of Canaan.
While higher still our joys shall rise;
I am bound for the land of Canaan.

Then come with me, beloved friend;
I am bound for the land of Canaan.
The joys to come shall never end;
I am bound for the land of Canaan.

Dona nobis pacem, pacem;
Dona nobis pacem.
Dona nobis pacem;
Dona nobis pacem.
Dona nobis pacem;
Dona nobis pacem;

Father, grant us, grant us Your peace;
Oh, loving Father, grant us Your peace.
Grant us, grant us peace;
Grant us, grant us, grant us Your peace.
Grant us, grant us peace;
Loving Father, grant us Your peace.

A coordenous ta paix, ta paix;
A coordenous ta paix.
A coordenous ta paix;
A coordenous ta paix.
A coordenous ta paix;
A coordenous ta paix.

Padre danos, tu paz, tu paz;
Padre danos, danos tu paz.
Padre danos tu paz;
Padre danos, danos tu paz.
Padre danos tu paz;
Padre danos, danos tu paz.

Come, ye disconsolate, where’er ye languish;
Come to the mercy seat, fervently kneel;
Here bring your wounded hearts, here tell your anguish;
Earth has no sorrow that heaven cannot heal.

Joy of the comfortless, light of the straying,
Hope of the penitent, fadeless and pure!
Here speaks the Comforter, tenderly saying,
“Earth has no sorrow that heaven cannot cure.”

Here see the bread of Life; see waters flowing
Forth from the throne of God, pure from above;
Come to the feast of love - come, ever knowing
Earth has no sorrow but heaven can remove.

Father, lead me day by day,
Ever in Thine own sweet way;
Teach me to be pure and true;
Show me what I ought to do.

When in danger, make me brave;
Make me know that Thou canst save;
Keep me safe by Thy dear side;
Let me in Thy love abide.

When I’m tempted to do wrong,
Make me steadfast, wise, and strong;
And when all alone I stand,
Shield me with Thy mighty hand.

May I do the good I know,
Be Thy loving child below,
Then at last go home to Thee,
Evermore Thy child to be.

Father, I stretch my hands to Thee;
No other help I know;
If Thou withdraw Thyself from me,
Ah, whither shall I go?

On Thy dear Son I now believe;
O let me feel Thy power;
And all my varied wants relieve,
In this accepted hour.

Author of faith! to Thee I lift
My weary, longing eyes;
O let me now receive that gift;
My soul without it dies.

Surely Thou canst not let me die;
O speak, and I shall live;
And here I will unwearied lie,
Till Thou Thy Spirit give.

How would my fainting soul rejoice
Could I but see Thy face!
Now let me hear Thy quickening voice,
And taste Thy pardoning grace.

I do believe, I now believe
That Jesus died for me,
And that He shed His precious blood
From sin to set me free.

Jesus, lover of my soul,
Let me to Thy bosom fly,
While the billows near me roll,
While the tempest still is high;
Hide me, O my Saviour, hide!
Till the storm of life is past;
Safe into the haven guide,
O receive my soul at last!

Other refuge have I none,
Hangs my helpless soul on Thee;
Leave, O leave me not alone!
Still support and comfort me;
All my trust on Thee is stayed,
All my help from Thee I bring;
Cover my defenseless head
With the shadow of Thy wing.

Thou, O Christ, art all I want,
More than all in Thee I find;
Raise the fallen, cheer the faint,
Heal the sick, and lead the blind.
Just and holy is Thy name,
I am all unrighteousness;
Vile and full of sin I am,
Thou art full of truth and grace.

Plenteous grace with Thee is found
Grace to pardon all my sin;
Let the healing streams abound,
Make and keep me pure within;
Thou of life the Fountain art,
Freely let me take of Thee;
Spring Thou up within my heart,
Rise to all eternity.

Jesus, lover of my soul,
Let me to Thy bosom fly,
While the billows near me roll,
While the tempest still is high;
Hide me, O my Saviour, hide!
Till the storm of life is past;
Safe into the haven guide,
O receive my soul at last!

Other refuge have I none,
Hangs my helpless soul on Thee;
Leave, O leave me not alone!
Still support and comfort me;
All my trust on Thee is stayed,
All my help from Thee I bring;
Cover my defenseless head
With the shadow of Thy wing.

Thou, O Christ, art all I want,
More than all in Thee I find;
Raise the fallen, cheer the faint,
Heal the sick, and lead the blind.
Just and holy is Thy name
I am all unrighteousness;
Vile and full of sin I am,
Thou art full of truth and grace.

Plenteous grace with Thee is found -
Grace to pardon all my sin;
Let the healing streams abound,
Make and keep me pure within;
Thou of Life the Fountain art,
Freely let me take of Thee;
Spring Thou up within my heart,
Rise to all eternity.

“We would see Jesus;” for the shadows lengthen
Across the little landscape of our life;
We would see Jesus, our weak faith to strengthen
For the last conflict, in this mortal strife.

“We would see Jesus,” Rock of our salvation,
Whereon our feet were set with sovereign grace;
Not life, nor death, with all their agitation,
Can thence remove us, gazing on His face.

“We would see Jesus;” other lights are paling,
Which for long years we did rejoice to see;
The blessings of this sinful world are failing;
We would not mourn them, in exchange for Thee.

“We would see Jesus;” this is all we’re needing -
Strength, joy, and willingness come with the sight;
We would see Jesus, dying, risen, pleading,
Soon to return and end this mortal night.

’Tis the blessed hour of prayer, when our hearts lowly bend,
And we gather to Jesus, our Saviour and Friend;
If we come to Him in faith, His protection to share,
What a balm for the weary! O how sweet to be there!

’Tis the blessed hour of prayer, when the Saviour draws near,
With a tender compassion His children to hear;
When He tells us we may cast at His feet every care,
What a balm for the weary! O how sweet to be there!

’Tis the blessed hour of prayer, when the tempted and tried
To the Saviour who loves them their sorrows confide;
With a sympathizing heart He removes every care;
What a balm for the weary! O how sweet to be there!

At the blessed hour of prayer, trusting Him we believe,
That the blessings we’re needing we’ll surely receive;
In the fulness of this trust we shall lose every care;
What a balm for the weary! O how sweet to be there!

hymns.chorus:
Moment by moment I’m kept in His love;
Moment by moment I’ve life from above;
Looking to Jesus till glory doth shine;
Moment by moment, O Lord, I am Thine.

hymns.lyrics:
Anywhere with Jesus I can safely go,
Anywhere He leads me in this world below;
Anywhere without Him, dearest joys would fade;
Anywhere with Jesus I am not afraid.

Anywhere with Jesus I am not alone;
Other friends may fail me, He is still my own;
Though His hand may lead me over dreary ways,
Anywhere with Jesus is a house of praise.

Anywhere with Jesus I can go to sleep,
When the gloomy shadows round about me creep,
Knowing I shall waken nevermore to roam;
Anywhere with Jesus will be home sweet home.

Lord of our life, and God of our salvation,
Star of our night, and hope of every nation,
Hear and receive Thy church’s supplication,
Lord God Almighty.

Lord, Thou canst help when earthly armor faileth;
Lord, Thou canst save when deadly sin assaileth;
Lord o’er Thy rock nor death nor hell prevaileth;
Grant us Thy peace, Lord.

Peace in our hearts our evil thoughts assuaging;
Peace in Thy church, where brothers are engaging;
Peace, when the world its busy war is waging;
Send us, O Saviour.

Grant us Thy help till foes are backward driven;
Grant them Thy truth that they may be forgiven;
Grant peace on earth, and, after we have striven,
Peace in Thy heaven.

The Lord is my light; then why should I fear?
By day and by night His presence is near;
He is my salvation from sorrow and sin;
This blessed persuasion the Spirit brings in.

The Lord is my light; though clouds may arise,
Faith, stronger than sight, looks up to the skies
Where Jesus forever in glory doth reign:
Then how can I ever in darkness remain?

The Lord is my light, the Lord is my strength;
I know in His might I’ll conquer at length;
My weakness in mercy He covers with power,
And walking by faith, He upholds me each hour.

The Lord is my light, my all and in all;
There is in His sight no darkness at all;
He is my Redeemer, my Saviour and King;
With saints and with angels His praises I sing.

hymns.chorus:
The Lord is my light, my joy, and my song;
By day and by night He leads me along;
The Lord is my light, my joy, and my song;
By day and by night He leads me along.

hymns.lyrics:
All the way my Saviour leads me;
What have I to ask beside?
Can I doubt His tender mercy,
Who through life has been my guide?
Heavenly peace, divinest comfort,
Here by faith in Him to dwell;
For I know whate’er befall me,
Jesus doeth all things well;
For I know whate’er be fall me,
Jesus doeth all things well.

All the way my Saviour leads me;
Cheers each winding path I tread;
Gives me grace for every trial,
Feeds me with the living bread;
Though my weary steps may falter,
And my soul athirst may be,
Gushing from the Rock before me,
Lo, a spring of joy I see;
Gushing from the Rock before me,
Lo, a spring of joy I see.

All the way my Saviour leads me;
O the fullness of His love!
Perfect rest to me is promised
In my Father’s house above;
When I wake to life Immortal,
Wing my flight to realms of day,
This my song through endless ages,
Jesus led me all the way;
This my song through endless ages,
Jesus led me all the way.

hymns.chorus:
On Christ, the solid Rock, I stand;
All other ground is sinking sand,
All other ground is sinking sand.

hymns.lyrics:
O safe to the Rock that is higher than I,
My soul in its conflicts and sorrows would fly;
So sinful, so weary, Thine, Thine would I be;
Thou blest “Rock of Ages,” I’m hiding in Thee.

In the calm of the noontide, in sorrow’s lone hour,
In times when temptation casts o’er me its power;
In the tempests of life, on its wide, heaving sea,
Thou blest “Rock of Ages,” I’m hiding in Thee.

How oft in the conflict, when pressed by the foe,
I have fled to my Refuge and breathed out my woe;
How often, when trials like sea billows roll,
Have I hidden in Thee, O Thou Rock of my soul.

O for a faith that will not shrink,
Though pressed by many a foe;
That will not tremble on the brink of poverty,
Of poverty or woe;
Of poverty or woe.

That will not murmur or complain
Beneath the chastening rod,
But in the hour of grief or pain, of grief or pain
Can lean upon its God;
Can lean upon its God.

A faith that shines more bright and clear
When tempests rage without;
That when in danger knows no fear, knows of no fear,
In darkness feels no doubt;
in darkness feels no doubt.

That bears unmoved the world’s dread frown,
Nor heeds its scornful smile;
That sin’s wild ocean cannot drown, no, cannot drown
Nor its soft arts beguile;
Nor Its soft arts beguile.

Lord, give me such a faith as this,
And then, whate’er may come
I’ll taste e’en here the hallowed bliss, the hallowed bliss,
Of an eternal home;
Of an eternal home.

I am trusting Thee, Lord Jesus,
Trusting only Thee;
Trusting Thee for full salvation,
Great and free.

I am trusting Thee for pardon;
At Thy feet I bow;
For Thy grace and tender mercy,
Trusting now.

I am trusting Thee to guide me;
Thou alone shalt lead,
Every day and hour supplying
All my need.

I am trusting Thee, Lord Jesus;
Never let me fall;
I am trusting Thee forever,
And for all.

Guide me, O Thou great Jehovah,
Pilgrim through this barren land;
I am weak, but Thou art mighty;
Hold me with Thy powerful hand;
Bread of heaven, Bread of heaven,
Feed me till I want no more,
Feed me till I want no more.

Open now the crystal fountain,
Whence the healing stream doth flow;
Let the fire and cloudy pillar
Lead me all my journey through;
Strong deliverer, strong deliverer.
Be Thou still my strength and shield,
Be Thou still my strength and shield.

When I tread the verge of Jordan,
Bid my anxious fears subside;
Death of death and hell’s destruction,
Land me safe on Canaan’s side;
Songs of praises, songs of praises
I will ever give to Thee,
I will ever give to Thee.

Gentle Jesus, meek and mild,
Look upon a little child;
Pity my simplicity,
Suffer me to come to Thee.

Lamb of God, I look to Thee,
Thou shalt my example be;
Thou art gentle, meek, and mild,
Thou wast once a little child.

Fain I would be as Thou art;
Give me Thy obedient heart;
Thou art pitiful and kind,
Let me have Thy loving mind.

I shall then show forth Thy praise,
Serve Thee all my happy days;
Then the world shall always see
Christ, the Holy Child, in me.

Come, ye thankful people, come,
Raise the song of harvest home!
All is safely gathered in,
Ere the winter storms begin;
God, our Maker, doth provide
For our wants to be supplied;
Come to God’s own temple, come;
Raise the song of harvest home!

We ourselves are God’s own field,
Fruit unto His praise to yield;
Wheat and tares together sown,
Unto joy or sorrow grown;
First the blade and then the ear,
Then the full corn shall appear;
Grant, O harvest Lord, that we
Wholesome grain and pure may be.

For the Lord our God shall come,
And shall take His harvest home;
From His field shall purge away
All that doth offend, that day;
Give His angels charge at last
In the fire the tares to cast,
But the fruitful ears to store
In His garner evermore.

Then, thou church triumphant, come,
Raise the song of harvest home;
All are safely gathered in,
Free from sorrow, free from sin;
There forever purified
In God’s garner to abide;
Come, ten thousand angels, come,
Raise the glorious harvest home!

Father, we thank You
For the light that shines all the day;
For the bright sky You have given
Most like Your heaven;
Father, we thank You.

Father, we thank You
For the lamps that lighten the way;
For human skill’s exploration
Of Your creation;
Father, we thank You.

Father, we thank You
For the friends who brighten our play;
For Your command to call others
Sisters and brothers;
Father, we thank You.

Father, we thank You
For Your love in Jesus today,
Giving us hope for tomorrow
Through joy and sorrow;
Father, we thank You.

Not I, but Christ, be honoured, loved, exalted;
Not I, but Christ, be seen, be known, be heard;
Not I, but Christ, in every look and action,
Not I, but Christ, in every thought and word.

Not I, but Christ, to gently soothe in sorrow,
Not I, but Christ, to wipe the falling tear;
Not I, but Christ, to lift the weary burden;
Not I, but Christ, to hush away all fear.

Christ, only Christ! no idle words e’er falling,
Christ, only Christ; no needless bustling sound;
Christ, only Christ; no self important bearing;
Christ, only Christ; no trace of “I” be found.

Not I, but Christ, my every need supplying,
Not I, but Christ, my strength and health to be;
Christ, only Christ, for body, soul, and spirit,
Christ, only Christ, here and eternally.

Heir of the kingdom, O why dost thou slumber?
Why art thou sleeping so near thy blest home?
Wake thee, arouse thee, and gird on thine armor,
Speed, for the moments are hurrying on.

Heir of the kingdom, say, why dost thou linger?
How canst thou tarry in sight of the prize?
Up, and adorn thee, the Saviour is coming;
Haste to receive Him descending the skies.

Earth’s mighty nations, in strife and commotion,
Tremble with terror, and sink in dismay;
Listen, ’tis nought but the chariot’s loud rumbling;
Heir of the kingdom, no longer delay.

Stay not, O stay not for earth’s vain allurements!
See how its glory is passing away;
Break the strong fetters the foe hath bound o’er thee;
Heir of the kingdom, turn, turn thee away.

Keep the eye single, the head upward lifted;
Watch for the glory of earth’s coming King;
Lo! o’er the mountaintops light is now breaking;
Heirs of the kingdom, rejoice ye and sing.

Watch, ye saints, with eyelids waking;
Lo! the powers of heaven are shaking;
Keep your lamps all trimmed and burning,
Ready for your Lord’s returning.

Lo! the promise of your Saviour,
Pardoned sin and purchased favor,
Blood-washed robes and crowns of glory;
Haste to tell redemption’s story.

Kingdoms at their base are crumbling,
Hark! His chariot wheels are rumbling;
Tell, O tell of grace abounding,
While the seventh trump is sounding.

Nations wane, though proud and stately;
Christ His kingdom hasteneth greatly;
Earth her latest pangs is summing;
Shout, ye saints, your Lord is coming.

Sinners, come, while Christ is pleading;
Now for you He’s interceding;
Haste, ere grace and time diminished
Shall proclaim the mystery finished.

Sweet promise is given to all who believe-
“Behold I come quickly, Mine own to receive;
Hold fast till I come; the danger is great;
Sleep not as do others;  be watchful, and wait.”

We’ll “watch unto prayer” with lamps burning bright;
He comes to all others a “thief in the night.”
We know He is near, but know not the day-
As spring shows that summer is not far away.

Yes! this is our hope, ’tis built on His word-
The glorious appearing of Jesus, our Lord;
Of promises all, it stands as the sum:
“Behold I come quickly, hold fast till I come.”

Christian, seek not yet repose,
Cast thy dreams of ease away;
Thou art in the midst of foes;
Watch and pray!

Gird thy heavenly armor on,
Wear it ever, night and day;
Ambushed lies the evil one;
Watch and pray!

Hear the victors who o’er came;
Still they mark each warrior’s way;
All with one sweet voice exclaim:
“Watch and pray!”

Hear, above all, hear thy Lord,
Him thou lovest to obey;
Hide within thy heart His word:
“Watch and pray!”

Watch, as if on that alone
Hung the issue of the day;
Pray that help may be sent down;
Watch and pray!

We know not the hour of the Master’s appearing;
Yet signs all foretell that the moment is nearing
When He shall return- ’tis a promise most cheering-
But we know not the hour.

There’s light for the wise who are seeking salvation;
There’s truth in the book of the Lord’s revelation;
Each prophecy points to the great consummation-
But we know not the hour.

We’ll watch and we’ll pray, with our lamps trimmed and burning;
We’ll work and we’ll wait till the Master’s returning;
We’ll sing and rejoice, every omen discerning-
But we know not the hour.

O Christian, awake! ’tis the Master’s command;
With helmet and shield, and a sword in thy hand,
To meet the bold tempter, go, fearlessly go,
Then stand like the brave, with thy face to the foe.

The cause of thy Master with vigor defend;
Be watchful, be zealous, and fight to the end;
Wherever He Leads thee, go, valiantly go,
Then stand like the brave, with thy face to the foe.

Press on, never doubting, thy Captain is near,
With grace to supply, and with comfort to cheer;
His love, like a stream in the desert will flow;
Then stand like the brave,  with thy face to the foe.

Fight the good fight with all thy might,
Christ is thy strength and Christ thy right;
Lay hold on life and it shall be
Thy joy and crown eternally.

Run the straight race through God’s good grace;
Lift up Thine eyes, and seek His face.
Life with its path before us lies;
Christ is the way, and Christ the prize.

Cast care aside, lean on thy guide;
His boundless mercy will provide;
Trust, and the trusting soul shall prove
Christ is its life, and Christ its love.

Faint not, nor fear, His arms are near;
He changeth not and thou art dear.
Only believe, and thou shalt see
That Christ is all in all to thee.

Lead on, O King eternal,
The day of march has come;
Henceforth in fields of conquest
Thy tents shall be our home;
Through days of preparation
Thy grace has made us strong;
And now, O King eternal,
We lift our battle song.

Lead on, O King eternal,
Till sin’s fierce war shall cease,
And holiness shall whisper
The sweet Amen of peace;
For not with swords, loud clashing,
Nor roll of stirring drums,
With deeds of love and mercy,
The heavenly kingdom comes.

Lead on, O King eternal,
We follow, not with fears,
For gladness breaks like morning
Where’er Thy face appears;
Thy cross is lifted o’er us;
We journey in its light;
The crown awaits the conquest;
Lead on, O God of might.

hymns.chorus:
Lord, lift me up, and I shall stand
By faith, on heaven’s tableland;
A higher plane than I have found;
Lord, plant my feet on higher ground.

hymns.lyrics:
Rise, my soul, and stretch thy wings,
Thy better portion trace;
Rise from transitory things
Toward heaven, thy native place:
Sun, and moon, and stars decay;
Time shall soon this earth remove;
Rise, my soul, and haste away
To seats prepared above.

Rivers to the ocean run,
Nor stay in all their course;
Fire ascending seeks the sun;
Both speed them to their source;
So a soul that’s born of God,
Longs to view His glorious face,
Forward tends to His abode
To rest in His embrace.

Cease, ye pilgrims, cease to mourn;
Press onward to the prize;
Soon our Saviour will return,
Triumphant in the skies;
Yet a season, and you know
Happy entrance will be given,
All our sorrows left below,
And earth exchanged for heaven.

Lord of all good, our gifts we bring You now;
Use them Your holy purpose to fulfill.
Tokens of love and pledges they shall be
That our whole life is offered to your will.

We give our minds to understand Your ways;
Hands, voices, eyes to serve Your great design;
Hearts with the flame of Your own love ablaze:
Thus for Your glory all our power’s combine.

Father, whose bounty all creation shows;
Christ, by whose willing sacrifice we live;
Spirit, from whom all life in fullness flows;
To You with grateful hearts ourselves we give.

Mine eyes have seen the glory of the coming of the Lord;
He is trampling out the vintage where the grapes of wrath are stored;
He has loosed the fateful lightning of His terrible swift sword;
His truth is marching on.

He has sounded forth the trumpet that shall never call retreat;
He is sifting out the hearts  of men before His judgement seat;
O be swift, my soul, to answer Him; be jubilant, my feet!
Our God is marching on.

In the beauty of the lilies Christ was born across the sea,
With a glory in His bosom that transfigures you and me;
He died to make men holy, let us live to make men free!
While God is marching on.

I vow to thee, my country, all earthly things 	above,
Entire and whole and perfect, the service of my love:
The love that asks the reason, the love that stands the test,
That lays upon the altar the dearest and the best;
The love that never falters, the love that pays the price,
The love that makes undaunted the final sacrifice.

And there’s another country, I’ve heard of long ago,
Most dear to them that love her, most great to them that know;
We may not count her armies, we may not see her King;
Her fortress is a faithful heart, her pride is suffering;
And one by one and fervently we pray for her 	increase,
And her ways are ways of gentleness and all her paths are peace.

hymns.chorus:
Love at home, love at home;
Time doth softly, sweetly glide,
When there’s love at home.

hymns.lyrics:
All things come of Thee, O Lord;
And of Thine own have we given Thee.
Amen.

Cast thy burden upon the Lord,
And He shall sustain thee;
He never will suffer the righteous to fall;
He is at thy right hand.
Thy mercy, Lord, is great, and far above the heavens;
Let none be made ashamed, that wait upon Thee.

God be in my head, and in my understanding;
God be in mine eyes, and in my looking;
God be in my mouth, and in my speaking;
God be in my heart, and in my thinking;
God be at mine end, and at my departing.

Holy Spirit, hear us;
Help us while we sing;
Breathe into the music
Of the praise we bring.

Holy Spirit, prompt us
When we kneel to pray;
Nearer come, and teach us
What we ought to say.

Holy Spirit, shine Thou
On the Book we read;
Gild its holy pages
With the light we need.

Bless Thou the gifts our hands have brought;
Bless Thou the work our hearts have planned;
Ours is the faith, the will, the thought;
The rest, O God, is in Thy hand.
Amen.

Dismiss us, Lord, with blessing, we pray;
As from Thy worship we go our ways;
Guide in life’s conflicts, all through the day;
Save in Thy kingdom, Thine be the praise.
Amen.

Praise God, from whom all blessings flow;
Praise Him, all creatures here below;
Praise Him above, ye heavenly host;
Praise Father, Son, and Holy Ghost.

Praise God, from whom all blessings flow;
Praise Him, all creatures here below;
Praise Him above, ye heavenly host;
Praise Father, Son, and Holy Ghost.

Ridza tsuri yevangeri, Murindi wanyewera;
Avo vanonzwa masoko, Vapinduke, vapone.

Ridza pamakomo ese Mapomo nemikana;
Nepanyanza ridzanyizve, Soko rekuponeswa.

Ridzanyizve pamagwanza, Nenzvimbo dzine dima;
Taura zvakagadzirwa, Baba atidayidza.

Ridza kune vakaneta, Vanoda kuponeswa;
Muponesi wadayidza, Mwese munodikanwa.

Mambo aripo pam’suwo, Iye wafa pamchinjiko;
Asi unowuya zvino Kutora vake’vo.

Zviwoneso zvekuuya, Zvino zviri kuitika;
Toona nekukasika Musi wakanaka.

Musanangise pasi’po, Kuti kusine dambudzo;
Dakara Muponesi’wo Auye pasi’po.

Ndizvo mupasi’po itsva, Tichagara nekugara;
Kufa kuchawa kusafa, Haiperi nguva.

Tichazoonana usu, NaTenzi toonana;
Ndinodisa kumuona Jesu wakandifira.

Nhasi handisi kum’ona, Basi nge kudawira;
Asi musi unouya, Jesu uchazoonwa.

Tichafara pamwe naye, Urombo hwazopera;
Ne nzira dzaruramiswa, Zvedima zvacheniswa.

Toonana ngerufaro, Kuona nekuziwa;
Iye Mununuri wangu, Jesu unondidisa.

Soko rakanaka kunesu vafambi, Apo tinoyenda pasi’po;
Asi Muponesi achazouyazve, Kutonga umambo hwake’wo.

Makuva ekare apo vanorara, Vafambi vakafa naKristu;
Vachazarurwazve, vanhu vanomuka, Vachapona pamwe na Jesu.

Tichasangana kumusha’wo kudenga, Tichaimba ngekuponeswa;
Vaponeswi’wo vachabva pasi rese, Vanamate Mambo wedenga.

Hariruya, Amen, nezve Hariruya, Ngekudawira, tichasvika;
Namata, simbira, kufara, dakara, Topfeka mbiri yekudenga.

Ridzanyi Tsuri neizwi guru;
Jesu unouya zve!
Farai vafambi, tendai, imbanyi;
Jesu unouya zve!

Ungiranyizve makomo imwi;
Jesu unouya zve!
Nyenye yakafa ive nembiri;
Jesu unouya zve!

Nyanza taura nemananda’yo;
Jesu unouya zve!
Apo pajecha kunyika dzese;
Jesu unouya zve!

Pasi rinoti nekuteneka;
Jesu unouya zve!
Champupuri’cho nekuvhuvhuta;
Jesu unouya zve!

Ndudzi dzepasi dzinoshatirwa;
Jesu unouya zve!
Ngwaru hwawanda, vanhu vafamba;
Jesu unouya zve!

Inzwai mapeni’wo, Arikuiswa
Ese ndeaJesu, Unogashira

Arikuiswa’mo, Kubva m’tuwoko;
Tinounza chipo Kuna Jesu’wo

Tirivo vaduku, Tine mapeni;
Zvetava vakuru, Tokupa zhinji

Kana tisina’ba, Tomupa rudo;
Zveunozoruda, Afare narwo

Ndiudze nyaya yaJesu, Uyi nyore mumwoyo;
Udza nyaya inokosha, Yakanakisa kwazvo.
Kuti ngirosi dzaka i-mbira Tenzi  abarwa,
Mbiri kudenga kum’soro Runyararo mupasi.

Kutsanya kwake mugwenya Ndiudze misi yake,
Achititambu dzikira Akakunda chitema,
Ndiudze nebasa rake Nekutambudzwa kwake;
Akashorwa nekurwadzwa Akarambwa nevese.

Nekurowera kwavo, Nekurwadziwa kwake;
Neguva vakamuwiga Nezvekumuka kwake;
Nyaya yerudo rwaJesu Iwe pachena kwazvo;
Ndiudze ini ndicheme Rudo rwakanditenga.

Ndinoona nanda dzvuku Tsime rakadzama,
Jesu Tenzi Muponesi Wakatifirayo.

Nda wona upenyu hutswa Ndanzwa ropa Rake;
Zwitema zwese zwapera Apo patsimero.

Ndamuka ndaitwa mutswa Nembiri yedenga;
Ne mwoyo nenguwo chenaa Na Kristu mandiri

Chishamiso tsitsi dzake, Ropa Rake pasi;
Muziwenyi Jesu chete wakati nunura.

Kwete ini Asi kudzai Kristu;
Asi Kristu Azihwe akudzwe:
Kristu chete mubasa redu rese;
Kristu basi mukufunga kwese.

Kwete ini Anonyaradza,
NdiKri-stu A-nobvisa masodzi;
NdiKri-stu A-nosimudza mutoro;
Ndiye Kristu Anodzinga kutya;

Kristu basi ha’tauri zwenhando;
Kristu basi Asina nyongano:
Kristu basi Asingazwi kudzi ba;
Kristu basi Ini ndisa onwe.

Handi-ni-ndi Kristu A ndipa zwese;
Handini ndi-Kristu \‘andipa simba;
Kristu chete Asimbisa muwiri,
Kristu chete, Dakara narini.

Kune kupenya mugomo, nekupenya munyanza,
Nemaranzi anogara Munzwimbo dzakanaka,
Mukati memwoyo wangu mazadzwa nekujeka,
Apo pana Muponesi pano jekesa kwese.

Ndosiya kusuwa kwangu Senguwadzo dzekare;
Ndifukidze nekutenda mundipenyikutenda.
Kumusha wembiri uyo makandigadzirira;
Mwoyo wangu unotenda ne mweya unobvuma.

Muponesi manditenga ndawawenyu narini;
Ngayipfute mwenje yese ipfutire iye Tenzi.
Kumusha wembiri uyo makandigadzirira;
Mwoyo wangu uno tenda nemweya unobvuma.

Mwari avona kashiri kaputsika pasi;
Kuti achida kashiri Anodazve ini.

Anogadzira maruva akanaka kwazvo;
Kuti anoda maruva anodazve ini.

Mwari wakasika zvese, shiri ne maruva,
Haachakanganwi tupwere, Twese anotuda.

Pam’chinjiko Akatifira, Akatichenura zvitema,
Ropa rake rikawerera, Mbiri kuna’ye

Ruponeso runoshamisa, Jesu ari kugara neni;
Pam’chinjiko akanditora, Mbiri kuna’ye.

Tsime rinobvisa zvitema, Ndinofara ndawa mariri;
Umo Jesu andichenura, Mbiri kuna’ye.

Uya kutsime rakanaka, Zviunze kuna Muponesi;
Pindamo nhasi uperere Mbiri kuna’ye

MuKristu muka! Tenzi akutuma;
Nenhowo nemu-nondo mumaoko,
Enda, sangana nemuedzi shinga,
Mira segamba, utarise mhandu.

Kana mungozi, chenjera ngwarira,
Usadzokere, Hakuna chishangu;
Wakani wedima, Ungawakunde,
Mira segamba, utarise mhandu.

Basa raTenzi dziwira nesimba;
Rinda udise, urwe kumagumo;
Kwa anokutuma, enda kasika,
Mira segamba utarise mhandu.

Enda usatye, tenzi ari petyo,
Anopa tsitsi, nekukunyaradza;
Rudo rwake sekarwizi mugwenga;
Mira segamba, utarise mhandu.

Muponesi mambo wangu, wandifira ini;
Akafira munhu, akaita seni here?

Pam’sana pangu, Akaturikwa pamuti here?
Tsitsi, ngoni nerudo, Zvinoshamisa kwazvo!

Urombo hahukwanisi, K’ripa mhosva yangu;
Tenzi ndizvipira, Ndizvo-chete ndingaite!

Tese taita sehwayi dzapumhuka kure;
Ndingaona senyi nzira yekuva mudanga?

Ndatenderedzwa nenhamo Mwari anondinzwa;
Apo wazhinji wochema, Ndoziva senyi idi?

Kuna Kristu nzira nedi, Handicha pumhuki;
Ondi isa kuna Baba; Kumusha wembiri

Simukanyi mese, Murikudze zita ra Jehova
Taurayi nebasa rerudo rwake,
Netsitsi dzake ihuru kwazvo

Reganyi hwamanda imukudze, Nebopoto guru;
Reganyi marinda ese amukudze;
Manzwi azare nezita rake

Apo muchim’kudza, Ridzisanyi zvese zvinakidze;
Anopa upenyu, mweya imupe mbiri;
Yake huru, m’kudzenyi Tenzi

Nyenyedzi yakabud’ usiku,  Yakapenya nembiri huru
Yakatungamira vazivi ,  Kuna M’ponesi kudanga

Vakaziviswa nenzvi redi, M’nguva yeiyi nyeredzi;
Vakateera nyenyedziyo, Yayipenya iri Kristu

Tinoiteera sevakare, Mwenje wenyika wataurwa;
Tinoteera mwenje wayo, Dakara tisvike kudenga

Yakafanira nyenye,  Yakafanira nyenye;
Yakafanira nyenye, Yabaiwa

Tenzi unza umambo! Huzopedza chitema;
Unzai makore churu, Moyera.

Nguva dzese tinonzwa, Tim’de Timusandire
Tinosvika Zioni, Tim’one

hymns.chorus:
Zvakaroverwa’po, Pam’chinjiko wake
O zvizhinji sey’ atakura!, Nekurwadzwa kose;
Jesu atakura, zvese zvitema zvangu

hymns.lyrics:
Letsa phala ea evangeli, bohle ba khalemeloe;
Bohle ba utloang molaetsa, ba inyatse ba phele.

E utloahale phahameng, le hona bakeng tsohle;
Leoatle le ke le pake, poloko ee thabisang

E letse le teng litseleng, moo o leng balahlehi;
Ntho tsohe li lokisitsoe, Ntate O ba emetse.

Letsetsa ba leng bothateng, ba batlang tokoloho;
Utloang memo ea ’Moloki, ee e reng le tleng ho ’na.

Morena O teng monyako, Ea neng ’jere sefapano,
Joale bao ba lokileng, Ba bokelloa bohle.

Liponts’o ka lemo tsohle, Li re O se A le mona;
Re tla bona haufinyane, Ea teng mehleng eohle.

Hlokomelang tsa lefats’eng, Mats’oenyeho ha a fele;
Mopholosi O tla fihla, Mothetsi a fele.

Mane lefats’eng le lecha, Re tla lula re le bacha;
Ba neng ba shoa ha ba sa shoa, Le ka ho sa feleng.

Fahleho li tla bonana, le Kreste Mopholosi;
Ke tla thaba ha ke ’mona Jesu Mothusi oa ka.

Ke tla ’mona ho ler’otho, O sa ntsea nts’iretse;
Tsatsi le letle le ea tla, ke tla ’mona ka lona.

Ke tla thabela ho ’mona, ho lla ho tla feela;
Hohle ho hong ho sa tsejoeng, ho tla bonesoa hohle.

Faheho li tla bonana, le Mopholosi oa ka,
Re tla bonana le Eena, Jesu ’Moloki oa ka.

Monate ha litaba li tlela moeti, leha a le hole le lehae;
Kapeele-peele ’Moloki O tla hlaha, ’Me kapele ’muso’ tla ba

Mabitla a baeti batho ba khale, a tla buloa joaleka pele;
Bongata bo robetseng le leoatleng, bo tla phela hape lefats’eng.

Re tla kopana lehaeeng la Edene, Re bine lipina tsa thabo,
Ho tsoa Leboea, Boroa, balopolloa ba tla khumamela Morena.

Alleluya amen, Alleluya hape, kapele re tla ba teng bohle;
Lebelang ka ts’epo le nyakalleng ke hona, re roale moqhaka oa khanya.

Lebelang bahalaleli, bona matla ’leholimo;
Mabone a ’ne a tuke, itukiseng Jesu Oa tla.

Bona ts’episo ’a ’Moloki, beng tseo re li ts’oaretsoeng;
Liaparo le meqhaka, phetang le tokoloho e re:

Mebuso e ea felisoa, utloang makoloi a luma;
Phetang mohau o moholo, ’Kolulo la bosupa lea lla:

Lichaba li ea timela, ho tla borena ba Kreste;
Lefats’e le ea qetellong, hoeletsang jesu O a tla.

Baetsalibe tlong le ea bitsoa, Jesu O a le buella;
Phakisang mohau oa koaloa, ho tla thoe jo ho felile.

Mohlang A tlang, Mohlang A tlang ho etsa mahakoe;
E leng a Hae a bohlokoa, baratuoa ba Hae

O tla phutha, O tla phutha, mahakoe a Hae;
Ba hloekileng le ba khanyang, baratuoa ba Hae.

Le bana ba banyenyane, ba ratang Jesu;
Ke mahakoe a bohlokoa, baratuoa ba Hae.

Letsang ’kolulo le lle haholo, Jesu O oa tla hape;
Nyakallang bohle, thabang le bineng, Jesu O oa tla hape.

Hoeletsang lihlorong le lithabeng, Jesu O oa tla hape;
Konyana’e hlabiloeng, e ea khanya, Jesu O oa tla hape.

Maqhubu leoatleng, lumang haholo, Jesu O oa tla hape;
Lehlabathe le qhaloe lebopong, Jesu O oa tla hape.

Ntoa lia bonts’a ka ho loana, Jesu O oa tla hape
Le ponts’o li atile ruri, Jesu O oa tla hape.

Chaba li halefile haholo, Jesu O oa tla hape
Le tsebo e atile haholo, Jesu O oa tla hape.

Na re tla phutheha nokeng, khatong tsa mangeloi;
Nokaneng tse halalelang tse mathang teroneng

Hona teng bopong la noka, moo metsi a leng matle;
Ke tla khumama kamehla, linakong tsa nyakallo.

Ha re eso fihle nokeng, re tla rola meroalo;
Re tla bona hlohonolo, le seaparo le moqhaka.

Kapele re fihla nokeng, leeto le tla fela;
Pelo li tla tlala thabo, le lipineng tsa khotso.

Ke tla latela ’Moloki, Hohle moo A nkisang teng’
Moo A eang ke tla ea teng, E Morena ke tla ea

Leha ke le khathatsehong, Ke lekoa habohloko;
Ke hopola le ka Uena, ’Me ke tla ke thabile.

Ha ke leba nqa Jordane, Serameng le botebong;
U ts’etse pele ho ’na, ’Me ke tla ho latela.

Ha u ka ntlohella botubong, Ke le mo bofutsaneng;
U ne u se na lehae, ’Me ke ea ho latela.

Morena ke batla ho ba ea phethehang;
Morena ’na ke batla ho phetheha;
Ke batla U be ho ’na mehleng eohle,
U thuhe melimo, U lihe sera;

Morena Jesu, bona U le troneng;
U nthuse ke etse le ka boitelo,
Kea inehela, le hoo ke ho tsebang;
Ntlhatsoe ke soeufale joaloka lehloa.

Jesu, ke bopa ka boikokobetso;
Ke le maotong a neng a thakhisoe,
Tumelo e mponts’a mali a ntlhatsoang;
Ntlhatsoe ke soeufale joaloka lehloa.

Morena, ke lebetse ka mamello;
Tlo U bope pelo e ncha ka ho ’na;
Ha u ka ke ua hanela ba u batlang
Ntlhatsoe ke soeufale joaloka lehloa.

Jesu oa nthata e ’na, ho rialo mangolo,
Ba ba’nyane ke ba Hae, ba fokola, O matla.

Jesu oa nthata O nchoetse, khoro e butsoe holimo;
’Me O tla ntlhatsoa libe, ke lumelloe ho kena.

Jesu oa nthata, haholo, le ha ke le masoabing;
O tsoa troneng holimo, ho mpona mo ke leng teng.

E Jesu O oa nthata, O tla tsamaea le ’na;
Le ’na ha ke Mo rata, O tla nkisa holimo.

Ke hlapile liatla, Hantle hoseng hona;
’Me ka li nea Jesu, Ho mo sebeletsa

Ke joetsitse tsebe, Tsa ka ho mo mamela;
Ketsong e bonolo, Ea liatlanyana.

Mahlo a ka a bona, Ketsong le papaling;
A thibeloe le kotsing, Ka thato ea Jesu.

Re thabisoa ke rato, Tsela e bonolo;
Le re thusa le khopolong, Ho ba mosa bathong.

Fats’e le tletse lefu, Le eona ts’enyeho;
Re tla leka ka lerato, Ho sokolla ba bang.

Bophelo ha bo se teng, Re bitsoa holimo;
Pina ea rona e tla ba, Ea ka hosafeleng

Itise moea oa ka! Lira li atile;
Makhotla ’sebe a teng, Hore a tle a ho lihe.

Hlabana u rapele! Se inehele ntoeng;
Hlabana nako tsohle,’Me u be u kope thuso.

Ha u eso ho hlole, ’Se ke ua tepella;
Mosebetsi o tla feela, U be u thole moqhaka

Ke ea tla sefapanong, Bofumeng le bofofung;
Tsohle ke ea li lahla, Ke tla bona poloko.

Pelo ea u llela, sebe se ntse se mpusa;
Jesu O bua ho ’na O re: “Ke tla u hlatsoa.”

Ke U fa tsohle tsa ka, Metsoalle le maruo;
Moea ’mele ke tsa Hao, Tsohle ka ho sa feleng.

Ke ts’epa lits’episo, Joale ke utloa mali;
Ke namaletse fats’e, Ke Mapotsoe le Jesu.

Jesu O ntlatsa moeeng, ’me ke ea phethehileng;
Hohle ke phethehileng; Ho tumisoe Konyana.

Moea o halalelang, hlatsoa pelo e ts’ohileng;
Ntlatse ka boteng ba Hao, tlo U ntlatse hona joale.

Moea O bonolo O ka ntlatsa, ha ke tsebe joang;
Me ke ea U hloka haholo, tlo U ntlatse joale.

Ke tletse bofokoli, maotong a halalelang;
Moea O lehlohonolo, ntlatse ka rato la Hao.

Ntlhatsoe, nts’elise, mpholose; U hlatsoe pelo ea ka;
U ’a ts’elisa oa pholosa, U ntse U ntlatsa joale.

Ha ke na see ke se qosang, Mali a Hao a ts’olotsoe;
’Me U mpitsetsa ho uena,Konyana’ Molimo Ke ea tla.

Joale ke ntse ke emetse, Ho nts’a sebe moeeng oa ka;
Uena Ea hlatsoang ka mali, Konyana ’Molimo ke ea tla.

Ha ke ntse ke akheha le lintoeng le hona ngongorehong;
Ts’abo kahare le kantle, Konyana ’Molimo ke ea tla.

Ha ke le bofumanehing, Pono leruo pholiso;
E, tsohle ke ea li hloka, Konyana ’Molimo ke ea tla

Joaleka ha ke le tjena, nkuke, nts’oarele U ntlhatsoe;
Hoba U ts’episitse, Konyana ea Molimo ke ea tla.

Ha ke le tje, ’rato la Hao. Le thuhile lintho tsohle;
Ke tla ba oa Hao fela, Konyana’ Molimo ke ea tla.

Tsatsi le ea likela, Mantsiboea a fihla;
Tlong rapelang Morena, Ha naleli li hlaha
Leholimong.

Morena oa bophelo, Le oa lefats’e lohle.
Re phuthe bana ba hao, Leratong le leholo; Eba haufi.

Letsatsi le liketse; Joale re u emetse;
Hore U re fe khotso, Ea Hao ee sa sirelang;
U re thuse.

Ha bosiu bo feta, Ho feta mahlomola;
Leholimong U re fe, Hore re tle re bone;
Uena Jesu.

hymns.chorus:
Oa halalela, Morena ka;
Lefats’e leholimo, Li ea u rorisa ka;
Mehla eohle.

hymns.lyrics:
Tsatsi la moea oa ka ’Moloki, Ha ho bosiu ha u le teng;
Ho se ke hoa ba teng maru, Ho U pata mahlong a ka.

Ha ke tleloa ke boroko, Mahlo a ka a otsela;
Mohopolo oa ka fubeng, Sa ’Moloki O tla phomola.

Lula le ’na mantsiboeng, Ha ke le mong nke ke ka phela;
Lula le ’na ka bosiu, Hoba ha ke batle ho shoa.

Ntlhohonolofatse mesong, Ke tsamaee mo lefats’eng;
Leratong la Hao ke be ke, Kene hona teng leholimong.

Ke talimme Uena, Konyana ’Golgotha;
’Moloki, Utloa kea rapela,
U ntlose melatong; Ho tloha kajeno,
Ke be oa Hao.

Eka mohau oa hao, O ka ’matlafatsa;
Ke U rate, Joalokaha ’nchoetse,
A lerato la ka, Le se ke la fetoha,
Le phele.

Tseleng ea lefifi, Le bofumanehing;
U ntsamaise, U tlose lefifi;
Hlakola meokho, U se nteselle,
Ka u tlohela.

Molim’o be le lona bohle;
O ts’ehetse le eletsoe,
Mohlapeng O le boloke;
Re be le hona ho kopana.

Molim’o be le lona bohle;
Tlas’a mapheo le patoe
Le fepjoe manna kamehla,
Re be le hona ho kopana.

Molim’o be le lona bohle;
Tsietsing O le phemele,
O le bee liatleng tsa Hae,
Re be le hona ho kopana.

Molim’o be le lona bohle;
Leratong le phahamisoe,
’Me o le qobele lefu;
Re be le hona ho kopana.

hymns.chorus:
Re tla kopanang...re kopaneng,
Re kopaneng maotong a Jesu;
Re tla kopanang...re kopaneng,

hymns.lyrics:
Ha mosebetsi oa ka o s’o felile mona,
’Mele ona o tla apara ho sa shoeng;
Ke tla tseba Molopolli oa ka ka nqane,
O tla nkamohela a bososela.

Thabo e tla ba kholo ha ke ’mona ’fahleho;
Ha leihlo la mosa le nchebile,
Pelo ea ka e tla ’moka ka mosa lerato,
Holimo ke lokiselitsoe tulo.

Ke hopola barat’oa ba se ba shoele khale;
Ke hopola tumeliso le nokeng,
Ha re ka ke ra arohana hona Edene;
Takatso ke ho bona le ’Moloki.

Ke tla tsoa khorong tsa motse, ke apere tse ts’oeu;
O tla nkenya teng, moo ho seng meokho;
Ke tla ’ne ke bine pina ea balopolloa,
Ke lakatsa ho bona ’Moloki teng.

hymns.chorus:
Mphe Bibele molaetsa o ts’epehang,
Leseli la Hao le tla ntsamaisa;
Molao, ts’episo lerato hammoho,

hymns.lyrics:
Nokeng ea Jordan ke eme, ke lahlela leihlo;
Kana e ntle ea thabo, moo letlotlo le leng teng.

Lithoteng tse hole-hole, moo ho leng ho benya;
Jesu letsatsi Oa busa, O leleka bosiu.

Ke tla finyella neng botleng, ke hlohonolofatsoe;
Ke tla bona neng Ntate teng, ke lule ’musong oa Hae.

Thabo e tletse ka pelong, ha nka ke ka lula;
Maqhubung a Jordane ke ts’ela ke sa ts’abe.

Mohloli oa ’hlohonolo,Tlo U nthute ho bina
Melatsoana ea mohau e lokela thoriso;
U nthute ho U khabisa, Ke bonts’e molemo ’hao.
Ha ts’epo ea khalalelo eona ne mpha fela.

Ke bea kelello ea ka, Ka thuso ea Hao mona;
Ke na le ts’epo ho fihla hae ka boitumelo,
Jesu ’mptlile ke lahlehile, Ke tsoile mo mohlapeng;
Ho mpoloka le likotsing, A ts’olla mali A Hae.

Hlohonolong ke na le molato ka mehla eohle,
’Me U ntlame ka marapo, Ke be haufi le Uena;
Morena ha ke lahleha, Ke tloha ho Molimo;
U nke pelo ena ea ka, U e tlise ho Uena.

Moea O Halalelang, eba haufi le mokreste,
Re hule ka seatla, re baeti mo lefeelleng;
Ba khathetseng ba nyakalla, Ha ba utloa lentsoe lee;
Le sebang, “tlo molahlehi, Ntatele ke tla u isa hae.”

U motsoalle ea ts’epehang, U haufi ho re thusa.
U se ke ua re sia, ts’abong le hona lefifing;
Ha ho le litsietsi, lipelo li tepella,
U sebe, “Tlo molahlehi, Ntatele ke tla u isa hae.”

Ha mosebetsi O fetile, ke emetse ho lokolloa;
Re maketse re sa tsebe! Ha mabitso a ngoliloe,
Re ts’ela moroallong, Ho kopa mali a Jesu,
U sebe “Tlo molahlehi, Ntatele ke tla u hula.

Ntho eo ke e kopang tseleng ea ka e liretse;
Le meleko e chesang, ntlhatsoisise, ntlhatsoisise.

Ha u mpha pono e khanyang, kea thaba moeeng oa ka;
’Me haholo pelo e ncha ho hotle-hotle ho ’na.

E, ha pelo e hoekile ke tla ateloa ke pono
Bophelong ba hau ho bonoa ho hloekileng, ho hloekileng.

Ke hana tsel’e liretse le khopolo e lits’ila;
Leha ke leka ke loana ha kea hloeka, ha kea hloeka.

Jesu thabo ea pelo, Uena noka ea bophelo;
Boitumelong ba lefats’e, Re khutlela ho uena hape.

Uena bohobe bo phelang, Re lakatsa ho ja uena,
Re noe ho Uena mohloli; U tlatse meea ’rona.

Re u lakatsa moeeng, Hohle moo re lahleloang teng;
Ho thabo h’a bososela, Leseho ha re ho lumela.

Jesu u lule ho rona, U re etsetse khotso;
Leleka fifi la sebe, U bonesetse lefats’e.

Boholo ka Jesu ke tsebe, Boholo ka mohau ke bonts’e.,
Ke bone poloko ea Hae; Lerato le Ea nchoetseng.

Qoqa se seng ka Jesu, Le ka kelello ea Hae;
Moea oa Molimo mphe, Ho tseba ka Jesu oa ka.

Ithute se seng ka Jesu, Atamela ka thapelo;
Mamela lentsoe la Hae; Bolella ba bang ka Eena.

Se seng ka Jesu Morena, Ka setulo sa borena;
Paka taba tseo le uena; Le ka tsa ho khutla ha Hae.

Ho hotle ho ts’epa Jesu, Ho utloa lentsoe la Hae;
Le ho boloka ts’episo, Ho rialo Morena.

Ho monate ho mo ts’epa, Ho ts’epa mali a Hae;
Ka tumelo ho ntlhoekisa, maling a Hae a matle.

E ho hotle ho mo ts’epa, Ho tela libe tsohle;
Ho Jesu ho ikukela, Bophelo thabo khotso.

Ke thabetse ho mo ts’epa, Ho tela libe tsohe,
’Me kea tseba O na le ’na, O tla ba le ’na hohle.

Le monate letsatsi la ho ikhethela Mong a ka;
A pelo ee nyakaletseng, e bolele thabo ena.

Ho felile ho phethiloe, ke oa Morena Ke oa ka,
O na mpitse ka latela ka thabela pitso eo.

U phomole pelo ea ka, nahana ka lintho tsena;
U se tlohe ho Morena, Eena ea ruileng molemo

hymns.chorus:
Monate tsatsi lee Jesu a ntlhatsoitseng sebeng;
O nthutile ho rapela le ho phela ka nyakallo.
Le letle tsatsi lee Jesu a ntlhatsoitseng sebeng.

hymns.lyrics:
Tlong ba ratang Morena, Thabo ea rona e tsejoe;
Re bineng hantle hommoho, Re bineng hantle hammoho,
Re pote terone, Re pote terone.

Ba hanang ho bina, Ba sa tsebeng Molimo;
\'Me bana ba leholimo, \'Me bana be leholimo,
Ba bue ka thabo, Ba bue ka thabo.

Thaba ea Sione, E hlahisang botle;
Re eso fihle holimo, Re eso fihle holimo
Litseleng tsa gauda, Litseleng tsa gauda.

A re keng re bine, Meokho e ome;
Re tsamaea Emmanuele, Re tsamaea Emmanuele,
Fats’eng a Holimo, Fats’eng a Holimo.

hymns.chorus:
Re ea teng Sione, E ntle E ntle Sione;
(T&B)
Rona re ea Sione, E ntle, E ntle Sione;
Re ea holimo Sione, Motse motle oa Molimo
(T&B)
Re teng Leholimong.

hymns.lyrics:
Topollo ke rata ho e pheta, Ke lopolotsoe ka mali;
Ke lopolotsoe ka mohau, Ke ngoana Hae kamehla.

Topollo e ea nthabisa, Haho puo e nka e buang;
Ke tseba hore seli la Hae, Le lutse ho ’na kamehla.

Ke nahana ka Mopholosi, Ke nahana tsatsi lohle;
Ke ntse ke bina ke sa khutse, Ke bina lerato la Hae.

Ke tla bona botle ba Hae, Morena eo a nthabisang;
Ratong la Hae O a nkalosa, O isa pina’ bosiu.

Ke ea tseba moqhaka o teng, Mane meahong e metle;
Kapele ha ho ’so phethiloe, Ke tla lula le Morena.

Leruo la gauda, ho ’na ha se letho,
Ke batla leholimo, ke kene mohlapeng;
Bukeng ea Hau ea ’muso, maqhepheng a matle,
U mpolelle ’Moloki, Na ke ngoliloe teng?

Libe tsa ka li ngata, tje ka lehlabathe;
Empa mali a ’Moloki ona a ntekane,
Empa mali a ’moloki on’a ntekane,
Le ts’episo e ngotsoe, ka hlaku tse khanyang.

Motse o motle oane, tulong ea leseli;
Moo ba halalelitsoeng, ba aparo tse ts’oeu;
Mo bobe bo sa keneng, ho senya ntho tse ntle
Tebellong ea mangeloi, na ke ngoliloe teng?

Re memetsoe moketeng oa Hae, Ho lula le batho ba Hae teng;
Ho tla ba joang ho uena le ’na Krese ha ’kena?

Meqhaka bakeng sa meutloa, Khalalellong ea shoetseng batho,
Pono ee ntle joang pel’a rona Kreste ha ’kena.

Nakong eo ho tla bonesoa, Lintho tse li patetsoeng bohle;
Re tla tsebana libopeho, Kreste ha ’kena.

Mahlo a Hae a tla talima, Bohle ba apereng tse ts’oeu;
Botle ha re ka ema tekong; Kreste ha ’kena.

Khao-hano e ke keng ea fela Bohloko ho ba lahlehileng;
Ho ts’abeha joang nakong eo Ha Kreste a kena.

Morena re fe ’hlohonolo, E mong le e mong a lebele;
Hore re se ke ra u ts’aba, Mohlang U kenang.

hymns.chorus:
Roetse mangata, roetse mangata;
Re tla thaba ha re roetse mangata,
Roetse mangata, roetse mangata;
Re tla thaba ha re roetse mangata.

hymns.lyrics:
Ke utloa lentsoe la Molisa, Lefeelleng le mo lefifing;
A bitsa tse lahlehileng, Hole le mohlape oa Hae.

Ke mang ea ka eang ho thusa, Ho ’matlisa malahleha;
Ke mang ea tla li khutlisang Moo li ka ba polokehong?

Utloa ha li lla mo feelleng, Moo lithabeng tse phahameng;
Utloa ha Morena A re: Tsamaea u eo li batla.

Thusang balahlehi, Le ba baballeng;
Ba phamoleng sebeng le lebitleng, le lleleng batloli,
Tsosang ba oeleng; Ba pheteleng ka Jesu ’Moloki.

Leha ba mo nyatsa, O ba emetse;
O emetse ba ba sokolohang
Ba lekeng ka matla le ka bonolo O tla ts’oarela ba mo lumelang.

Ka pelong ea motho eo a leng tekong,
Ho patiloe see seka bolokang;
Ba angoa ka lerato le ka mosa, ba tla khutlela ba tsohe hape.

Thusang balahlehi, ho le ts’oanetse;
Morena O tla le nea ketso,
Tseleng e ts’esane le ka mamello, ba bolelleng ’Moloki O shoele.

Hole haufi masimo a tletse, Mangata a butsoitseng;
Hole haufi gauda e ea benya, Matsoapong le lithoteng.

Ba rome e sa le ka meso, Le hona mots’eare;
Ha tsatsi le ea likela, Ba phuthe le kahohle.

Uena u rongoang ke Morena, E ea phutha mangata;
Leholimong le mantsiboea U tla itulela.

Sebetsang he bahlanka ba Molimo,
A re sebetseng tsela’ Morena rona;
Ka lentsoe la Hae re tla fumana matla
A re etseng ka matla ’rona ntho tsohle

Sebetsang le fepe batho ba lapileng
Le ba hulele selibeng sa bophelo;
Sefapano e tla ba thabo ea rona.
“Re bolela bophelo bo se nang theko.”

Le sebetseng hoba mosebetsi o teng,
Hobane ’muso oa lefifi o tla oa,
Bitso la Jehova le tla utloahala;
Ho boleloe bophelo bo se nang theko.

Sebetsang Morena a be a tlo fihla,
Mageloi a tla tla ho tla kotula;
Re tla lula motseng oa bahalleli;
Re bine bophelo bo seng theko.

Morena ha e-sa le hoseng, Utloa kopo ea ka;
Ho Uena ke tla rapela, Ke talimme Uena.

A u ke U nkhule moeeng, Tseleng ena ea Hau;
Mesebetsi eohle ea ka, E tle loke hantle.

Bao ba O ratang Jesu, E ba tla kholisoa;
Molimo O tla ba thusa, Ka mohau oa Hae.

Lebela nako ha eo,U lebele kajeno,
Lebela u se hlolehe,Rapela Mokreste;
Lebela nama ea tseta,’me sera ke see matla,
U lebele monyali,Leha a ka lieha.

U leleke le boroko, Tlosa le pelaelo;
U ts’episitsoe moputso, phomolong holimo,
Lebela ’me u rapele, Eena ’Moloki oa hao,
O u utloetse bohloko, A ba a rotha mali.

U ts’epe Jesu fela, U hlokomele sera;
U nke lihlomo tsa hao, lebela morena;
Letsatsi ha le chabile, U se ke ua lieha,
Hona nakong eona eo, U lebele mokreste.

Ho felile ho sebetsa Re se re qala Sabbatha;
Moea o tle o tlo thaba Ke tsatsi le halalelang.

Tlong re leboheng Morena, Ka phomolo e monate;
Mahlohololo re a filoe, Kajeno le mehla eohle.

Eka khopolo ea rona, E ka leboha Morena;
Re tla fumana bo Kreste Moea o halalelang.

Ho thaba ho leng ka pelong, Ke ts’epo le ho phomola;
Ho neiloeng balumeli, Ho fihlela bosafeleng.

Sekolo see sa Sabbatha,Ho ’na s’a rateha;
Pelo ea ka h’lokomela,Tsatsi la Sabbatha.

Ka na ka qala ho bona, Tsela ea bophelo;
Ka ba ka bona ho hotle, Ka bona le lehae.

Teng Jesu O ntse A eme, A re e tla ho ’na,
Hore ke tle ke mo khethe, Le Sabbatha ea Hae.

Le se keng la lebala, Sabbatha ’a Molimo;
Ke e ntle ho feta matsatsi a mang ’ohle,
Le ea re phomotsa mesebetsing ea rona;
E re tlisetsa phomolo e tsoang holimong.

E halaletse u mo rapele kajeno;
Ea itseng ho barutuoa, Ke ’na tsela ’phelang,
Ha le latela ’Moloki ka boikokobetso;
O tla re fa metsi a bophelo bo sa feleng

Tsatsing le khethiloeng, thabelang nako e ntle;
Binela Jesu, e leng motsoalle oa bana,
A ’Moloki ea mosa O lokile hakaakang
Tsepiso ea bohlokoa ’tla aha pelong tsohle.

Tlo ka pula letsatsi, La phomolo lefats’eng;
O tle sefubeng sena, Leseli la holimo.

Letsatsi la ho Khutsa, Li’a feta nako tsa Hao;
Pholiso bofutsaneng, Re qete mosebetsi.

Letsatsi la bohlokoa, Le pako le thapelo;
Ke le ka hlalefisang, La hlohonolofatso.

Ke tla lula le moloki ha ke tsamae A se teng;
Ke utloa ha a le ho ’na Ants’oara ka letsoho.

Ke tla lula le ’Moloki, Tumelong ee fokolang;
O tla nts’elisa ka mantsoe, Ho se mang ea ka buang.

Ke tla lula le ’Moloki, Leetong la bophelo,
Lifefong le letsatsing; Le hona har’a lintoa.

Ke tla lula le ’Moloki, Ihlo la Hae le nkhule;
Ke fihle le Jordane, Ke ts’ele ho ea mose.

Ha ke boha sefapano, Moo Moren’a ka shoetseng teng;
Leruo la fats’e lena, Le ke ke la nthusa letho.

Bonang hlohong, le matsohong, Masoabi, lerato ke tseo;
Li kopane ka mohlolo, Ho ea roesitsoeng meutloa.

A ho se rorisoe letho, Ha e se sefapano sa Hae;
Lintho tsohle tsee sa thuseng, Ke tla li tela Morena.

Leha nka rua lefats’e, Eo hase mpho e lekaneng;
Rato leo le lekakang, Le nqosa bophelo ba ka.

Jesu O u bitsa ka bonolo, Hona joale, Hona joale;
U furallelang lerato la Hae,U nts’u ikela hole?

Jesu O bitsa ba mokhathaleng, Hona joale;
Mo nehe thoto  ea libe tsohle, U ke ke ua soabisoa.

.Jesu O ’emetse, tlo ho Eena, O ’emetse, O ’emetse;
Tlisa libe tsa hao maotong a Hae, Tlo se ke ua lieha.

Jesu O u pheheletse utloa, Utloa joale, utloa joale;
Ba mamelang pitso ba tla thaba, Ema U ee ho Eena.

hymns.chorus:
Pheta u tsoaloe hape.
Ka ’nete-nete ke re ho uena;
“Phetang le tsoaloe hape.”

hymns.lyrics:
Re tla aha ho Jesu, Lefikeng le le sa feleng;
Joale mohlang lifefo li tsohang, Na re tla ema joang.

Ba bang ba aha lehlabatheng, La Maruo a lefats’e;
Ba bang maqhubung a sebe, A letlotlo la menyaka.

A le keng le ahe lefikeng, Motheong o tiileng,
Ts’epo ea poloko ea rona; Ke ee e leng ’netena.

hymns.chorus:
Re aha lefikeng;
Fikeng la ’nete, Re tla aha lefikeng ruri
E leng Eena Kreste.

hymns.lyrics:
.Mpolelle pale ea Jesu e ngole pelong ea ka;
Mpolelle ea bohlokoa e fetang tsohle tse ling,
Mpolelle ha mangeloi, a bina tsoalo ea Hae;
Khanya e be ho Molimo, khotso bathong kaofela.

A ila lijo lefeelleng, bolela ts’iu tseo;
Tekong ea libe tsa rona, O na hlole qetellong;
Bolela ts’ebetso ea Hae, le bothata ba Hae;
O n’a telloa A hlorisoa A se na hae A hloka.

Bolela ha A thakhisoa, A utloisoa bohloko,
Bolela ka bitla la Hae bolela tsoho ea Hae,
Pale ea rato le letle, lee bonahalang hantle;
A nke ke lle ha u seba, rato la pholoso ea ka

Utloang mantsoe a ’Moloki, Ke mantsoe a bophelo;
Utloa, hopola Jesu O re “Ba hlohonolo ba etsang”.

Bona ba tla kena metseng, ba lokolloe le sebeng;
Ba hlatsoisitsoe ba tsejoa kahohle ba je tholoana tsa bophelo.

hymns.chorus:
Ba hlohonolo ba etsang taelo, Ba hlohonolo ba hlohonolo.
Re lefeela ha re utloa melao le lits’episo;
Ha re sa phethe hohle—hohle ho lehlohonolo ba etsang.

hymns.lyrics:
E ke bona mali joale, Mohloli o tebileng;
Jesu Moren’a bolokang, O supa ’hlakore.

Ke bona popo e ncha, Le mali a buang;
A re hlahoo e ea feta, Moroallong botebong.

Ke nyolohela leseling, Le leng leholimong;
Ke pelong eo e hloekileng, Jesu O lutse teng.

Ke hoo makatsang lefats’eng, Ho utloa mali ’tsoileng;
’Me ke tseba Jesu feela, Ea nthakhiselitsoeng.

Haufi-ufi le Morena,
Nkhule Jesu oa ka ea ntatileng;
Nts’ike nkatametse ho Uena,
Mpate haha la ka la phomolo;
Mpate haha la ka la phomolo.

Haufi-ufi ha ho letho,
Lee ka bang sehabelo ho Jesu;
Pelo ke ena e nang  le pako,
A k’u ntlhatsoe maling a Hao Jesu;
A k’u ntlhatsoe maling a Hao Jesu.

Haufi-ufi Jesu nkuke,
Ke tele sebe bobe ba sona;
Ho ikhohomosa hohle ho tlosoe,
U mphe Jesu ea thakhisitsoeng;
U mphe Jesu ea thakhisitsoeng.

Haufi-ufi ha ke phetse,
Ts’epo ea ka e be khalalelong;
Le ka lilemo tse li sa feleng,
Ke ba haufi le Uena ’Moloki;
Ke be haufi le Uena ’Moloki.

Ho teng letsatsi lithabeng, le teng le mo leoatleng;
Mahlaseli a gauda a bonoa    le botaleng;
’Me leseli le leholo le tlatsa pelo ea ka,
O lutse teng ’Moloki leseli le ho Uena.

Roleng ke siea masoabi a matsatsi a fetileng;
U nkapesa ka thabo ’me u ntlatsa le ka pako,
Lehaeng la khalalelo lee u nkhapetseng lona,
Ke nyoloha ka pelo moea oa ka o latetse.

Uena ’Moloki ’nthekile hohle ha ka ha Hao;
Bone la rato la Hao le tuke ho U boka,
Lehaeng la khalelo U nkhapetseng ho lona,
Pelo, kelello lia hloa, moea ka oa latela.

Ke oa Hao Morena ke utloa lentsoe, Le mpolella ka rato;
Ke lakatsa ho ba matla, A k’u nkhulele haufi.

Ho monate joang, ka hora eo ha ke le bophahamong;
Ha ke khumama ke le thapelong, Ke bua le motsoalle.

Le teng lerato le sa bonoeng, Ke la lehae ka mose;
Ho teng thabo e ke sa e tsebeng, Ke e-so fihle teng

Ntlohele ke tsamaee le Uena, Molimo joale ka Enoke;
U nts’oare ka letsoho la Hau, U bue ka bonolo le ’na.
Leha ke sa bone tsela, Jesu U tsamaee le ’na.

Ha ke tsamaea ke le mong, Sefefo se halefile;
Fifi le nts’oara maotong, Lira li ntaletse haufi;
U khutsisitse leoatle Morena tsamaea le ’na.

Ha ke phomola ho Uena, Tsa lefats’e ke lefeela;
Ke nka leeto ka sebete, Ke tla phahamisa ’fapano
Ke be ke bone Sione, ’Moloki A tsamaea le ’na.

Ke ea U rata Morena, o feta lefats’e;
Hoba U mphile khotso, E sa senyeheng

U haufi ho fetisa, Bohle ba lefats’e;
Khopolo ea Hao e monate Ho fetisa pina.

U mphile le eona thabo, ’Me ke tla nyakalla;
Kantle ho lerato la Hao, Ke lula ka ts’oabo.

’Moloki e motle oa ka, Ho tla lula joang teng;
Ha tsela ena e le ntle, Ha kena le Uena.

Nka lefats’e U mphe Jesu, Tsa lona ha se letho;
Lerato la Hae le lutse lilemo joalo joalo.

Nka lefats’e u mphe Jesu, Khothatso e ntle moeeng;
’Moloki u ntlhokometse, Ke bina le bothateng.

Nka lefats’e u mphe Jesu Ke bone le nyakallo;
’Me leetong la ka lohle, Seli le tla nchabela.

Nka lefats’e, u mphe Jesu, Ke ts’epe sefapano;
Ke bone pono e khanyang, Re shebane le Jesu.

Nka bophelo ba ka, U ntokisetse ba Hau;
U nke ’tsoho la ka Le etse thato ea Hau.

Nkuke Morena E be ka ho sa eng kae.
Nka maoto a ka, A mathele ho Uena

Nka ’ntsoe la ka kamehla, Ke tle ke U binele.
Nka molomo oa ka, O tlale mantsoe a Hao;

U nke hohle ha ka ’Me ho se sale letho.
Nka nako tsa ka tsohle, Li U rorise joalo;

Nka kelello ea ka U e sebelise eohe.
Inkele thato ea ka, E be ee U e ratang;

Inkele pelo ea ka E be ee U e ratang;
Inkele pelo ea ka E be eona tolo ea Hao.

Nka rato la ka Jesu, Le beoa matong a Hao;
U nkuke hohle ha ka, Ke be oa Hao kamehla.

Ke se ke fumane motsoalle, Eena ea nthatang;
Ke huloa ke lona lerato, A nkisa ho Eena;
O ntlamile moo pelong eaka; Ka khoele e tiileng.
Jesu ’na ke ngoana oa Hao, leha e ka ba neng. .

Ke se ke fumane motsoalle ea mpholositseng;
E seng ka ho phela feela, empa A itela.
Hohle ke nang le hona ke ho beela Eena,
Pelo le ho lula ha ka  ke tsa Hae joalo

Ke se ke fumane motsoallle, Ea filoeng matla;
Ha Eena A ka nkemela tseleng ea leholimo;
Ho ea khanya bakeng sa-ne se ntiisitseng;
Ha ke lese ho sebetsa ke tla phomola pele.

Ke se ke fumane motsoalle, Ea mosa ruri;
Eena O tla ntsamaisa ke fihle leholimong;
Ho Uena ea nthatileng ke fumana matla;
Re tla khaohangoa ke lefu! Che ’na ke oa Hao.

K’utloa ntsoe la Jesu le re \"Tlo phomole ho ’na;
Robala ha u khathetse Moo sefubeng sa ka.\"
Ke tla le ho ’Moloki, Ke khathetse haholo,
Ka fumana phomolo teng, Eena A nthabisa.

Ke utloile Jesu A re, \"Ke u nea feela
Uena ea nyoretsoeng mesi: ’Me o phele,\"
Ka tla ho Jesu Ka noa metsi a phelisang;
Ka nyorolloa, ka nchafala, Joale ke phelile.

Ke utloile Jesu A re,  ke seli la fats’e;
Sheba ho ’na O chabeloe, Tsatsi la phatsimo.
Ka talima Jesu, Eena le letsatsi la ka;
Ke tla tsamaea seling lee ke qete leeto.

Re qhalanye Morena,
U re tlatse ka khotso;
Re ruoe lerato la Hao,
Re lokolloe ka mohau;
Re nchafatsoe, re nchafatsoe,
Re tsamaea lefeeleng.

Ho isoe teboho, khanya,
Evangeli ea thabo;
Litholoana tsa poloko,
Li ate ka lipelong,
Oa ts’epeha, Oa ts’epeha
Re fumanoe moo ’neteng.

Ha re sa ntse re phelile;
Re ineele Morena,
Re titimeng re sa tenoe;
Re na le eona ts’epo,
Re e bone khalalelo;
Eona ea leholimo

Ke leba tsela ’nyolohang, Ke hloa ka matsatsi ohle;
Ke tsamaea ke rapela Morena mpee holimo.

Ha ke lakatse ho lula mona ho nang le khang fela;
Mohlomong ba bang ba rata, ’na ke rata leholimo.

Ke se ke rata holimo, mona Satane Oa ntlhopha;
Tumelo ea ka e utloa pina ea bahalaleli.

Ke ntse ke hloella holimo, Ke tla be ke bone khanya;
Ke kope ke be ke thole, Morena mpee holimo.

U phele ka ho ’na, Jesu Morena oa ka;
Uena U be karabo, potsong tsohle tsa ka,
U phele ka ho ’na U etse thato ea Hao;
’Me ’na ke bonahatse, khalalelo ea Hao.

Mele o inehetseng, O hloekisitsoe sebeng,
A leseli la Hao le ke le o khants’etse;
Fats’e le ke le thole, ’mele o fetoloe,
Mohlanka oa Hao a tsamaisoe ke Uena.

Lintho tsa oona tsohle, li ikokobetse;
Li lumele hore li ke li sebelisoe,
Li hloke hlolohelo liketsong melekong;
Li be ts’ebetsong ea Hao, ho se pelaelo.

Nke ke lule phomolong le ho lokeng hohle,
Ke ntse ke U emetse, ha Uena U ntlhoka;
U phele ka ho ’na Morena oa Marena,
Uena U be karabo potsong tsa ka tsohle.

Ntate nkhulele haufi, ke ea u lakatsa nkuke;
Haufi nkenye matsohong ke batla ho phomola.

’Moloki nkhulele haufi, se ke ka U tlohela;
Ha ke le matsohong a Hao, ke ea itebala.

’Moloki nkhulele haufi, se ke ka U tlohela;
Ha ke le matsohong a Hao, ke ea itebala.

Kae le kae le Jesu nka ea ka ts’epo, Kae le kae moo A ka nkisang lefats’eng;
Ka ntle ho Eena thabo ke lefeela; Kae le kae Jesu ’a le teng ha ke ts’abe.

Hohle ke na le Jesu ha ke ts’abe, Ha metsoalle e ntahla, Eena O teng;
Leha A ka ntamaisa bothateng, Kae le kae Jesu ke ntlo ea lithoko.

Hohle ke na le Jesu nka robala, Ha ke tleloa ke meriti e mets’o,
Ha nke ke ka ts’oha ho ea tahlehong; Kae le kae le Jesu e tla ba lehae.

Bolela le ’na Jesu, bua ka bonolo;
U sebe ka lerato, hoba ha u nots’i,
U bule pelo ea ka, ho utloa ’ntsoe la Hau;
U ntlatse ka lithoko, ke thabe ho Uena.

Bua le bana ba Hao, ba hulele tseleng;
Ba tlatse ka nyakallo, ba rute  thapelo,
Ba ke ba u nehele bophelo ba bona,
Akofisa borena, re bone Morena

Bua joaloka khale, ha u its’enotse;
Ke tsebe ho nts’oanelang, ke phethe taelo,
U nkise khalalelong, nthuse ho ’rorisa;
Ke etse ka ho thaba, ke U nee hlompho

hymns.chorus:
U bue ke ho seba, seba ka lerato;
U tla ’ne u be mohloli, hoba ha u ’nots’i;
Bua le ’na Morena, bua ka bonolo,
Joale ke utloe u seba, hoba ha U ’nots’i.

hymns.lyrics:
Molebeli mpolelle ka meso, botle ba Sione;
Na ponts’o, tsa ho tla ha Hao, li khants’itsoe mo tseleng,
E motsamai tsoha, qamaka mafube a ea hlaha,
Apara aparo tsa Hao, bo sele tsoha, tsoha.

Molebeli bona seli, le khants’elitse tsela;
Ponts’o li tletse ka hohle tsa letsatsi le letlang,
Ha lekolilo le lla ho tsosa ba leng leoatleng;
Bahalaleli ba shoeleng ba apara ho sa shoeng.

Molebeli boka seli, selemo sa Sabbatha,
Re phahamisa mantsoe, ’muso oa Hao o haufi;
Molebeli ke ea bona, khalalelo ea Kanana,
Motse le bona botle boo le ho phahama ha teng.

Moleti motseng oa gauda, O lutse troneng ea Hae;
Ke Morena oa Sione, O busa le ka khotso,
Le lithabeng tsee khanyang, tse phatsimang haholo,
Melatsoana e runyang, e matha metsi a matle.

Moleti fats’e le haufi, le nang le litholoana;
Ho hotle joang kameso, tholoana tsa Edene;
Ho utloahala lipina, li ntse li luma holimo,
Bongata ke bo mametseng, kapele re tla ba teng.

Ho se tsoe melomong ea lona mantsoe a khalefo,
Tse boima tse kapelong Li lahloe li e so senye.

Lerato ke le hloekileng Metsoalle e ts’epehang;
Li se ke tsa sengoa fela Ka bona booatla fela.

Lentsoenyana la khalefo,  Le ferekanya pelo;
Tse ntle tsa bophelo li rojoa ke le le leng fela.

Ke bolokeloe Jesu, Ka matla ’Molimo;
Ke tsehetsoe lefats’eng, Likhatong tsa Jesu.

Ke bolokeloe Jesu, Ke etse thato ’Hae;
Ke thabele Moreneng, Mosebetsing oa Hae.

Ke bolokeloe Jesu, Khaohanong ea lefats’e;
Ee ikokobelitse, Ka pelo e hloekileng.

Ke bolokeloeJesu, Ke be oa Hae hohle;
E be ka ho sa feleng, Ke be oa Hae feela.

Ke lutse maotong a Jesu, k’utloa mantsoe a matle;
Tulo e ntle ea bohlokoa Ke tla lula kamehla;
Ke lutse maotong a Jesu, Ke sheba tse ka morao,
Rato la Hae la mohau, Le hapa pelo ea ka.

Ke kae moo ho shoang ho ka ba, le lona hlohonolo?
Ke bea libe le ts’oabo, Ke tle ke be phomolong,
Ke lutse maotong a Jesu, Ke tla lla ke rapele;
Ke phutha botlalong ba Hae Mohau le Ts’eliso.

Hlohono’fatsa ’Moloki ke leta maotong a Hao,
A k’u nchebe ka lerato Ke bohe sefahleho;
Mphe mohopolo oa Jesu, nkhalaletse ka Eena,
Ke bonts’e ha A le ho ’na, Eena ho loka ha ka.

hymns.chorus:
Molimo ’tla hlako... la likeleli le lefu.
(hlakola)(lefu)
Ha ho baloe le lilemo, Teng bosiu ha bo eo.
Menyako ea perela, e teng motseng ola;
Mapatlelo ke a gauda,teng bosiu ha bo eo.
Menyako ha e koaloe, hona motseng ola;
Ho teng noka ’bophelo, teng bosiu ha bo eo.
Tsatsi ha le hlokehe, hona motseng ola;
Teng  Konyana ke khanya, teng bosiu ha bo eo.

O tla tla... A re emeng re loke,
O tlatla... Alleluya, alleluya;
(O tla tla) (O tla tla)
O tla ka maru khalalelong ea Ntatae,
Ha re tsebe nako.
Leseli le teng ho ba batlang poloko;
’Nete eteng bukeng Ts’enolong ea Jesu,
Le bopr’feta bo supa nako ela;
Ha re tsebe nako.
Re tla rapela re khants’itse mabone;
Re le ts’ebetsong Morena A be A tle,
Re bine thabong re hlokomele ponts’o,
Ha re tsebe nako.

hymns.lyrics:
Ts’episo e ntle ho ba lumelang,
Bonang ke ea tla ho tla tla nka ba ka;
Ts’oarang le tiise, Kotsi li kholo;
’Me u se robale, lebela leta.

hymns.chorus:
Ts’oarang le tiise, ke ts’episo, ntle;
Borena le tla bo khutlisetsoa,
Kenang thabong ea ka, lulang le ’na;
Moqhaka o motle, Ts’oarang le tiise.
Re tla rapela ha ho khants’itsoe,
Ho ba bang O tla joaloka ka lesholu;
Re’tseba O haufi, Nako ha e tsejoe,
Joaloka selemo ponts’o ’hlabula.
E, ena ke ts’episo ea rona,
Ho hlaha ha Morena A le khanyeng;
Ke hona ho fetang lits’episo,
Ke ea tla kapele, ts’oarang le tiise.

hymns.lyrics:
Re bua ka ’muso motle, le ka lefats’e le letle;
Ho boleloa botle ba teng, ’me ho tla ba joang ho ba teng.
Le ka ’mila ea gauda, e khabisitsoeng ka majoe,
Limakatso tsee sa tsejoeng, ho tla ba joang ho lula teng.
Re bua tokollo ’sebeng, bofutsaneng le melekong;
Meleko, kahare le kantle, ho tla ba joang ho lula teng.
Ka liketso tsa lerato, le aparo tsa bakhethoa;
Kereke ea matsibolo ho tla ba joang ho lula teng.
Bofumeng, bomalimabe, ntokisetse leholimo;
Haufinyane ke tla utloa ka monate oa hona teng.
Re tsamaea le masimong a borena bo boholo;
Le mangeloi le bakhethoa, le Jesu A le hona teng.

Jesu re Kopane, Teng tlung ena ea Hao;
Tlo le Uena a re kena, Re be mahlong a Hao.
Lipelo tsa rona, Li ea u hlorela;
Le oona moea oa rona, O ntse O u llela.
Ho kopa ha Hao, Nate re u utloe;
Ha ho buloa lentsoe la Hao Le Uena re Utloe.
U re lokisetse, Rona batho ba Hao;
Mohlang re shoa Re boele hona teng leroleng.

Leha ke le molibe;
Jesu O ile a nchoela;
Hore ke tle ke phele,
Hore ke se ke ka shoa;
Tje ka kala morara
Ke oa ka ke ’na oa Hae.
Boholo ba lerato,
Bo feta leholimo;
Le ho teba leoatleng,
Le teng ka ho sa felang;
Le mphihletse koa hole
Ke eso ho mo batle.
Leha ke le molibe,
Kreste ke tsohle ho ’na;
Tseba se ke se hlokang,
O tseba le masoabi;
Ke bolokoa ke Eena
O ts’ehetsa bophelo.

hymns.chorus:
Lebitso... le letle, Ke ts’epo ea lefats’e,
(lebitso... leletle)
Lebitso... le letle, Ke thabo ea lefats’e.
(lebitso le letle—letle)
Nka lebitso la Jesu, Ke lona thebe rona;
Ha U ’so bone meleko, Ts’epa lebitso lena.
Oho! Lebitso la Jesu, Lona le ea thabisa;
Ha A s’a re amohetse, Re tla ’minela Eena.
Re khumame ka lebitso, Re oele maotong A Hae;
Ke Morena Oa Marena, Re boka mosa oa Hae.

E be khalalelo bitsong la Hae;
Mali a tsela pelo ea ka, rorisang Eena.
Poloko ea ka ea makatsa, Jesu O mpholositse sebeng;
Fapanong ke moo A nkukileng, rorisang Eena.
Mohloli o pholosang sebeng ke thabile ha ke kene teng;
Jesu oa nts’ehetsa oa nthusa, rorisang Eena.
Tlo Mohloling oo monate itihele maotong a Hae,
Teng joale U hlatsuoe sebeng, rorisang Eena.

hymns.lyrics:
U rata ho phelela Jesu u hloekile;
U ka tsamaea le Eena mo tseleng;
Kapa u ka mo nea moroalo a roale?
Lumella thato ea Hae.

Ho hotle joang haeeng moo rato le leng teng;
Ho teng molum’a thabo, rato le le teng.
Khotso ea ngatafala, thabo e ka nqa tsohle;
Nako e feta hantle moo rato le le teng.

Khutsang tu! Khutsang tu! R’utloa ho seba,
Khutsang tu! Khutsang tu! Bolokang lentsoe

Khutsang tu! Khutsang tu! Hoa ’halalela;
Aletareng ena Ea thomo e ntle.

Khutsang tu! Khutsang tu! A re rapeleng;
R’utloa ka Edene Ka nako ena.

Khutsang tu! Khutsang tu! Ngolang mohau;
Khutsang tu! Khutsang tu! Le Mo emeleng.

hymns.chorus:
Mahlohonolo ke ao re a hlokang;
Re ts’olleloa ka mohau,
Kopang mahlohonolo.

hymns.lyrics:
Na Jesu oa ntlhokomela ha ke hlorela pina;
Ke le bothateng le tsietsing,
Ke se ke khathetse tseleng.

Na Jesu O hlokomela ha tsela e ’lefifi;
Ha letsatsi le likela, bosiu,
Na O tla lula haufi;

Na Jesu O ntsa hlokomela, meleko e ntlhahela;
Pelo e bohloko ke sa khaotse
Ke lla bosiu kaofela.

Na Jesu Oa hlokomela ha ke tlohela baratuoa,
Pelo ee ea ka e batla ho shoa;
Na ho Eena ke lefeela.

hymns.chorus:
Kea tseba Oa hlokomela, ho ama pelo ea Hae;
Linakong tse thata ke ea tseba,
O nts’a ntlhokomela.

hymns.lyrics:
Moloki O re uena m’kreste tsoha,
Ka thebe la sabole ka letsohong;
Loana le meleko boea ka sebete,
Empa ka bohale talima sera.

Hoo e leng kotsi u ho hlokomele u se cheche
U se na thebe;
Ha u tla li hlola lira tsa hau,
Ema mohale u itlhokomele.

Loanela taba tsa morena,
Ka matla u loane ho fihla qetellong;
Mo latele hohle moo A u isang;
Loana ka bohale talima sera.

Tsoela pele Morena oa hao O teng,
O u nea mosa le sebete;
Lerato la Morena le ka noka,
Ka hoo ema talimana le sera

’Moloki O ts’olotse mali, A shoa Morena ’ka;
A itela A ba nchoela seboko see kang ’na.

Na ke ka liketso tsa ka, A sholeng sefateng;
Kutloelo-bohloko, rato ke tse fetisisang

Marotholi a masoabi a ke ka a lefa;
Ke ’na enoa Morena ’ka ke tla ke le joalo.

Mangeloi haa bina, Jesu seli lefats’eng;
Khalalelo Moreneng, Jesu seli lefats’eng.

Tsohang bohle ka thabo, Jesu se li lefats’eng;
Tlong hlolong le holimo, Jesu se lefatse’eng.

Kreste O khabisitsoe, Jesu seli lefats’eng;
Moren’a ea sa feleng, Jesu seli lefats’eng.

Bokang Moren’a ea sa feleng, Jesu seli lefats’eng.
Bokang tsatsi la toka, Jesu seli lefats’eng.

Ke lehlohonolo, kopano leratong,
Setsoalle e ka ba se ts’oanang le sa holimo.

Ka pele ho terone, Re lla ka thapelo;
Boikemisetso ba rona bo tla fela teng

Mats’oenyeho ohle, le eona meroalo;
Le ho Llellana ha rona, Hohle ho ea tsejoa.

Ha re khaohana, Re utloa bohloko;
Empa re ts’epa hore re tla be re kopane.

Tlong ho Jesu, Tlong ho Jesu; Tlong ho Jesu joale,
Joale tlong ho Jesu,Tlong ho Jesu joale.

Oa boloka, oa boloka, Oa boloka joale;
Joale a ka etsa, A ka etsa joale.

A ka etsa, A ka etsa, A ka etsa joale;
Joale a ka etsa, A ka etsa joale.

Bitsa Eena, Bitsa Eena Bitsa Eena joale
Joale bitsa Eena, Bitsa Eena joale

Bitsa Eena, Bitsa Eena Bitsa Eena joale
Joale bitsa Eena, Bitsa Eena joale.

O letile, O letile, O letile joale;
Joale O letile, O letile joale.

U mo ts’epe, U mo ts’epe U mo ts’epe joale;
Joale u mo ts’epe, u mo ts’epe joale.

Hlohonolo, Hlohonolo, Hlohonolo joale;
Joale Hlohonolo, hlohonolo joale.

Tsatsi le halalelang, La Jehova ’Morena;
Ke lona la bosupa, Le khethiloe ke Eena.

Mosebetsi oa qetoa, Ho e so qale lona,
A le hlohonolofatsa, Ke ka hoo re phomolang.

Batho ba le fetotse, Ba khetha la Sontaha;
Talima mangolo ha, a bolelle joalo.

Ba bangata ba sa re, Sontaha e lokile,
Empa buka’ Morena eona ea ba hanyetsa.

’Na ka talimisisa, Ka e bona Sabatha;
Ka phakisa ho kena, tseleng ena ea ’nete.

It’etlehe matsohong a Jesu, O tla u thusa, O tla u thusa,
Ha u ts’epa lerato la Hae Oa u tlatsa pako.

Its’etlehe matsohong a Jesu, O tla bonesa tsela ea hau;
Mo sale morao fela thabong. Utloa lentsoe la Hae.

Its’etlehe matsohong a Jesu, Tlisa tsietsi tsohle tsa hau;
Moroalo o bonalang boima, O tle ho Morena.

Its’tlehe matsohong a Jesu, Tlo, u sie tsohle ho Eena;
O tletse lerato ka pelong, Ha’ fifale mahlo.

Fa ’Fatlhogo Di Lebana, Le Kreste Go Tla Nna Jang
Boitumelo fa ke mmona, Jeso Kreste yo’ ntshwetseng.

Ka Lefitshwana Kea Mmona Go Le Losire Gare;
Me go tla tsatsi ja sego, Ja kgalalelo ya ’Gwe.

Boitumelo Mo Go Ene, Botlhoko Bo Fedile;
Tsela di siamesitswe Lefifi le fedile.

’Fatlhogo Di Tla Lebana Go Bona Le Go Itse;
’Fatlhogo di tla lebana Le Jeso Yo o nthatang.

Morena Ke Batla Go Itekanela;
Ke batla O nne, go nna ka bosaeng kae;
O thube disetwa, mme O ntshe baba;
Janong ntlhatswa ke tla gaisa kapoko.

Morena Jeso Leba Kwano Tlase,
Mme nthusa ke dire tshupelo tota
Kea ineela, le gotlhe ke go itseng
Janong ntlhatswa ke tla gaisa kapoko.

Morena Jeso Ke Rapelela Se;
Ke eme dinaong tsa ’Go tse bapotsweng,
Tumelo e mpontsha madi a ntlhatswang;
Janong ntlhatswa ke tla gaisa kapoko.

Morena Ke Letile Ke Itshokile;
Tla O bope pelo e ntsha teng ga me;
Ga O ise O gane ba ’Go batlang,
Janong ntlhatswa ke tla gaisa kapoko.

Tsiri, Tsiri Fela, Mo Diatlanyaneng;
Re di naya Jeso Banyana ba ’Gwe.

Utlwang Peni Dia Wa: Reetsang Fa Di Wa;
Tsotlhe tsa ga Jeso, O tla tsa’a tsotlhe.

Ka Re Le Banyana, Re Na Le Peni;
Mme fa re godile, Re tla na’a thata.

Lefa Madi Mannye, Re Mo Na’a Rato,
O tsa’a neo ya rona A ntse A nyenya.

Tsoga Moya Wa Me Dira, O Nne Tlhaga Tirong
Sianela legodimong, Serwalong se’ sa sweng.

O Bidiwa Ke Modimo, Ka Ntswe Je Tshedileng;
Ke One O neelang tuelo, Keletsong ya gago

Leru Ja Basupi Le Teng, Je Le Go Bolokang;
Lebala kgato e fetileng, Tswela pele tseleng.

Mmoloki O Simolotse Tshiano Ya Rona;
Re se’ re rwesitswe phenyo, Re rola diako.

Ke Etla Kwa Mokgorong Lehumeng, Phoufalong;
Tsotlhe ke ya di latlha, Ke tla bona poloko.

Ke Go Tlhologeletswe, Sebe Se Ntse Se Mpusa;
Jeso O nthaya A re, "Nna ke tla go tlhapisa"

Ke Go Fa Tsotlhe Tsa Me, Ditsala Le Dikhumo;
Moya mmele ’nna’a tsa ’Go, Tsotlhe ka bosakhutleng.

K’ikanya Tsholofetso, Janong Ke Utlwa Madi;
Ke namaletse fatshe, Ke bapotswe le Jeso.

Jeso O Ntlatsa Moeeng, Mme Ke Itekanetse;
Gotlhe k’itekanetse; Kgalalelo go Kwana.

Morena Ke Utlwa Masego A O Ntse O A Nesa;
A kgorisa ba nyorilweng, A ke a nnele le nna,

Rara Yo O Pelonomi, Se Mphete Nna Moleofi;
Mme lefa O ka Wa mpheta Se fete le masego.

A Ke Ntse Ke Letse Sebeng? Mme Ke Go Hutsafatsa?
Ke ntse ke le wa lefatshe? Intshwarele mpoloka:

Se Mphete Mo’a O Boitshepo, O Ka Bontsha Difofu;
Supa neo ya ga Jeso Bua kagiso go nna.

Wena Kea Go Batla, Jeso Yo Bolokang;
Lentswe ke ja Gago, Je le gomotsang.

Wena Kea Go Batla, Nna Gaufi Le Nna;
Thaelo kea di fenya, Fa O le gaufi.

Wena Kea Go Batla, Thabong Le Botlhokung;
Tla jana mme O nne, Botshelo lefela.

Wena Kea Go Batla, Nthute Thato Ya ’Go;
Diragatsa go nna Tsholofetso ya ’Go

Wena Kea Go Batla, Wena Yo Boitshepo;
Ao ntira wa Gago Morw’a Modimo.

Gotlhe Go Jeso Kea Ineela Ka Kgololego;
Ke tla Mo rata ka metlha, Ke ikanye go Ene.

Gotlhe Kea Ineela Jeso, Ka Obama Dinaong;
Boitumelo jwa lefatshe, Ke bo latlhile ntsaya.

Gotlhe Kea Ineela Jeso Mmoloki Ntira Wa ’Go;
Ke utlwe mo’a o boitshepo, Ke itse gore O’a me.

Gotlhe Kea Ineela Jeso, Ke Utlwa Mo’a Boitshepo.
Boitumelo jwa poloko, Kgalalelo ’ineng ja ’Gwe.

Sala Le Nna: Tsatsi Lea Phirima;
Go ya ntshofala; Morena sala:
Fa go se bathusi le kgomotso,
Thuso ya batlhoki, sala le nna.

Botshelo Bo Feta Ka Bonako;
Thamo le tlotlo tsa ’fatshe jeno;
Tsotlhe dia feta di ya nyelela,
Wena Yo sa feteng sala le nna.

Ga Ke Kope Foko Je Le Fetang,
Mme jaak’ O ntse le barutwa Jeso,
Kgomotso ka bopelotelele,
Tla mme O se ete sala le nna.

Ke Go Batla Ka Dinako Tsotlhe,
Tshwaro ya ’Go ’ka fenya Satane.
Ke mang yo’ tla nkgogang jaaka Wena?
Botlhokung, kgatlhegong, sala le nna

Fa O Le Teng Ke Tlelwa Ke Thata;
Le khutsafalo ga e botlhoko;
Ga ke tshabe loso le lebitla;
Kea di Fenya fa O sala le nna.

Tsholofelo Ya Me E Mading Le Tshiamong Ya Jeso
Ga ke ikanye bonna, mme Ke ikaega go Jeso.

Fa Lefifi Le Mo Sira, Ke Ikhutsa Tshwarong Ya ’Gwe;
Mo sefefong se se tona, Ke tlhomame mo go Ene.

Ikano, Kgolagano Le Madi A Gagwe Dia Nthusa;
Fa batho botlhe ba ntatlha, K’ Ene tsholofelo ya me.

Fa A Tla Ka Loshalaba, Ao, Ke Fitlhelwe Go Ene;
Ke apesitswe tshiamo, Ke eme gaufi teroneng.

Modim’o Nne Le Lona Lotlhe;
O tshegetse, O kaele;
Mo sakeng O lo boloke;
Re tsamae re be re rakane.

Modim’o Nne Le Lona Lotlhe;
Phukeng ts’ One O lo fitlhe,
Ka mana O lo tlamele,
Re tsamae re be re rakane.

Modim’o Nne Le Lona Lotlhe,
Tlalelong O lo femele,
Mabogong O lo dibele;
Re tsamae re be re rakane.

Modim’o Nne Le Lona Lotlhe,
Loratong O lo tsholetse,
Mme O lo fapose loso;
Re tsamae re be re rakane.

Lo A Nkopelele Gape, ’Foko A Botshelo;
Ke bone bontle jwa one, ’Foko a Botshelo;
’Foko a botshelo, A nthuta tumelo.

Jeso Mmoloki O Lerile, ’Foko A Botshelo;
Reetsang pitso tsa lorato,’ Foko a Botshelo;
Ke a neo fela, Re bidiwa godimo,

Bolelang Bontle Jwa Pitso,’ Foko A Botshelo;
Boitshwerelo go botlhe,’ Foko a Botshelo;
Jeso ke Mmoloki, O ya re itshepisa....

Go Tla Mogopolo, Go Nna O Masisi;
Ke gaufi gae gompieno Go gaisa gale.

Gaufi Tlung Ya Rara, Kwa Mannong A Mantsi;
Gaufi kwa Jeso O busang, Lewatleng je lentle.

Ke Gaufi Go Gae, Ke Rola Morwalo,
Mokgoro wa bohutsana, ke rwala serwalo.

Ke Timeletse Kgakala, Janong Ke Tla Gae,
Ke sepetse mo boleong, Jeso ke tla gae.

Ke Sentse Ngwaga Tse Dintle, Janong Ke Tla Gae;
Ke ikwatlha’a ka go lela Jeso ke tla gae.

Ke Lapisitswe Ke Sebe, Janong Ke Tla Gae;
Ke tla ikanya rato lwa ’Gu; Jeso ke tla gae.

Kopo Ya Me Ke Yone E, Janong Ke Tla Gae;
Gobo Morena A ntshwetse, Jeso ke tla gae.

Ke Tlhoka Madi A Gagwe, Janong Ke Tla Gae;
Ntlhapise ke nne mosweu, Jeso ke tla gae.

Lotlhe Tlotlang That’a Jeso: Baengele Ba Wa,
Lereng rwalo sa bogosi, Lo rwese Morena;
Lereng rwalo sa bogosi, Lo rwese Morena.

Lona Ba Lo Itshenketsweng, Lona Masalela,
Mo tlotleng Yo lo bolokang, Lo rwese Morena;
Mo tlotleng Yo lo bolokang, Lo rwese Morena.

Ditso Tsotlhe Le Ditshaba, Mo Lefatshing Jeno,
Botlhe a ba Mo nee tlotlo, Ba rwese Morena;
Botlhe a ba Mo nee tlotlo, Ba rwese Morena.

’Kete Re Na Le Baitshepi, Re Ka Wela Fatshe,
Re tla opela ka gale Re rwese morena;
Re tla opela ka gale, Re rwese Morena.

Jeso Morati Oa Me, Ke Fofela Go Wena,
Fa dintelo di ntlela, Ke tlelwa ke sefefo:
Mphitlha, ao, Mmoloki, ’Fefo se be se fete,
Ke tsene polokegong, o bo O nkamogele.

Ga Go Phemelo Epe; Ke Lebile Go Wena;
Ao O se nteseletse, Wena nna O ntsholetsa.
O tsholofelo ya me, Thuso e tswa go Wena;
O nkhurumetse tlhogo, ka diphuka tsa Gago.

Ke Batla Wena Kreste, Go Gaisa Dilo Tsotlhe;
O tsose ba ba oleng, O fodise balwetsi.
Go boitshepo Wena; Nna ke mosiamolodi;
Ke tletse leswe, sebe, O tletse kgalaletso.

O Tletse Kgalaletso, E Bipang Dibe Tsa Me;
Go tle nok’e fodisang, O ntshegetse boitshekong.
O noka ya botshelo, A ke nwe kgololegong,
O tswele pelong ya me, Tsogela bosakhutleng.

hymns.chorus:
Bogolo ka Jeso, Bogolo ka Jeso,
Ke bone poloko ya ’Gwe;
Lorato lwa Yo O ntshwetseng.

hymns.lyrics:
Keng Se Ka Ntlhatswang Sebe? Fa E Se Madi A Jeso
Keng se ka intshekisang? Fa e se madi a Jeso.

Ke Bona Se Se Ntlhatswang, Mme Ke Madi A Ga Jeso;
Ke lopa boitshwarelo- E le ka madi a Jeso.

Ga Go Se’ Ka Letlanyang,- Fa E Se Madi A Jeso;
Ga ke ya dira sepe- Fa e se madi a Jeso.

E Ke Kagiso Ya Me,- E E Mading A Ga Jeso;
E ke tshiamo ya me-E e mading a ga Jeso

Kgalalelo K’opela -One Madi A Ga Jeso;
Ke lere pako ya me- Ke one madi a Jeso.

Le Monate, Tsatsi Ja Go Itlhaolela Modimo;
A pelo e e ipele, E bolele boitumelo.

Go Fedile, Go Dirilwe; Ke Wa Moren’ Ene Wa Me;
O mpiditse, ka latela, Ke itumela mo pitsong.

Gone Janong Pelo Ya Me, Ikhutse Boitumelong;
O se tloge, go Morena, Yo O ruileng molemo.

hymns.chorus:
Le monate tsatsi Le Jeso O ntlhapisitseng:
O nthutile go rapela, Le go tshela boitumelong;
Le monate tsatsi Le Jeso O ntlhapisitseng.

hymns.lyrics:
Ga Ke Re Sepe Khumo, Lefa E Le Gouda;
Ke senka legodimo, Ke tsene lesakeng;
Kwalong lwa gosi jwa Go, Lo lo lontle thatha,
Mpolelela Mmoloki, A ke kwadilwe teng?

Morena Ke Mo Dibeng, Di Jaaka Mosawa,
Mme madi a Mmoloki, A intekanetse;
Go, na le tsholofetso, tlhakeng tse ’phatsimang,
"Lefa di le khubidu, Di tla nna ditshweu"

Motseng O Montle Ole, Mannong A Lesedi,
Kwa ba ’galaleditsweng, Ba kobo tse di tshweu;
Kwa ’sula bo sa tseneng, Go senya tse dintle,
Tebelong ya baengele, A ke kwadilwe teng?

Kwa Tirong: Kwa Tirong: Roma Ba Modimo,
Re lateleng tsela ya Moren’a rona;
Ka lefoko ja Gagwe A re nonotshe,
A re direng ka thata se re se dirang.

Kwa Tirong: Kwa Tirong: Ba Tlala Ba Jeseng;
Motsweding wa Botshelo isang banyorwi;
Kgalalelo ya rona e nne mokgorong,
Fa re bolela mafoko a "Poloko."

Kwa Tirong: Kwa Tirong: Botlhe Ba Ka Dira,
Gonne bogosi jwa lefifi bo tla wa;
Leina ja Jehofa le tla godiswa,
Mo go dumeng ga mantswe, "Poloko fela"

Kwa Tirong: Kwa Tirong Go Ya Kwa Bokhutlong,
Gonne go tla thobo go tla le barobi;
Mme re tla nna legaeeng ja babolokwa,
Mme re ntse re opela "Poloko fela"

Dira Bosigo Bo E Tla, Dira Maphakela;
Dira monyo o le teng, Dira dithunyeng,
Dira le sa tlhatloga, Dira motshegaring;
Dira bosigo bo e tla, Mo go sa dirweng.

Dira Bosigo Bo E Tla, Dira Mo Letsatsing;
Tlatsa nako ka tiro; Go tla boikhutso.
Neela dipaka tsotlhe, Se se ka bolokwang;
Dira bosigo bo e tla, Mo go sa dirweng.

Dira Bosigo Bo E Tla, Tsatsi Le Phirima:
Dira fa le fubila, Dira lea fofa.
Dira fa le fifala,- Le ka letlatlana;
Dira le mo lefifing, Tiro e fetile.

K’opela That’a Modimo, E Tlhotseng Dithaba,
E tsharolotseng lewatle E, le legodimo;
Ke opela ’tlhale jo bo Tlhomileng letsatsi;
Le yone kgwedi mo taolong, Naledi dia utlwa.

K’opela Molemo Wa ’Gwe, Wa Dijo Mo Fatshing,
O tlhotse ka foko ja ’Gwe, A re go molemo.
Morena dikgakgamatso Tsa Gago di gotlhe:
Fa ke tlhatlhoba lefatshe, Gongwe legodimo

Tsotlhe Tse Di Melang Tlase Dia Go Galaletsa;
Maru le difefo di teng, Di laolwa ke Wena.
Le tsone ditshidi di mo Pabalelong ya Go;
Ga go kwa re ka tshabelang, Modimo O gone.

Rara Re Tla G’wena Ka Ke Wena Thuso;
O re sireletse, Rea Go bitsa;
Fatshe lea boitshega. Fa Wena u seo;
Re gomotse fano, Rara’ botlhe.

Re Boloke Babeng, Le Mo Mahutsaneng,
R’ikhutse go Wena Fa re tlhoka;
Re boi re bokoa, O bue kgomotso,
Tla O re nonotshe Ka letsogo.

Re Nee Tshwaro Ya Go, Re Nne Ba Go Fela,
Tlosa nao tsa rona Mo boleong.
Wena O re goge, Mo botshelong jono,
Mme kwa kgalalelong, Re tla nna nao

hymns.chorus:
Jeso, Jeso, O nkutlwe telong;
Fa O etela ba bangwe,
Se mphete le nna.

hymns.lyrics:
Disa Ga Go Nako; Disa Gompieno’
Disa o se fengwe; Rapela Mokreste;
Disa nam’e bokoa; Mme mmaba o thata;
O dise Monyadi; Lefa a diega.

CHORUS (SOPRANO):
Disa o rapele Disa
Disa lefifing le mo motshegaring Mokreste disa.

Leleka Kotselo, O Se Belaele;
O solofeditswe; Boikhutso godimong;
Disa o rapele; Mmoloki wa gago,
O n’a go disetsa Botlhokung jwa madi.

O Ikanye Jeso; Disa Mmaba’ Gaufi;
O tlhomele; sentle; O dise Morena.
Fa tsatsi le dule, Se tlhole o diega,
Mo lobakeng lono. Disa o rapele.

hymns.chorus:
(BA BANGWE):
Disa o rapele, Disa rapela, Disa rapela;
Disa lefifing le mo motshegaring Mok’reste disa.

hymns.lyrics:
A Tsatsi Ja Boikhutso, Ja Boitumelo,
Kgomotso bohutsaneng, Je lentle phatsimong;
Go wena botlhe ba ba Obamang teroneng,
Ba re go Boitshepo, Ene yo’ sa Khutleng.

Wena Yo O Femetsweng Fefong Tse Di Tsogang,
Tshim’ e farafarilweng Ke noka tse dintle;
Diba se’ tsidifatsang Komelelo ’tshelong;
Fa re le kwa go Wena, Re bona kwa ’gaeng.

A Tsatsi Je Le Botshe, Tsatsi Ja Lorato;
Ke tsatsi ja go rata Dilo tsa godimo.
Re bona tshegofatso, Tsatsing ja boikhutso,
Re senka go ikhutsa Kwa mannong a mantle.

Tla Ka Pula Tsatsi Ja Boikhutso Mo Lefatshing;
O tle mo sefubeng se, Lesedi ja godimo.

Tsatsi Ja Tuulalo, Go Fitlha Nako Tsa Go;
Phodiso bohutsaneng, Re bo re wetse tiro.

Tsatsi Je Le Boitshepo, Ja Pako Le Thapelo,
Ke je le tlhalefisang, Ja masego a mantsi.

Re Utlule Tum’ E Reng, Jeso Oa Boloka;
Bolelang tikologong, Jeso Oa boloka;
Isang foko lefatsheng, Dithabeng le lewatleng,
Ke taolo ya Morena, Jeso Oa boloka.

Lo Boleleng Dintelong, Jeso Oa Boloka;
Bolelelang baleofi, Jeso Oa boloka;
Lo opeleng ditlhakeng, Le dikgaga lewatleng,
Lefatshe le tla ikhutsa, Jeso Oa boloka.

Lo Opeleng Mo Dintweng Jeso Oa Boloka;
Ka loso le botshelo Jeso Oa boloka
Opelang ka bonolo Fa pelo e fegelwa
Lebitla O le fentse Jeso Oa boloka.

Tsosa Lentswe Mo Phefong, Jeso Oa Boloka,
Janong tshaba di ’pele, Jeso Oa boloka;
Kuang poloko gotlhe, Dithabeng le dikgageng,
Ke kopolo ya phenyo, Jeso Oa boloka.

Re Na Le Tsala Go Jeso, O Rwele ’Be Tsa Rona;
Ke lobaka lo lontle jang Modimong ka thapelo;
Gantsi re tlhaela kagiso, Ka mo go sa tshwanelang,
Gonne re sa ise tsotlhe Go Modimo thapelong.

A Re Na Le Dithaelo? A Go Teng Matshwenyego?
Re se ka ra ngodiega, Go Morena thapelong.
A re ka bona kae tsala, E e re hutsafalelang
Jeso O re itse bokoeng; Go Morena thapelong.

A Re Na Le Go Imelwa, Ke Merwalo Ya Rona?
Jeso Mmoloki, phemelo, Go Morena thapelong;
A o nyadiwa ke ditsala? Bolelela Morena;
Mme O tla go sireletsa, O tla gomola gone.

Moeng O Teng Mojako, Mmulele;
(Bulela Mmoloki, O mmulele);
O na A le teng pele, Mmulele;
(Bulela Mmoloki, O mmulele);
Mmulele A ise A ye, Mmulele Moitshepi,
Jeso Morwa Modimo, Mmulele
(Bulela Mmoloki, O mmulele).

Mmulele Pelo Ya Go A Tsene; Mmulele;
(Bulela Mmoloki O mmulele);
Fa O leta Oa feta, Mmulele;
(Bulela Mmoloki, O mmulele);
Mmulele ke tsal’a go, O tla go sireletsa,
Go ya ka bosakhutleng, Mmulele,
(Bulela Mmoloki, O mmulele).

A Janong Wa Mo Utlwa? Mmulele:
(Bulela Mmoloki O mmulele);
Janong Mo itlhaolele, Mmulele;
(Bulela Mmoloki, O mmulele);
O eme fa mojako, O tla go fa boipelo,
O tlotle ina ja Gwe, Mmulele,
(Bulela Mmoloki, O mmulele).

Moeng Wa Legodimo, Mmulele
(Bulela Mmoloki, O mmulele);
O tla nna mo modirong, Mmulele;
(Bulela Mmoloki, O mmulele);
O tla go itshwarela, Fa tsa lefatshe di ile,
O tla go isa gae, Mmulele,
(Bulela Mmoloki, O mmulele).

hymns.chorus:
Go sego ba ba dirang ditaolo,
Go sego bone, ba sego;
Go sego ba ba dirang ditaolo,
Go sego, go sego bone;

hymns.lyrics:
Ngaka E Kgolo E Gaufi, Jes’ O Pelotlhomogi
O bua ka go nametsa, Utlwa lentswe ja Jeso.

Dibeng O Go Itshwaretse, Utlwa Lentswe Ja Jeso;
Ya godimong ka kagiso. Rwala rwalo sa Jeso.

Tlotlo Go Kwana E E Swang, Ke Dumela Go Jeso;
Ke rat’ina ja mmoloki, Ke rat’ina ja Jeso.

Le Tlosa Molato Wa Me Leina La Ga Jeso;
Ke itumela go utlwa Leina la ga Jeso.

Mogang A Tlang Le Serwalo, Serwalo Sa Botshelo;
Foo re tla nna fatshe nae, Re bua ka thekololo.

Ke Utlwa Ntswe Ja ’Go, Le Mpitsa Morena;
Go ntlafatswa mading a ’Go, A elang khal’fari

Ke Tla Mo Bokoeng, Thata E Go Wena;
O nntlafatsa lesweng jotlhe, Ke be ke itsheke.

Ke Jeso’ Mpiletsang Tumelong, Loratong;
Tsholofelong le kagisong,’Fatshing le godimong.

Tumisang Madi A ’Gwe; Tumisang Poloko;
Tumisang neo ya Morena, Nonofo ya rona.

E, Janong Ke Bona Madi, Motswedi O Boteng;
Jeso Moren’ O bolokang, O supa tlhakoring.

Ke Bona Bopo Lo Losa, K’utlwa Madia Buang;
A re tshenyego e ya swa, Mading a tlhapisang.

Ke Tlhatlogela Leseding, Je Le Kwa Godimo;
Ka pelo e itshekileng, Jeso A le mo teng.

Kgakgamatso Fano Tlase, G’utlwa Madi A Duleng,
Mme ke itse Jeso fela, Wa me yo’ bapotsweng.

Rara Ke Leba Go Wena; Ga K’itse Nngwe Thuso;
Fa Wena O nteseletsa, Ao ke tla ya kwa kae?

Ke Dumela Morwa Gago, O Nltutiwise Thata:
Mme O nkgolole dithatong Gone nakong eno.

Mung-a Tumelo Go Wena, Ke Leba K’eletsa;
Janong ke bone mpho eo, Fa e se yo nka swa.

Go Letsatsi Kwa Dithabeng, Go Letsatsi Lewatleng,
Mme marang a gouda a Robetse kwa botaleng;
Mme lesedi je legolo, Le tlatsa pelo ya me,
Gonne O nna teng Mmoloki, Go lesedi kwa O teng.

Leroding Ke Sia Maswabi A Malatsi A Fetang,
Gonne O nthwesa boipelo Mme O ntlatsa ka pako;
Mme gaeng ja kgalaleo, Jele O le nkgapetseng,
Ke tlhatlogela ka pelo, Mo’a me o Go latetse.

O Intheketse Mmoloki, Gotlhe Ga Me Ga Gago;
Lobone lwa rato lwa ’Go Lo tuke go Go baka;
Mme gaeng ja kgakalelo, Jele O le nkgapetseng,
Ke tlhatlogela ka pelo, Mo’a me o Go latela.

Ke Na Le Kopelo K’e Ratang, Ka Ke Rekolotswe;
Ya Mmoloki wa me Kgosi, Ka ke rekolotswe.

Ke Na Le Krest’ O Ntekaneng, Ka Ke Rekolotswe;
Thato ya ’Gwe ke e dire, Ka ke rekolotswe

Ke Na Le Mosupi Tota, Ka Ke Rekolotswe;
Yo O tlosang pelaelo, Ka ke rekolotswe.

Ke Baakanyeditswe Legae, Ka Ke Rekolotswe;
Ke tla nna ka bosakhutleng, Ka ke rekoloswe.

Modimo O Bona Go Wa Thaga Wa E Tshola;
Fa a rata dinonyane, Kea itse Wa nthata.

O Taka Dithunya Nageng, O Di Naya Lonko,
Mme fa A rata dithunya, Kea itse Wa nthata.

Modimo O Di Dirile, Tsotlhe Le Tse Kgolo;
Ga A na go di lebala, Kea itse Wa nthata.

Jeso’ Rile Kwa Babedi Bararo,
Ba Go phuthegetseng, O tla dira teng
Janong r’a dumela, Re mo thapelong;
Jeso segofatsa; O itshenole.

Jeso O Ntse O Kopana Le Rona,
Tla O nne le rona Ka bosakhutleng;
Tla Wena Mmoloki, Bonatsa tswaro;
Utlwa, segofatsa Fa re rapela.

Jeso O Re Rute Pako Tsa Gago;
E re fa re lopa Wena re utlwa,
Re tiise tumelong, Le tsholofelong,
Re itsheke ’ratong Lesedi tseleng.

Ke Wa Go Jeso ’Ntswe Ja Go Le Mpolelela Rato Lwa Go;
Mme ke eletsa go tlhatlogela Go Wena ka tumelo.

Ntsenya Tirelong Ya ’Go Morena,
Ka thata e e boitshepo;
Ke lebe godimo tsholofelong, Ke dire thato ya ’Go.

A Lobaka Lwa Boitumelo Fa Teroneng Ya Gago,
Ke khubama, le Wena ke bua Jaaka tsala, le tsala.

Go Lorato Lo Lo Boteng Thata, Kwa Moseja Ga ’Watle;
Go maipelo a goletsegileng, Kwa kagisong ya Gago.

Nke Ke Tshwane Le Jeso, Mmoloki A Nne Le Nna;
Ntlatsa kagiso, rato; Ntira bopelonomi;
Nke ke tshwane le Jeso, Fa ke le mo lefatshing;
Ke humanege moyeng, Mmoloki A nne go nna.

F’a Utlwa Mahukubu; Fa Leitlho Ja Gagwe
Le bona dinonyane Ruri O tla nkutlwa nna,
O tla nthuta go tshela, Bomatleng A intshwarele,
Ke nne itsheke pelong, Mmoloki A nne go nna.

Nke Ke Tshwane Le Jeso, Ke Rapele Ka Metlha;
Ke ikhutse go Ene, Metsing a a didimetseng;
Ke tsetswe tshegofatsong, Ka lorato lwa Gagwe,
Ke humile tumelo, Mmoloki A nne go nna.

O Ntese Ke Tsamaye Nao, Modimo Jaaka Enoke;
O tshware seatla sa me, O bue ka bonolo le nna;
Lefa ke sa bone tsela, Jeso O tsamaye le nna.

Ga Ke Tsamae Ke Le Nosi; Sefefo Se Galefile;
Diru di ntshwara dinaong, Baba ba ntaletse gaufi;
O didimatse lewatle Morena tsamaya le nna.

Fa Ke Ikhutsa Go Wena, Tsa Lefatshe Ke Lefela,
Ke eta ka pelokgale, Ke tla tsholetsa mokgoro,
Ke be ke bone Sione, Mmoloki tsamaya le nna.

Ke Ya Go Rata Morena, Go Gaisa Tsa ’Fatshe;
Gonne O mphile kagiso E e sa senyegeng.

O Gaufi Go Gaisa Botlhe Ba Lefatshe;
Monate kgopolong ya ’Go Go gaisa kopelo.

O Mphile Boitumelo Mme Ke Tla Ipela;
Kwa ntle ga rato lwa Gago Ke nna mo maswabing.

Mmoloki Yo Montle Wa Me; Go Tla Nna Jang K’o Teng?
Fa re ka rweswa boipelo Go Wena fatshing je.

hymns.chorus:
Bogolo jwa tshegofatso;
Ao bogolo jwa rato;
Botlalo jwa thekololo,
’Tshelo jo bo sa khutleng.

hymns.lyrics:
Tsa’a Tshelo Jwa Mme Bo Neelwe Wena Morena,
Tsa’a atla tsa me mme di Dire thato ya Gago.

Tsa’a Dinao Tsa Me Mme Di Fefofele Wena;
Tsa’a ntswe ja me ka metlha Ke opelele Kgosi.

Tsa’a Pounama Tsa Me Mme Di Tlatse Thomo Ya ’Go;
Tsa’a madi a me otlhe Go se je le saletseng.

Tsa’a Nako Tsa Me Tsotlhe, Di Nnele Ruri Pakong,
Tsa’a kelelelo ya me O e dirise yotlhe.

Itseele Thato Ya Me Mme Ga E Sa Le Ya Me;
Itseele pelo ya me E nne ’tulo sa Gago.

Tsa’a Rato Lwa Me Jeso, Ke Lo Ba’a Naong Tsa ’Go;
O ntsee mme ke tla nna Wa Gago metlheng yotlhe.

Ke Bonye Tsala Ya Nnete; O Ntse O Nthata Gale;
O nkgogetse mo go Ene, Ka kgole tsa lorato.
Mme mo pelong O mphapile Ka kgole e’sa kgaogeng,
Ke Oa Gagwe Ene wa me Ka gale le ka gale.

Ke Bonye Tsala Ya Nnete; Ene O Na A Ntshwela;
Ga se neo ya botshelo Fela O inneetse.
Ga kena se e leng sa me, Ke di tshwaretse Momphi;
Pelo, thata, le botshelo, Ke tsa Gagwe, ka gale.

Ke Bonye Tsala Ya Nnete; O Neilwe Thata Yotlhe;
Go nkgoga mo tseleng ya me, E e nkisang godimo.
Kgalalelo e sa khutlheng, Ke yone e ’nnotshang;
Go leta, go dira, go lwa, foo, boikhutso ka gale.

Ke Bonye Tsala Ya Nnete; Ke E E Pelonomi
Mogakolodi, Mogogi, Mohemedi yo’thata.
Go Yo o sa leng ka’nthata, Ga go se se ka ntlosang,
Botshelo, loso, kgotsa eng? Nyaa ke wa Gagwe gale.

K’utlwa Ntswe Ja Jeso Le Re "Tla Go Nna Ikhutse;
Ikaega wena molapi Mo sefubeng sa me."
Ka tla jaaka ke ne ke ntse Ke lapile thata;
Ka fitlhela boikhutso, O ’ntumedisitse.

Ke Utlwile Jeso A Re, "Bona, Ke Na’a Fela
Ga metse a a tshedileng; Inama, nwa , tshela."
Ka tla kwa go Jeso ka nwa Metse a tshedisang;
Ka timoga, ka safala, janong, ke tshedile.

Ke Utlwile Jeso A Re " Ke Sedi Ja’ Fatshe.
Leba go Nna O tlhabelwe Tsatsi ja phatsimo."
Ka leba Jeso, mme Ene Ke letsatsi ja me;
Ke tla tsama’a seding je ke Be ke fetse loeto.

Ke Ka Nna Wa Gago Mmoloki; O Nthute, O Nthute;
Nka dira thato’a ’Go Morena, O thuse janong.

A Tsa Lefatshe Tsotlhe Ke Eng O Se Teng, O Se Teng?
Ke tla di tlogelela Wena, O khumo ya me.

Fa Ke Fulara Tsa Lefatshe, Tla Gaufi, Tla Gaufi;
Go Wena ke fitlhela tsotlhe, Kgomotso ya me.

Ke Mo Tseleng Ya Godimo, Ka Metlha Ke Ya Tlhatloga;
Ke rapela ke ya gone, "Morena ntlhoma godimo."

Ga Ke Na Keletso Go Nna Ngongoregong Le Poifong,
Lefa bangwe ba go rata, Ke rapelela godimo.

Ke Senka Go Nna ’Godimong, Lefa Satane A Mphula;
Ka tumelo ke utlwile, Kopelo ya baitshepi.

Ke Senka Go Ya ’Godimong, Ke Bone Teng Kgalalelo;
Ke rapelela ’godimo, Morena nkisa ’godimong.

Nkgogela Gaufi Nao Rara, Ke Ya Go Eletsa;
Gaufi ntsenya mabogong a ’Go, Ke senka boikhutso.

Nkgogela Gaufi Nao Mmoloki, Ke Se Go Tlogele;
Fa ke le mabogong a Gago, Key a itebala.

Nkgogela Gaufi Nao Ka Mowa, Ke Tshwane Le Wena;
Ntsosa, ntlhapisa, O nntlafatse, Ke be ke itsheke.

Morena Ga Ke Rapelele Ka Moso;
Nthiba selabeng sa sebe Gompieno;
A ke se bue ’foko ja Ithamako;
Kana pounama tsa me Gompieno.

Nka Dira Ka Tlhoafalo, Ka Rapela;
Ke nne pelonomi tirong Gompieno
Nnonotsha k’utlwe go dira Thato ya Go;
Ke intshe setlhabelo Gompieno.

Mme Lefa Botshelo Jwa Me Bo Ka Feta,
Ao tsholofetso tsa Gago Di ntshegetse.
Mme tsa ka moso ga ke di Rapelele;
Ntshegetsa, Nkoga, Morena, Gompieno. Amen.

Moleti Mpolelela, A Moso Wa Sion’ Wa Sa?
A tshupo tsa go tla ga ’Gwe, Di phatsimile tseleng?
Moeti, e! tsoga, leba; ’Sedi le teng loaping;
Apara tsa go tsa nyalo, Bo sele tsoga; tsoga.

Moleti, Bona, Sedi Le Phatsima Tseleng Ya Go;
Tshupo di mo fatshing jotlhe, Tsa letsatsi je le tlang
Je ’tla reng naka lo lela, Lo tla tsosa ’fatshing; watleng,
Baitshepi ba ba robetseng Ba apare bosasweng.

Moleti Baka Lesedi Ja Ngwaga Wa Sabata;
Botlhe ba bolele gore Bogosi bo gaufi;
Moeng ke bona moseja, Kgalalelo Kananeng;
Saleme e kgalalelong, ’Seding je le kwa loaping.

Moleti Motsing Wa Gouda, O Ntse Troneng Ya Gagwe,
Ke Kgosi ya kwa Sione, O busa ka kagiso;
Kwa thabeng tse di leseding, Di phatsima botlalong.
Melatswana e phatsimang, Kwa go melang dithunya.

Moleti Fatshe Le Gaufi, Je Le Nang Le Maungo;
Kwa moseja, go gontle jang. Dithunyeng tsa Edene.
Go utlwala dikopelo, Di duma kwa loaping;
Bona bontsi, O ba reetse, Kgantele baeng ba koo.

hymns.chorus:
Lona ratanang,(Lo ratane),
Go bua Mmoloki,(lo ratane),
Bana utlwang taolo ya Rara; (Ke taolo ya Rara);
Lona ratanang,(Lo ratane),
Go bua Mmoloki,(lo ratane),
Bana utlwang taolo ya ’Gwe; (Ke taolo ya Gwe);

hymns.lyrics:
Morena Ke Go Tlhoka Jang;
Lefumeng le boleong;
Ke ya roroma O nkgoge,
Nnonotshe O mphe pono.

O Ntswese Bopelonomi, Gonne Ke Leofile;
O nthute bokoa jwa me, Ke rapelela thata.

Fa O Nkoga Ke Tshedile; Ke Wa Fa Ke Iikanya.
Tsamaya le nna botshelong, Wena O tsotlhe go nna.

Foo Tsotlhe Tse Di Ka Tlang, Boipelo, Khutsafalo,
Ke tla nna ke nna go Wena, O ntse O le Monthusi.

"Tshegelediwa Jeso" Thateng Ya Modimo;
"Tshegediwa lefatshing," Kgatong tsa ga Jeso.

"Tshegelediwa Jeso." Ke Dire Thato’a ’Gwe;
"Tshegeled’wa Morena; Tirong ya Morena.

"Tshegelediwa Jeso." Kgaoganong Le ’Fatshe;
Boingotlo mo moyeng, Boitsheko mo pelong.

"Tshegelediwa Jeso." Go Nna Wa ’Gwe Gotlhe.
Go ya ka bosakhutleng Ke nne wa’ Go fela.

Fika Ja Bosakhutleng; Ke Iphitlhe Go Wena;
A metsi le madi a Tswang tlhakoring ja Gago,
A a mphodise dibe, Mpoloka mo melatung.

Ga Se Tiro Ya Diatla, E Ka Kgonang Molao;
Lefa ke sa ikhutse, Keledi di thologa,
Ga go tetlanyo sebing; Boloka Wena fela.

Ga Go Se Ke Se Tshotseng, Ke Tla Fela Mokgorong;
Ke kopa go apes’wa, Ke kopa tshegofatso;
Ke fofela motsweding, Ntlhatswe Morena kea swa.

Fa Ke Sa Le Botshelong, Ke Bodulala Losung,
Fa ke ya bosaitsiweng, Ke go bona katlholong
Fika ja bosakhutleng, Ke iphitlhe go Wena,

Jeso Ke Modis’a Me Ga Ke Tlhoke;
Ke ja botaleng ke bolokegile;
O nkgoga metsing a a didimetseng,
O ya nthekolola fa ke timetse.

Lefa Ke Tsama’a Moruting Wa Loso,
Ka O nkoga ga ke boife bosula;
Thobane ya Gago e tla mphemela,
Ga ke welwe ke kotsi, O le gaufi.

O Mpaakanyetsa Bojelo Mo Dintweng,
Senwelo sa me sea penologa;
O ntlotsa ka tse di monko monate;
Ke tla kopang gape sa pabalelo?

Modimo Wa Me Molemo Le Tshwaro
Di ntatela go fitlha kwa go Wena,
Ke batla ka dikgato tsa borara,
Fatshing ja bojaki-bogosi jwa Go

Morua Bogosi, O Otselela Eng?
O robalelang gaufi gaeng ja ’go?
Tsoga, nanoga, itlame lotheka,
Itlhaganele baka lwa feta.

Merafe Ya Lefatshe E Mo Dintweng,
E ya roroma e reregile;
Reetsa utlwa modumo wa dikara;
Morua bogisi se diege.

Se Nnele Ditsiesto Tsa Lefatshe;
Bona tlotlo ya jone ea feta,
Kgaola tse mmamba a go bifileng;
Morua bogisi O retologe.

O Siamise Leitlho Ja Gago;
Letela kgalalelo ya kgosi;
Bona sedi le’ tlhaba kwa dithabeng;
Morua bogosi ’pel’ opela.

Mmopi, Kgosi Ya Me, Tsa Me Ke Tsa Gago;
Ke Wena Motswedi wa me Wa masego otlhe;
Ke Wena motswedi wa me Wa masego otlhe.

Bopiwa Sa Gago, Ke Tshela Go Wena;
Modimo wa me, molemo Wa gago o bakwe;
Modimo wa me molemo Wa Gago o bakwe.

Morena Nka Go Fang, Ka Tsotlhe Ke Tsa ’Go?
Rato lwa Gago lo lopa Pelo e lebogang;
Rato lwa Gago lo lopa Pelo e lebogang.

Nnonotsha Mo Moyeng Ka Tshwaro Ya Gago;
Foko ja me le keletso Le metlha tsa Gago;
Foko ja me le keletso Le metlha tsa Gago

Mmoloki Jaaka Modisa, Re Goge Ka Bonolo;
Re je mafulong a mantle, Re baakanyetse saka;
Jeso yo segofaditsweng O re rekile rona;
Jeso yo segofaditsweng O re rekile rona.

Re Ba Gago Re Tsalanye Disa Tsela Ya Rona:
O re dise mo boleung, Re batle re timetse.
Jeso yo segofaditsweng Utlwa fa re rapela;
Jeso yo segofaditsweng Utlwa fa re rapela

O Solofeditse Gore O Tla Re Amogela;
O tshwaro go re golola, Tshwaro go re ntlafatsa.
Jeso yo segofaditsweng Re tla kwa go Wena.
Jeso yo segofaditsweng Re tla kwa go Wena.

hymns.chorus:
Morena Jeso re tla opela leng boipelong?
Kreste Wa bo’a, Hajeluja; haleluja;
Amen, Haleluja: Amen.

hymns.lyrics:
A O Iketleleditse Fa Monyadi A Tla?
A O iketleleditse Fa Monyadi a tla?
Bonang O e tla; bonang O e tla;
Aparang gonne Monyadi O e tla.

Tshubang Pone Tsa Lona. Fa A Tla, Fa A Tla;
Tshubang pone tsa lona. Fa a tla, fa a tla
O tla ka bonako; ka bonako;
Moya leta fa Monyadi a tla

Re Tla Go Mo Kgatlhantsha, Fa A Tla Fa A Tla;
Re tla go Mo kgatlhantsha, Fa A tla fa A tla
Ruri O e tla; Ruri O e tla’
Re tla kgatlhantsha Monyadi fa’ tla.

Re Tla Bina Aleluja Fa A Tla, Fa A Tla;
Re tla bina aleluja Fa A tla, fa A tla;
Bonang o tla janong; O tla janong;
Aleluja Monyadi O e tla.

hymns.chorus:
Bonang Monyadi, O e tla, O e tla;
Bonang Monyadi, O e tla, O e tla
Bonang O e tla; bonang O e tla;
Aparang gonne Monyadi O e tla.

O tla tla re leteng re lebele;
O tla tla, haleluja; haleluja;
O tla tla ka maru kgalalelong ya Rragwe-
Mme ga r’itse nako.

hymns.lyrics:
Mmoloki Re Baka ’Ina Ja ’Go
Kopelong ya rona ya Kgaogano;
Re Go Tlotla re ise re tswale,
Foo re khubama re leta Wena.

Re Nee Kagiso Fa Re Ya Kwa Gae;
Re simolole re fetse nao;
Re femele sebing le ditlhonnye,
Tlung e, fa re bitsa ’ina ja’Go.

Re Nee Kagiso Mo Tshelong Jono,
Kgomotso ya rona bofutsaneng;
Mogang O re laolang go khutla,
Morena, re biletse kagisong.

Le ke le moleofi, Jeso Ola A ntshwela,
Gore ke tle ke tshele, Gore ke se ke ka swa,
Jaaka mofineng, Ke wa ’Gwe Ene wa me.
’Golo jwa rato lwa ’Gwe Bo feta legodimo,
Lo boteng go lewatle, Lo nna ka bosakhutleng;
Lo mpitlhetse kgakala; Ke ese ke Mo batle.
Le ke le moleofi, Kreste ke tsotlhe go nna;
O itse tlhoko tsa me, Futsana jwa me jwa ’Gwe;
Ke polokong go Ene, O Tshegetsa botshelo.

Yang Kwa Gethesemane, Lona Ba Lo Thaelong
Bonang ntwa ya Mmoloki, Letang Nae mo botlhokung;
Se Mo leseng’futsaneng, Go En’ithuteng thapelo.

Lo Yeng Ntlung Ya Katlholo; Mmoneng Ba Mma’a Molato;
Lo boneng le santlhokwe; Mmoneng mo motlo tseding;
Se Tshabeng dipogiso, Ipeleseng mokgoro.

’Futsaneng Jwa Khal’fari; Naong Tsa ;Gwe Mo Tlotleng,
A kgakgamatso ele; Tshupelo ya Modimo, "Go Fedile,"
Mo utlweng; Go Jeso Ithuteng go swa.

hymns.chorus:
Thata ’Gwe e ka go siamisa;
Madi a ’Gwe a ka go ntlafatsa;
Rato lwa ’Gwe lo ka go bontsha,
Fa Go tshwanetse a tsamae nao.

Lo bakeng Morena, Lefatshe le M’utlwe;
Lo bakeng Morena, Batho ba ipele;
Ao tlang kwa go Rara, ka Jeso Morwa
Lo mo tlotlele tiro tse di kgolo.

hymns.lyrics:
Jeso Mmoloki Nkgoga Sefefong Sa Botshelo;
Ke tlelwa ke dintelo, Fika je le sa bonweng;
Thuso e tswa go Wena; Jeso Mmoloki nkgoga.

Jaaka Mosadi Ngwana, Didimatsa Lewatle;
Dintelo dia ’Go utlwa; Fa O re, "Didimalang; "
O Kgosi ya lewatle, Jeso Mmoloki nkgoga.

Fa Ke Se Ke Tla Tlola, Go Kgorotlha Makhubu,
Gare ga me le ka’iso, Foo ke le fubeng sa ’Go,
A k’utlwe Wena O re, Se boife kea go goga.

hymns.chorus:
Gatang ka bonolo, Morena O fa;
Gatang ka bonolo, Re atameleng.
T &amp; B.
Lo gateng ka bonolo fa, Morena O fa;
Lo gateng ka bonolo, fa, Re atameleng.

hymns.lyrics:
Re Tla Nelwa Ke Masego, Tsholofetso’a Lorato;
Dipaka tsa tapologo Tse di tswang kwa Mmoloking.

Re Tla Nelwa Ke Masego-a Mantle A A Tsosang;
Dithabeng le megogorong, Tumo ya pula e ntsi.

Re Tla Nelwa Ke Masego; A Romele Morena;
Janong re fa tapologo, Tla janong O itlotle.

Re Tla Nelwa Ke Masego; A A We Gompieno,
Ka r’ipolela Modimong, Re bitsa kwa go Jeso.

Bojosing? Nnyaa Ga Ke ’Si Jeso’ Na Le Nna;
O Wa intumedisa; K’itse O gaufi.
Ga go tsala? Nnyaa ’Teng, Jeso Tsala ya me;
Ke’ fetoga mme O nna jalo go ya bokhutlong.

Ke Lapile? Nnyaa Fa Ke Le Fubeng Sa ’Gwe;
Ke mo boitumelong, Le mo boikhutsong.
Ga ke na thuso? E, Mme k’ikaegile,
Mabogong a that’a Jeso, Mme O mpolokile.

Ke Letile? E, O Re Ke Lete Tisong;
Ke gakgamala gantsi, Keng se diang Morena.
Boitumelo jo Bo se nang mafoko,
Motheo o o thata Boipelo Moreneng.

hymns.chorus:
Nnyaa ga ke esi, nnyaa ga ke esi;
O solofeditse gore ga A ntlogele bojosing. (gabedi)
T&amp;B.Nnyaa, nnyaa, ga ke esi Nnyaa, nnyaa, ga ke esi;
O solofeditse gore ga A ntlogele bojosing. (boela khorase)

hymns.lyrics:
O Nkgoge, Wena Jehofa. Ke Moeti Lefatsheng;
Ke bokoa, mme o thata; O ntshware ka seatla;
O nkgorise, Ka senkgwe sa ’godimo, O nkgorise
Ka senkgwe sa ’godimo.

O Bule Janong Motswedi Wa Metsi A Fodisang;
A leru je le molelo, Le nkgoge mo loetong;
Mogolodi, O nne nonofo ya me. Mogolodi,
O nne nonofo ya me.

Fa Ke Fitlhile Jordane, O Tlose Poifo Go Nna;
Ntlodisa noka e golang Mpa’a moseja Kanana;
Wena ke tla Go opela pako: Wena ke tla
Go opelela pako.

Lefatshe Ja Kwa Gae, Fatshing Ja Go Tsalwa;
Ga go ’sigo kwa Gae, Moso o’ sa khutleng;
Ke fegelelwa Gae. Botlhoko mo pelong,
Ga go setlhabi kwa Gae, Kwa ke atamelang;
Ga go setlhabi kwa Gae, Kwa ke atamelang.

Morena’ Me O Kwa Gae, O Na Le Ba’ngele;
Ga go boleo kwa Gae, Ga go thaelo teng,
Dipina tsa kwa Gae Di Duma ditsebeng,
Fa ke gopola ka Legae, Dikeledi dia tswa.
Fa ke gopola ka Legae, Dikeledi dia tswa.

Baagi Ba Kwa Gae Ba Mpiletsa Gone,
Kwa loso, bofutsana, Di sa tseneng mo Gae;
Lefatshe je ke tsetsweng; Kagiso godimo...
Jeso re tlisa kwa Gae O re rekolotse.
Jeso re tlisa kwa Gae O re rekolotse.

Mokreste, Tsoga; Morena O Laotse;
Ka tlhoro, le thebe, le tshaka ’tsogong,
Go kgatlhantsha moraedi O se boife;
Mme O tlhomame leba mmaba matlhong.

Fa Go Le Diphatsa, Itise O Se
Retolege ga go phemo’ mokwatleng;
Mophato wa fifi, fa ’ka o fenya,
Foo O tlhomane, leba mmaba matlhong.

Emela Moren’a ’Go Ka Nonofo;
Disa, tlhoafala, O lwele bokhutlo;
Kwa A go gogelang ya ka bonatla,
Mme O tlhomame, leba mmaba matlhong.

Tswelelang Fela Molaodi O Gaufi,
Go go na’a tshwaro le go go gomotsa,
Rato lwa ’Gwe ’kete motswedi nageng,
Foo O tlhomane, leba mmaba matlhong.

Mang Yo O Moreneng? Tlhomamong;
Tlhakoring tse pedi, O fa kae?

Bontsi Ga Bo Tlhophe Tshiamo;
Mme ga se ntlha e e Tlhomameng.

Tla Ntlheng Ya Morena; Ka Ntlha Yang?
Poloko e gone Kganteje.

Jaaka Nku Thabeng Serameng, Botlhe Ba Timetse;
Botshelong, Kagisong, sakeng, Ntla bona jang tsela?

Ke Timetswa Ke Pelaelo, Go Modimo Nka Ya;
Fa bansti ba re, "Fa, fale," Nk’itse jang ’mmaaruri?

Go Kreste, Tsela, Botshelo, Boammaaruri, K’e Tla;
O tla nkgogela go Rara, Gaeng ja bosakhutleng.

hymns.chorus:
Ke Nna tsela, ’mmaaruri, ’tshelo; Ga go yo’tlang go
Rara fa e se ka Nna. Ke Nna tsela, ’mmaaruri, ’tshelo;
Ga go yo’tlang go Rara fa e se ka Nna.
T.&amp;B. Ke Nna tsela, ke Nna tsela, le boammaaruri le
botshelo;
Ga go yo’tlang go Rara fa e se ka Nna.
Ke Nna tsela, Ke Nna tsela, le boammaaruri le botshelo;
Ga go yo’ tlang go Rara fa e se ka Nna.

hymns.lyrics:
Ga Ke Na Go Go Tlogela, Ga Ke Na Go Go Latlha;
Ntla go goga, Ke boloke, Ka ntlha ya leina ja me,
O se boife Bosula, Tsala kgakololo ya Me.

Fa O Tlelwa Ke Difefo, O Mpitse Mo Thapelong;
Ketla go tshola mabogong, Tisong ya tlhokomelo;
Mo ditekong, Mo ditekong, K’o ntlafaletse tsela.

Fa Godimo Le Le Phepa, Mme O Le Mo Phatsemong,
Boitumelo ’kete noka, Tsotlhe e le boipelo;
Ke tla nna nao, Ke tla nna nao, Ke goga kgato tsa ’go.

Fa Mo’a Wa’ Go O Le Fifing, O Tletse Bofutsana,
Mo’waneng o go tlaletseng, Ke tla bonatsa ’sedi,
Le sekgele, Le sekgele, Sa rato lwa Me se bonwe.

Utlwang Ba’ngele Ba Re, Jeso Sedi Ja ’Fatshe;
Kgalalelo mo Kgosing, Jeso sedi ja ’fatshe.

Tsogang Lotlhe Boipelong, Jeso Sedi Ja ’Fatshe;
Tlang phenyong ya godimo, Jeso sedi ja’fatshe.

Kreste Oa Kgabisiwa, Jeso Sedi Ja ’Fatshe;
Morena’ bosakhutleng, Jeso sedi ja ’fatshe.

Mmakeng Kgosi ’A Kagiso, Jeso Sedi Ja ’Fatshe;
Bakang tsatsi ja tshiamo, Jeso sedi ja’fatshe.

Emang, Emelang Jeso, Lona Ba Mokgoro;
Lo goletseng banera, A e se senyegeng;
Go tswa mo phenyong tsotlhe, O tla goga ba ’Gwe,
Baba botlhe ba fele, Kreste ke Morena.

Emang, Emelang, Jeso, Lo Utlweng Lonaka;
Lo ye kwa ntweng e thata, Gone tsatsing jeno;
Banna lo Mo direleng, Mo babeng ba bantshi
Lo nneng bopelo-kgale, Ineeleng bothateng.

Emang, Emelang Jeso, Emang Thateng Ya ’Gwe
Losi lo tla tlhaela; Lo se iikanyeng;
Tlhomelang ka lefoko, Disang mo thapelong,
Kwa lo bitswang, diphatseng, Se tlhokafaleng teng.

Emang, Emelang Jeso, Ntwa E E Ya Feta;
Kajeno ke mokgosi, Ka moso ke phenyo;
Yo fenyang o tla newa ’Rwalo sa botshelo,
A na le Kgosi O tla Busa bosakhutleng.

Tsoga Moya Wa Me, Tswa Mo Poifong Ya ’Go,
Tshupelo e madi E ya mponalela;
Monkemedi Oteroneng Monkemedi O teroneng
Ina ja me atleng sa ’Gwe.

O Tshela ’Godimong, Go Tla ’A Nthapelela;
Ka rato lwa Gagwe, Ka madi a Gagwe;
A n’a thologela botlhe, A n’a thologela botlhe.
A kgatsha trone ya tshwaro.

A Tswa Ntho Tse Tlhano, Tsa Kwa Khalefari;
Di nntshetsa thapelo, Di mpuelela thata;
Mme di re "Mo itshwarele," Mme di re Mo itshwarele,
Se mo leseletse go swa."

Rara Oa Mo Utlwa, Motlodiwa Wa ’Gwe
Ga ’kake A busa Boteng jwa Morwawe;
O arabela mo mading, O arabela mo mading,
Are ke tsetswe Modimong.

Tlang Go Jeso, Tlang Go Jeso,
Tlang go Jeso janong,
Janong tlang go Jeso, Tlang go Jeso janong.

Oa Boloka, Oa Boloka, Oa Boloka Janong;
Janong Oa boloka Oa boloka janong.

O Ka Kgona, O Ka Kgona, O Ka Kgona Janong;
Janong O ka kgona, O ka kgona janong.

Bitsa Ene, Bitsa Ene, Bitsa Ene Janong;
Janong bitsa Ene, Bitsa Ene janong.

Oletile, O Letile, Oletile Janong;
Janong O letile, O letile janong.

Mo Ikanye, Mo Ikanye, Mo Ikanye Janong;
Janong Mo ikanye, Mo ikanye janong.

Tshegofatso, Tshegofatso, Tshegofatso Janong;
Janong Tshegofatso, Tshegofatso janong.

Modimo Thuso Ya Rona, Tsholofelo Metlheng;
Tshireletso mo sefefong, Gae ja bosakhutleng.

Moruting Wa Trone Ya ’Go, Baitshepi Ba Gone;
Tsogo ja ’Go le lekanye, Phemo e tlhomane.

Dithaba Di ’Se Di Tsalwe, Fatshe Le Sa Botswa,
Go tswa bosasimologeng, O nts’O le Modimo.

Bontsi Jwa ’Ngwaga Go Wena ’Kete Ma’banyane;
Bo khutshwane jaaka moso, Pele ga letsatsi.

Boikhutso Jwa Jehofa, Tsatsi Je Le Itshepileng;
Ja bofelo bosupeng, O le neile batho.

O Na A Swetsa Tiro, Sabat’a Simologa;
Mme A le segofatsa, Mme re ikhutsa ka kutlo.

Mme Bantsi Ba Fetotse, Ba Ikhutsa Ka Ja Ntlha;
Bibeleng O tla itse Gore ga go’a nna jalo.

Boammaruring Ba Ka Re Ke Motho Yo Fetotseng;
Mo Fokung ja Modimo, Ga go phetoge epe.

Ka Bala Mme Ka Bona Molao Wa Sabata;
Mme ka nna boikobo, E e leng yone tsela.

hymns.chorus:
Tla ka pula, Tla ka pula;
Re itumelela jone, Boikhutso jwa Jehofa.
T.&amp;B. Tla ka pula metlha yotlhe,
Tla ka pula metlha yotlhe;
Re itumelela jone, Boikhutso jwa Jehofa.

hymns.lyrics:
Dikagiso; Fatshing Je Ja Sebe;
Madi a Jeso a re kagiso.

Dikagiso; Matsapeng A Tiro;
Go direla Jeso tapologo.

Dikagiso; Gar’a Mafutsana;
Fubeng sa Jeso ke mo kgomotsong.

Dikagiso; Baratwi’kgakala;
Go Jeso re bolokilwe rotlhe.

Dikagiso; Tse Di Sa Itsiweng;
Jeso re’ itse O mo teroneng.

Dikagiso; Loso Lo Re Sira;
Mme Jeso O nyeleditse loso.

Go Lekanye; Ntwa E E Tla Ema,
Jeso O re biletsa godimong.

Jeso Ntla Go Latela, Gonne K’utlwa O Mpitsa,
’Ratong ikanyong ke tla, Gore O nkise gae.

Matlho A Ka Tswa Tseleng, ’Naonyana Tsa Fapoga;
Lefa ke le bokoa, Mme O thata ya me.

Le Ke Le Bofutsaneng, Dibe Di Le Mo Tseleng;
Ke tla nna pelokgale Fa ke Go latela.

Morena Bona Sefefo; Makhubu A A Tlola.
Godimong go maru a mantsho; Ga go thuso gaufi;
A ga O bone re ya swa? A O robaletseng?
Fa nako tsotlhe di theregisa, Bobipo mo botenyeng.

Morena Ke Mo Tlalelong Bofutsaneng Kajeno;
Ke mo phuduegong ya pelo Ao tsoga O mpoloke,
Dibe di ntsetse tlalelong Ke fupetse moyeng;
Mme ke ya swa, ke ya swa, Morena; Akofa mme O laole.

Morena Poifo E Ile. Gotlhe Go Mo Boikhutsong;
Tsatsi le phatsema lewatleng, Legodimo le gaufi;
O nne le nna Mompoloki, Se ntese bojosing;
Boipelong ke tla fitlha tsibogong, K’ikhutse boitumelong.

Tsela ’Go Morena, E Seng Ya Me Fifing;
Nkgoga k’atla sa ’Go, O ntlhopela tsela,
Ga ke itlhophele, Ga nkak’ ’itlhophela;
Ntlhophela Modimo, Ke tla tsama’a bontle.

’Gosi Ke Bo Batlang Ke Jwa ’Go; A Tsela
E isang teng nne ya ’Go, Nka tla ka timela.
Tshwara tshwara tshelo ja me, Futsaneng boipelong
Tlatsa kaf’O bonang: O ntlhophele tsotlhe,

Ntlhophela Ditsala, Bolwetse Le ’Tshelo;
Tlhopa tsa botshelo ’Fuma kana Khumo.
E seng tlhopo ya me, E kgolo kana nnye;
Mogogi, Thata’ me, Tlhale ’tsotlhe k’Wena.

Pelo E Futsafetseng, Matlho A Eletsang.
Boipelo go dumelang; Lesedi go Jeso.

Tsa Selefatshe Ga Di Kake Tsa Kgorisa;
Re lekanya lorato, Lorato ga lo swe.

Kgomotso E’boitshepo Go Kreste M’fodisi;
Ao seketswe tatlho? Ikwatlhae O tshele.

Kagiso Ya ’Gwe Noka, Rato Lwa ’Gwe Pina;
Jokwe wa ’Gwe, motlhofo; Mo letsatsing jotlhe.

Naledi E Ntle Ya Tswa ’Sigong, Ka Lesedi Ja Boitsheko;
Ya goga banna ba botlhale Go bona ’lao jwa Mmoloki.

Ba Bonye Fokung Boammaruri, ’Ne Le Nako Ya Go
phatsima;
Ba latela sedi ja yone, Kreste naledi ya moso.

Re Tla Latela Jaaka Bone, "Lesedi Ja Lefatshe’ Jotlhe;
Re tla latela seding ja ’Gwe Go ya kwa gae legodimong.

Utlwang Mantswe A Boididi, A Dipako Godimong;
Boipelo Jeso Wa busa, Modimo Wa lorato;
Bona O dutse teroneng; Jeso O busa Esi.
Haleluja: haleluja: haleluja: Amen.

Kgosi Ya Kgalalelo O Buse Ka Bosakhutleng;
Ga go se se ka kgaoganyang Ba Gago ratong lwa ’Go;
Boitumelong go bona Sefatlhego sa Gago.
Haleluja: haleluja: haleluja: Amen.

Mmoloki Tla Ka Bonako; Tsatsing Ja Kgalalelo
Mogang oo legodimo le Lefatshe di tla feta:
Foo re tla opela re re, "Kgalalelo go Kgosi."
Haleluja: haleluja, haleluja, Amen.

Go Ba Ba Tlhokang Kgomotso, Fa Malatsi A Feta;
Go mewa e e nyelelang Fa malatsi a feta;
Fa re ka nyenya sesa, Ka re eta mo tseleng,-
Re ka dira molemo, Fa malatsi a feta.

Ga Go Nako Ya Tshameko, Fa Malatsi A Feta;
Lo nne fatlhogo tsa moso, Fa malatsi a feta;
Phegelo di mo ’fatsheng, Bofutsana keledi
Lo thuseng ba ba oleng, Fa malatsi a feta.

Rato Lo Lo Re Kopantseng, Fa Malatsi A Feta;
Re lo tlogela ka bonye, Fa malatsi a feta;
Mme peo tse re di jalang Ke tse tla nna di gola,
Di re thamisa pelo, Fa malatsi a feta.

Mo Nakong Ya Teko Rara Nnonotsha;
Ke se ’Go itatole Ka tswa go Wena.
Mpona ke reketla, O mpitse sesha,
O se ntese ka wa Ratong lwa Gago.

Ka Tse Di Ditsweng ’Fatshe Je Le Ka
Leka go nkgogela, Go ntira Kotsi;
Rara ntshegetsa ka Rato lwa Gago;
Thiba baba ba me Le Kgatlheg’a me.

A Tshwaro Ya ’Go E Ka Mpha Tlalelo,
Kana bofutsana, Mo tseleng ya me:
Nna’a atla sa Go ke Tshware ka metlha;
Ke latlhele ’rwalo Wa me go Wena.

E Ya Tshwanela Kwana, E Ya Tshwanela Kwana;
Ea tshwanela Kwana, e Tlhabilweng.

’Gosi Jwa ’Go A Bo Tle! Nyeletsa Thata’ Sebe;
Lere boikhutso jwa ’Go, Moitshepi.

Re M’ikutlwe Ka Metlha, Re Mo Rate, Re Mmake,
Gore re bone kwana kwa Sione.

Nkgoga Ke Se Timele, Mmoloki Ka Bonolo;
Ke bolokegile fa ke le tlhakoring lwa ’Go

Wena Phemelo Ya Me, Makhubung A Botshelo;
O le gaufi poloko, O tsholofelo ya me.

Nkgoga Go Ya Bokhutlong, Sefefo Se Khutlile,
Ntla fitlha ’fatshing ’tsatsi, kwa ’keledi di seyong.

hymns.chorus:
Nkgoga, nkgoga, Mmoloki bonolo O nkgoge ;
Nakong ke se timele, Nkgoga tseleng yotlhe (le yotlhe)
T.&amp; B.
Nkgoga,nkgoga, Mmoloki ka bonolo O nkgoke;
Phetogong nakong ke se timele, Nkgoga tseleng
yotlhe(leng yotlhe).

hymns.lyrics:
Morena Nthobela Senkgwe Se Se Tshedileng,
O etse Kwa lewatleng; Morena, moseja, K’a Go bona;
Mo’ a me o batla Wena Lefoko.

O Ntshegofaletse Boamma’ruri,
Jaaka senkgwe sa kwa Galelia;
Kgolego’ tla fela, Kgole di we;
Go wena nlta bona Aleluja!

A Mowa, Botshelo,’foko A ’Go;
K’akofa g’ikoba,Mme ke bokoa;
Wen’ O thuso ya me,Tshelo jwa me;
Ke fenye ke utlwa ’foko ja ’Go

Tholi lidza phalaphala, vhathu kha vha kaidzwe;
Vhane vha pfa mafhungo, vha rembuluwe vha tshile.

Lidza i pfiwe nga vhothe, u ime na kha thavha,
Vhidzelela na kha malwanzhe, mafhungo a vhutshilo.

Kha i pfale dzindevheni, dza kha vha re swiswini;
I ri zwothe zwo lugiswa, khotsi o ri lindela.

Vhudza vhane vha lemelwa, vhane vha lila Yesu;
Murena u khou vhidza, Ida zwino u tshile.

Murena U munangoni, we a hwala tshifhambano;
Vhothe avho vha u luga, vha do kuvhanganywa.

Zwithu zwothe zwi sumbedza, u da ha Yesu hu tsini;
Ri do vhona madautsha, a duvha lihulu

Sedzani zwa shangoni, phusu-phusu a dzi fheli;
Musi Yesu a tshi vhuya, u do dzi fhelisa

Henengei shangoni liswa, ri do dzula ri vhakhethwa;
Hu si tshe na vha no do fa, nga hu sa fheliho.

Mato a do di Mu vhona, Yesu a tshi do vhuya
U do di da nda Mu vhona, Yesu o ri felaho

Afha huna tsho tsiraho, tsho tsiraho nga ngoho;
li a da duvha lavhudi, ri do mu vhona Yesu;

Ndi takala u mu vhona, zwililo zwi tshi fhela;
Zwothe zwi sa divhiwiho, zwi do diswa tshedzani.

Mato a do di Mu vhona, Ene Mutshidzi wanga
Ndi do vhonana na Yesu, Yesu Mutshidzi wanga.

A’difha mafhungo ndevheni ya mudali, e kule-kule na hayani
Hu tsini-tsini-ha u vhuya ha Murena, na muvhuso U a da nawo.

Vho faho kale-kale vho lala zwaloni, vha do vuwa zwaloni zwavho;
Vhothe vhare lwanzheni lu re na maanda, vha do vhu wana vhutshilo.

Ri do di tangana ngei shangoni liswa, ri tshi do imba ro takala;
Vhane vha bva kule na kha mashango othe, ri do rabela Mudzimu

Haleluya Amen Haleluya Amen, ri do swika nga u tavhanya;
Fhatuwa u fulufhele Murena khotsi, U a da Murena na khare.

Sedzesani talifhani, vhonani-ha dzitsumbedzo;
Penyisani-ha dzimbone, ngauri Yesu U a da.

Fulufhedziso la Yesu; Tshilidzi tshi sa fheliho;
Malofha a re kha nguvho, a sumba mushumo watsho.

Mivhuso yo balangana, ipfani thikho dzi tshi wa;
Vha vhudzeni zwa tshilidzi, phala-phala i do lila.

Mashango ha na mulalo, u da ha Yesu hu tsini;
Hu vho do fhedzwa lifhasi, musi Yesu a tshi vhuya.

Vhavhi ,pfani ni a vhidzwa, Khotsi U tshe O lindela;
tavhanyani hu do valwa, a sathu u ri: "Ho valwa."

Kha ri lidze-ha phalaphala-vho, Yesu u a da hafhu
Khwatha mudali vhidzelelani, Yesu u a da hafhu.

Huwelelani na dzithavhani, Yesu u a da hafhu;
Ngwana yo no vha tsini vhukuma, Yesu u a da hafhu. 3. Lwanzhe lu ambe nga magabelo, Yesu u a da hafhu;
Lu thudze khunzikhunzini lu ri, Yesu u a da hafhu.

U fhihamelwa ha shango hu ri, Yesu u a da hafhu;
Muya na madumbu zwa bvumela, Yesu u a da hafhu.

U sinyuwa ha dzitshakha hu ri, Yesu u a da hafhu;
Ndivho yo no dala lwa u dala, Yesu u a da hafhu.

Ri tangana mulamboni, hu na tshedza tshavhudi;
Madi awo ndi avhudi, a bva kha khulunoni.

Tsini na uyo mulambo, ri do lumelisana;
Ri tshi renda Mudzimu, ro di takala nga misi

Mulamboni u penyaho, hu rulwaho mihwalo;
Ro no tshidzwa nga tshilidzi, ra tanganedza khare

Mulamboni u penyaho, mathupho o no fhela;
Mbilu dzashu dzo takala, nga vhulenda vhuhulu.

Ndi do u tevhela Yesu, Hothe hune wa nnyisa;
Hune wa ya ndi do ya-vho, Murena ndi do di ya.

Naho ndila i na mipfa, Na musi hu madini;
Ndi do gwadama nga misi, Nda do di U tevhela.3 Naho mathupho e manzhi, Ndi tshi lingwa nga hothe;
Ndila i dihwa nga iwe, Ndi do di U tevhela

Ndededze ndi matunguni, Naho ndi kha vhushai;
Iwe wo lingwa nga zwothe, Ndi do di U tevhela.

Arali U nga ntutshela, Ndi do sala ndi ndothe;
Nda si divhe hune nda ya, Ndi funa U tevhela

Murena kha ndi vhe o fhelelaho;
Ndi tama uri U dzule na nne;
U bvise yothe midzimu i sili;
U ntanzwe-vho ndi tshene sa Mahada.

Yesu ntsedze U ngeyo tadulu;
Nthuse ndi vhe tshithavhelo Tshau;
Ndi a dinekedza tshothe-tshothe-vho;
ntanzwe-vho ndi tshene sa Mahada.

Yesu ndi a di nyadza ndi humbela;
Ndo gwadama nayoni dza Murena;
Zwino ndi di nekedza  tshothe-tshothe-vho;
ntanzwe-vho ndi tshene sa Mahada.

Yesu ndo U lindela nga vhulenda;
Ida U ntsikele mbilu ntswa;
Ngauri a funaho a U mu hani;
ntanzwe-vho ndi tshene sa Mahada.

Ipfa mali tshi wa, thetshelesa-ha;
Ndi ya Yesu yothe, i ya kha Ene.

Ngwinzhi, ngwinzhi, kheyo ndi mutendelo;
Tshifhiwa tsha Yesu, kha vhana vhawe.

Naho ri vhatuku, kha ri bvise-vho;
U nga vhahulwane, vha nekedzaho.

Naho ri vhashai, ri a mu funa;
U do di takala, nga u mwemwela.

1, Yesu U a mpfuna, na Bivhili i ralo;
Vhana ndi vha Murena, Maanda avho ndi Ene.

2, Yesu U a mpfuna, ndi Ene O ’pfelaho;
Muvula litadulu, ntanzwe zwivhini zwanga.

Yesu U a mpfuna, naho ndi mulwadze-vho;
Musi ndi matunguni, U ilafha nne-vho.

Yesu U a mpfuna, arali nda mu funa;
U da hawe hu tsini, A da a dzhia nne.

hymns.chorus:
Mudzimu U ri funa rothe, ri tama u fana nae,
Nga lufuno lwa Yesu, ri pfa ro takala;
Ri kona u kondelela na kha vhanwe vhathu.

hymns.lyrics:
Vuwa khuthalela Yesu, shuma iya phanda;
Vha ralo-vho makoleni, khuthalela khare.

Ili ipfi ndi la Yesu, li vhidzelelaho;
Ndi a nea malamba, kha vho khuthalaho.

Ndi vhanzhi vhare dzithanzi, Vha U tanzilela;
Litsha dzindila dza fhano, Lilala tadulu.

Ri do dzheniswa nga Yesu, Wa dzothe dzitshakha;
Ri do vhea phanda hawe, malamba ashu-vho

Murena ndi ama hetshi, Ndila dzanga dzo vhifhaho;
Kha dzi tambe nga madi na mulilo-vho, ntanzwe tshothe.

Musi ndi tshi vhona tshedza, Ndi takala na muyani;
Ndi funa mbilu ntswa-vho, Zwi nakese na kha nne.

Musi mbilu yo no tshena, Ndi nga vha na bono fulu;
Vhutshilono hanga hu vhe na zwithu zwire zwikhethwa.

Ndi linga u bva vhuvhini, Ndi dzule ndo vhofholowa;
Ndi linga nga hothe uri ndi kone u vha mukhethwa.

todani avho vho xelaho, Ni vha thuse-ha nga tshilidzi;
Vha fheni-ha maipfi a Murena, Ane ari: Idani nothe.’

todani avho vho no xelaho, Vhaswogeni-ha vhade khae;
Vha kokodzeni nga yone ndila, i no ya hone vhutshiloni.

Ndi a tuwa-vho Yesu o mbidza, U ntevhele nga misi yothe.’
toda vho faho na vho no waho, u ri vha do divhadzwa Yesu.

Tsimu dzone dzo no lindela, mavhele o vhibva;
Dzi re kule ro no dzi vhona, hayani o vhibva.

Vha rume na nga matsheloni, na nga masiari;
Naho hu na swiswi lihulu. Vha kana mavhele.

Iwe wo runwaho nga Yesu, kana u si bvafhe;
Wa fulufhela zwa tadulu, u wana malamba.

Yesu matsheloni ipfa, u rabela hanga;
Iwe ndi do u rabela, ndo U lavhelesa.

Nkokodze nga muya wau, ndi ndilani yau;
Hothe u tshimbila yanga, nndededze Murena.

Vha funaho Iwe Yesu, vha do fushwa vhothe,
Mudzimu Ene RaMaanda, U hangwela vhothe.

Vhathu rothe kha ri imbe, ri rende dzina la Yesu;
Ndi dzina li ri tshidzaho, rendani dzina la Yesu.

Yesu ndi Mutshidzi washu, rendani dzina la Yesu;
Mu rendeni nga dzithendo, ni rende dzina la Yesu.

li ri tanzwa zwivhi zwashu, rendani dzina la Yesu;
Yesu o fulufhedzea, rendani dzina la Yesu.

Rendani Khotsi Yehova, A nea mpho dzothe;
Zwivhumbwa zwothe rendani, Khotsi na Murwa na Muya
Amen!!!

U songo mphira Mutshidzi, Ipfa tshililo;
Musi U tshi vhidza vhanwe, U songo mphira.

Tshidzuloni tsha tshilidzi, Ndi vhofhololwe;
Ndo gwadama nda dinyadza, Mphe lutendo.

Ndi fulufhela tshilidzi, Ndi U vhone-vho;
U fhodze-vho muya wanga, thi tsha kona nne.

U tshisima tsha phumudzo, U fhira zwothe,
Makoleni na shangoni, U thikho yanga.

hymns.chorus:
Yesu, Yesu, Ipfa tshililo;
Musi U tshi vhidza vhanwe,
U songo mphira.

hymns.lyrics:
Ndi zwavhudi u rabela, zwi do humisa vhutungu;
Zwi ntswikisela ha khotsi, zwothe zwine nda zwi shaya.
Nga tshifhinga tsha mathupho, ndi a anzela u fhumudzwa;
Ndi ponyoke u lingwani, nga tshifhinga tsha thabelo.

Ndi zwavhudi u rabela, hu isa khumbelo dzashu;
Ngoho yawe i shudufhadza, a mu thetshelesaho,
U ri ndi mu fune Ene, ndi tende na ipfi lawe.
Ndi do disa zwothe khaE, ndo lindela nga thabelo.

Ndi zwavhudi u rabela, u nga ri ndi nga fhumudzwa;
Ndi vhuye ndi vhone haya, ndi fulufhele-vho hone,
Nda wana muvhili muswa, ndi yo wana vho mukovhe;
Ndi huwelele ndi tshi ri, sala zwavhudi thabelo.

1.Ro pfa nga ha Murena, Yesu ndi Mutshidzi;
Vhudzani tshakha dzothe, nga Yesu Murena,
Vhidzelela kha shango, na kha malwanzhe othe,
Yesu u a ni vhidza, ndi Ene Mutshidzi.

Vhudzani vha re vhavhi, Vha de ha Murena;
U do vha tanzwa zwivhi, Vha khethwa vha khethwa;
Imbelelani nyimbo, dzi pfiwe mashangoni,
Shango li do awedzwa, nga Yesu Mutshidzi.

Huwelelani nothe, nga Yesu Murena.
Nga lufu na vhutshilo, ha Yesu Mutshidzi;
Imbani na swiswini, nga tshilidzi tsha Yesu,
U do kunda livhIda, nga Yesu Murena.

Posa ipfi muyani, u ambe nga Yesu;
Hothe Yesu u hone, A divhaho zwothe,
Muthu a tshi rabela, e hothe tshiphirini
Mudzimu u a mu pfa, A di mu fhindula.

1.Yesu u ri Idani hayani, U vhidza inwi namusi;
U si lambe musi wa u tshidzwa, U landulela mini?

Na vho netaho u a vha vhidza, U a vha vhidza namusi;
Ida kha Ene, U fhatutshedzwe, nga Ene Yesu zwino.

Ida-ha zwino o u lindela, O lindela iwe zwino;
’da na zwivhi u di tukufhadze, U songo hangwa, Ida.

U tshi mu toda u ya u thusa, U ya thusa, ada namusi;
Vhane vha tenda vha do takala, tavhanya u a vhidza.

1.Mueni munangoni, kha dzhene;
Ndi kale o lindela, kha dzhene
Mueni A songo huma, kha dzhene ndi Mukhethwa,
Yesu murwa wa Khotsi, kha dzhene.

Muneye mbilu yau, kha dzhene;
Nangani Ene zwino, kha dzhene;
Khoyo e munangoni, Ri do newa dakalo;
Rendani dzina lawe, kha dzhene.

Ipfa a tshi u vhidza, kha dzhene;
Mutende zwino Yesu, kha dzhene
A saathu u nala, Yesu u do u tshidza,
Rabela dzina lawe, kha dzhene.

U vhidzwa nga Mudzimu, kha dzhene;
Mutanganedze zwino, kha dzhene
U do hangwelwa zwivhi, Uya nga hu sa fheli;
A u isa tadulu, kha dzhene.

Ndi a u lilela Ida kha nne, Ida-ha Mutshidzi;
Ndi a u dzindela Ida kha nne, Ida-ha Mutshidzi;

A thi na vhuawelo vhusiku, Ida-ha Mutshidzi;
Wa ndavhelesa ndi n ga di tshila, Ida-ha Mutshidzi.

Ndi tshimbila ndaila dzi kondaho, Ida-ha Mutshidzi;
Mato anga a lilala kha’we, Ida-ha Mutshidzi.

U si sande u di-nyadza hanga, Ida-ha Mutshidzi;
Ndi a lila apfa thabelo yanga, Ida-ha Mutshidzi.

Hu na vhutshilo kha tshifhambano, Yesu u ri sedza tshone;
Zwa lino shango ndi lifhedzi, Sedza lupfumo kha tshifhambano.

Nga duvha le nda vhona Mutshidzi, a takala a tshi mmbona;
Musi ndi tshi dzhena zwivhini, nda sedza Tshifhambano ndo tshila.

Ndo dzula ndo sedza Tshifhambano, ndo fulufhela Mudzimu;
Sathane ha fhenyi muthu o fulufhela Maanda a tadulu.

Yesu u a ni vhidza nga vhulenda, U vhidza iwe na nne;
Vothini la mbilu o di lindela, U sedza iwe na nne.

Ni lengelani ni Yesu a tshi vhidza, U vhidza iwe na nne;
Ni lengelani na nyadza tshilidzi, Tshilidzi kha ’we na nne.

Tshifhinga na zwikhathi zwi a fhira, zwi fhira iwe na nne;
Mirunzi i tshi da na lufu lwa da, Lu swika kha ’we na nne.

Humbula fulufhedziso, lufuno, ndi la iwe na nne-vho;
Naho ro tshinya u do ri hangwela, U ri hangwela rothe.

hymns.chorus:
Ida haya, Wo neta Ida haya;
Yesu u a ni vhidza nga vhulenda,
U vhidza iwe na nne.

hymns.lyrics:
Nanga khulu ndi Murena, Yesu u na tshilidzi;
U vusa mbilu yo faho, ipfani ipfi lawe.

Zwivhi zwothe zwo hangelwa, ipfani ipfi lawe;
Ri tshimbile nga mulalo, ri do fhiwa dzikhare.

Kha ri rende Ngwana rothe, ri tende Yesu rothe;
Ndi a funa dzina ili, la Yesu Muphulusi.

Dzina ili li pandela, U ofha hanga hothe;
Muya wanga u takadzwa, nga dzina la Murena.

Na musi a tshi do vhuya, na khare dza vhutshilo;
Ra dzula nae Murena, ra amba nga u tshidzwa.

Ndi pfa Ipfi lau, Yesu u tshi mmbidza;
U ri ndi de ndi tanzwiwe, nga malofha au.

Nangwe ndi mutshinyi, ndi a u humbela;
U ntanzwe hothe vhutshinyi, ndi itwe mukhethwa.

Yesu u khou mmbidza, nga lufuno lwawe;
Uri ndi de kha vhuhosi, ha ngei tadulu.

Yesu ndi Mutshidzi, o nthengulula-vho;
Nga malofha a mutengo, ngei Tshifhambanoni.

Kheli gabelo litswuku, lo tsa lo atama;
Yesu u a tshidza vhothe, U sumba nthoni.

Ndi wana u sikwa huswa, hone malofhani;
Zwivhi zwothe zwi do fhela, zwa fa nga Murena.

Ndi tshimbila ndi tshedzani, ndi tshi ya tadulu;
Nguvho dzanga dzo tanzwiwa, nga Yesu Murena.

Ndi tshimangadzo tsha Yesu, tsha u rengwa hanga;
Ndi Yesu a zwi divhaho, zwa u tshidzwa hanga.

Dzina lone li funwaho, ndi line nda li divha;
lo nekedzwa nga Mudzimu, nga murwa a funwaho.

Kha nne li da na mashudu, uri ndi mu rende-vho;
Ndi imba dzina la Ene na hone vhudi halo.

Ndi imbela luimbo ngauri ndo vhofhololwa,
Ndi rende lini na lini, dzina lo ambiwaho.

hymns.chorus:
Itsho tshedza, tshedza tshavhudi;
Tshi vhonetshela mbilu,
Yesu u bvisa vhutungu, hu a penya mbiluni.

hymns.lyrics:
Ndi na luimbo lwa thendo, lwa u vhofhololwa;
Nga Mutshidzi khotsi-anga, we a mbofholola.

U mpfushisa nga vhurena, nga u vhofhololwa;
Ndi ite lufuno lwawe, O mbofholola-vho.

Na vhutungu vhu khagala, ha u tshidzwa hanga;
Vhu tusa u tima-tima, na u ofha hothe.

Wo mbetshela haya hanga, wo mbofholola-vho;
Nda dzula nga hu sa fheli, ndo vhofhololwa nne.

hymns.chorus:
Tshe nda vhofhololwa, tshe nda vhofhololwa;
Thendo kha dzina lawe, tshe nda vhofhololwa,
Ndi do mu renda Yesu wanga.

hymns.lyrics:
Musi thongola i tshi wa u a i vhona-vho;
U funa zwothe zwinoni u funa na nne-vho.

U nakisa na maluvha a tshi tou fhefheda;
U funa othe maluvha, na nne u a mpfuna.

Mudzimu o sika zwothe, zwa fhano shangoni;
Vhana vhatuku ndi vhawe, na nne U a mpfuna.

Kha ndi fane na Yesu, Ene Murena wanga;
Tenda Mutshidzi wanga, a de a dzule na nne.
Kha ndi fane na Yesu, shangoni fhano fhasi;
Ndi lila muya wau, dzula na nne Mutshidzi.

Zwinoni zwi tshi tshila, U a zwi lavhelesa;
A tshi vhona zwi tshi wa, ngoho na nne U do mpfa,
U sedza ndila yanga, uri a ndendedze-vho;
Ndi funa u khethiwa. Dzula na nne Mutshidzi.

Kha ndi fane na Yesu, ndi tshile misi yothe;
Ndi funa u awela, fhethu ho fhumulaho,
Ndo bebiwa nga huswa, nga lufuno lwa Yesu;
Kha ndi vhe na lutendo, dzula na nne Mutshidzi.

Ndi tshimbila na Mudzimu, ndi fane-vho na Henoxe;
U nkokodze-vho nga Tshanda, uri ndi vhuye ndilani;
Musi ndi tshi vho do neta, kha ndi kokodzwe nga Iwe.

Ndi nga si kone ndi ndothe, zwa ralo ndi do balelwa;
Zwikhukhuliso ndi zwinzhi, na maswina a tshi ntanga,
Ho dala zwikhukhuliso, nthange phanda ndi tshimbile.

Musi ndo awela kha ’we, zwa shangoni a s tshithu;
Ndi tshimbila ndo talifha, ndi do hwala tshifhambano,
Ndi de ndi vhone Tsioni, Ida u tshimbile na nne.

Muya wanga u a khoda, vhuhulu ha makoleni;
Ndi nnyi a khodaho, a ambaho lufuno lwa lu na Yesu?

Lu a ri linda vhusiku, lu a penya lu swiswini;
Lufuno lwa Mudzimu, ndi mushonga une wa ilafha.

Ndi a fulufhela tshothe, ndi do thuswa-vho ndi tshi wa;
Vhutshiloni na lufuni lufuno lwa Yesu lu hone.

U fhirisa zwithu zwothe, ndi funa Murena;
Ngauri u na mulalo, u sa do fhelaho.

Ndi di-sendedza kha Iwe, nga maduvha othe;
Zwo naka u divha Iwe, wa dzothe dzithendo.

Mbilu yanga yo takala, nga maduvha othe;
Arali ndi si na Iwe, zwothe ndi lifhedzi.

Mutshidzi wanga wavhudi, a hu tshe na munwe;
Ndi tshimbila na Iwe, zwothe zwi a luga.

Dzhia shango u mphe Yesu, ngauri ndi lifhedzi;
Zwi re khalo a si tshithu, Yesu Ene ha fheli.

Shango a si tshithu kha nne, musi ndo wana Yesu;
Ndi lindwa nga Mutshidzi, ndi imba lu difhesaho.

Shango a si tshithu kha nne, ndo sedza tshifhambano;
Kha ndi vhone-ha Murena, ndo’ bonyoloswa tshothe.

A bvaho e na tshililo, A tshi kho’ zwala mbeu;
A sa lali, A sa neti, U do wana tshilidzi.

nwando u wa lwa vhulenda, duvha la vhonetshela;
Ri fhiwa na mitshelo-vho, nga Maanda a tadulu.

Zwino u singo tshenuwa, Zwala, U songo neta;
Khwatha naho zwi tshi konda, U do kana dakalo.

Tombo le nda korelwa, Ndi di dzumbe kha Iwe;
Ndi tshidzwe nga malofha, E a bva dzinthoni,
Ivha mushonga tshothe, U ntanzwe zwivhini.

’Thi koni u vuledza maambwa nga mulayo;
Naho nda fungelela hani na nga zwililo,
Ndi nga si thuthe tshivhi, Mutshidzi ndiwe fhedzi.

Ndi da ndi si na tshithu, Nda losha tshifhambano;
Ndi fhedzi ndi ambadzwe, ndo xela kha ndi thuswe,
Ndo tshinya Yesu wanga, ntanzwe uri ndi si fe.

Ndi tshi vuledza lwendo, ndo kunda lone swina;
Ndi tshi ya hu sa dihwi, Ndi vhona khulunoni,
Tombo la kalekale, Ndi di dzumbe kha Iwe.

Mutsho muhulu wo no sendela, Yesu u a da;
U do dzhia vha vhana vhawe,
Vha ya hayani.

Mafhungo madifha a do huwelelwa kha vhothe;
Muhwe ha tsha lenga, Phalaphala i do lila.

Na vharunwa vhawe vhothe vha do mu fhelekedza;
A tshi da u dzhia vhawe Mathupho a fhela.

Vhahashu vho faho kale vha do dovha vha vhonwa;
Hu do fhulutwa mitodzi ya u lilelana.

fa Yesu kha tshifhambano, Ndo humbula u tanzwa zwivhi,
Ndo tanzwa mbilu nga malofha, Thendo kha Yesu.

U tshidzwa hanga ho mangadza, Zwo naka Yesu e na nne-vho;
O ntsedzisisa tshifhambano, Thendo kha Yesu.

O! Tshisima tshi ri tshidzaho, Ndi a takala ndi nga ngomu;
U mbulunga nda vha wavhudi, Thendo kha Yesu.

Idani kha itshi tshisima, dinekedzeni kha Murena;
namusi Idani ni tshidzwe, Thendo kha Yesu.

U a tenda u tanzwiwa vhuvhi? Nga Maanda a re malofhani;
U a funa u kunda vhuvhi naa? Hu na Maanda malofhani.

U a funa u litsha vivho naa? Nga Maanda a re malofhani;
U do bviswa zwothe zwivhi zwau, Hu na Maanda malofhani.

U funa u tshena sa Mahada? Nga Maanda a re malofhani;
’Da u tambe tshisima ndi Yesu, Hu na Maanda malofhani.

U a funa u shumela Yesu? Nga Maanda a re malofhani;
U a livhuwa maduvha othe, Hu na Maanda malofhani.

Swiswi a li nga vhi hone hafhu, Musi Yesu a tshi vhuya fhano;
Swiswi a li nga vhi hone hafhu, A tshi da u dzhia vhawe.

A hu nga vhi na matungu hone, A hu tsha do vha na zwi dinaho;
Hu do vha matsheloni avhudi, Musi Yesu a tshi da.

Mitodzi a i tsha do vha hone, Zwililo a zwi tsha do vha hone;
I do vha khano khulu ya thendo, Vhawe vha this do tuwa.

Vha do imba nyimbo dza dakalo, Dzi do vha nyimbo dza ndumeliso;
Na dakalo lihulu a tshi da, A tshi tuwa na vhawe.

hymns.chorus:
Ee, Yesu u a londa ngangoho (Ngoho ngoho U a londa)
U pfela ’ne vhutungu, Zwi tshi konda lotsha;
Na nga vhusiku; Ngoho U a londa (londa).

hymns.lyrics:
Haya havhudi Shango lashu la mulalo!
A huna vhusiku khalo, Ndi mutsho fhedzi;
Ndo li lindela tshothe, Fhano ndi la mbilu;
Shango ilo a li na mathupho, A no dina;
Shango ilo a li na matungu, vhu no dina.

Khotsi o dzula khalo na vharunwa vhawe;
A hu’ tshivhi na mulingo kha ilo shango;
Nyimbo dza hone dzi bvuma ndevheni dzanga;
Mitodzi i a bva nda humbula kha ilo shango.

Vhadzuli vha hone mmbidza uri ndi ye;
Hayani hu si na lufu na zwi vhavhaho;
Yawee! Shango lifunwa! la dzawelo fulu!
Kristo ri ise rothe hayani ha lufuno;
Kristo ri ise rothe hayani ha lufuno.

Mu rendeni ndi Yesu Mutshidzi washu,
Imbani nga ha lufuno lwawe;
Mu losheni inwi vharunwa vhakhethwa,
Hulisani dzina lawe likhethwa;
Sa mulisa u linda vhana vhawe,
U vha kuvhatedza nga maduvha.

Mu rendeni ndi Yesu Mutshidzi washu,
O thuphwa a fela zwivhi zwashu;
Ndi tombo lashu ri do tshidzwa nga Ene,
Mu rendeni ndi Yesu Muvhambwa;
Mu khodeni, o hwala zwivhi zwashu,
Lufuno lwawe ndi luhulusa.

Mu rendeni ndi Yesu Mutshidzi washu,
Vha tadulu imbani Hosana;
Yesu u do vhusa nga hu sa fheliho,
Hulisani a re khosi yashu;
U a vhuya nga gundo lifhasini,
U na Maanda na vhurena hothe.

Mmbudze zwa kale-kale, Zwithu zwa tadulu,
Zwa vhurena ha Yesu, zwa lufuno lwawe;
Mmbudze zwo pfufhifhadza, zwi tshi nga zwa nwana,
Ndi muhota ndo neta, Ndo dala nga tshikha.

Toolola ngavhuya, Zwi vhe na tshirunzi;
Humbula nne ndi muvhi, yesu o dela nne;
Mmbudze tshifhinga tshothe, Arali u tshi do,
’Vha mukhuthadzi musi ndo no vha khomboni.

Dovha u mmbudze zwothe, Musi hu na nyofho,
Vhugala ha shangoni vhu tshi vho nndina;
Ee, vhurena ha shango vhu tshi vho dodela,
Mmbudze zwa kale-kale: Yesu u a fhodza.

Vhona Yesu munangoni! U khokhonya a sa neti,
Tshe a lindela tsha kale; A no ngo mu tanganedza.

U ri renga musuku vhukuma na nguvho yavhudi;
Lafha Mato u di vhone, U tanzwe madondo othe.

Ipfa mukosi wa thanzi, Ndi mukosi wa u fhedza;
Wo no mu sinyusa tshothe! Rembuluwa-ha u vhuye.

Mushumo wawe tadulu u tsini na u vuledzwa;
Wa tshika a vhe wa tshika, Mukhethwa a vhe mukhethwa.

nwando wo no Mu nukadza, O londela u vulelwa;
Vuwa u vule munango; Murena a si tsha lenga.

Mu tanganedze Mueni; Dzula nae wo takala,
Nga vhukonani vhukuma, Ni le ndiloni nthihi.

Ndo swika shangoni liswa, lupfumo lwalo ndi lwanga;
Afho tshedzani tsha vhudi, vhusiku a vhu ho hone.

Yesu u tshimbila na nne, Ri tshimbila ri tshi amba;
O mpfara nga tshanda tshawe, U khou nyisa-vho tadulu.

Hu na munukho wa-vhudi, u bvaho kha iyo miri;
Hu na maluvha avhudi. Hu na madi a vhutshilo.

Nyimbo dza ngei tadulu, dzi pfala ndevheni dzanga;
Vharunwa vha imbelela nyimbo dzau renda khotsi.

hymns.chorus:
Shango la ngei Kanana, nda ima kha thavha yalo;
Nda sedza zwa seli halo, afho hu re na nndu yanga;
Ndi do vhona-vho tadulu, haya ha lini na lini.

hymns.lyrics:
Vuwa muya wanga! U fhufhure nyofho,
Yesu o no fela nne lwa vhutungu,vO dzula o nndindela;
O dzula o nndindela;
Ndo nwalwa tshandani tshawe.

U dzula tadulu A tshi nnyambela,
Lufuno lu tshidzaho, Malofha a vhudi,
Ro no rengwa nga malofha,
Ro no rengwa nga malofha,
A hashaho khulunoni.

Ndi thanu ntho dze A rungwa Khalivari;
Ntho idzo dzi kho’ nthabelela-vho.
Dzi ri ndi hangwelwe vhuvhi;
Dzi ri ndi hangwelwe vhuvhi;
Wa shanduka a u nga fi.

Vhona Mudodzwa A tshi humbela khotsi;
Khotsi ha nga furaleli Murwa wawe.
Na Muya U ya Mu thusa;
Na Muya U ya Mu thusa;
U ri : Ndi thusa Murena.

’da kha Yesu, ’da kha Yesu,
’da kha Yesu zwino;
Zwino Ida khae, Ida khae zwino.

U do tshidzwa, U do tshidzwa,
U do tshidzwa zwino;
Zwino U do tshidzwa Ida khae zwino.

U na Maanda, U na Maanda,
U na Maanda, zwino.
Zwino U na Maanda, Ida khae zwino.

Mu humbele, Mu humbele, Mu humbele zwino;
Zwino, Mu humbele, Ida khae zwino.

O lindela, O lindela, O lindela zwino;
Zwino, O lindela Ida khae zwino.

Fulufhela, Fulufhela, Fulufhela zwino;
Zwino, Fulufhela, Ida khae zwino.

Fhatutshedzwa, Fhatutshedzwa,
Fhatutshedzwa zwino;
Zwino, Fhatutshedzwa, Ida khae zwino.

Vhona Mulisa wa Isiraele O ima;
Ipfa A tshi vhidza nngu, na u dzi takula.

U ri: ’Litsha dzi de fhano;
U songo dzi thatha;
Ngauri ndo dela u fhatuthsedza vhenevha.’

Ri vha disa nga dakalo, Kha Iwe Murena;
Ri takalela uri ri vhana vhaU tshothe.

Ndi do fhira govhani li no pfi ndi likhethwa;
Kha nne ndi lone govha lila la Kanana.
Hune nda pfa mafhungo a takadzaho mbilu;
Mutshidzi U tsini na nne lwendoni lwothe.

A huna gole disaho swiswi ndilani;
Ngauri tshedza tsha Murena tsho i tshenisa.
Hu kha di imbelelwa lu divhaho tadulu;
Hu pfala luimbo lu ntakadzaho nandi!

Ndi tshimbila ndo takalela tshedza tshavhudi;
maduvha othe ndi do di dzula ndo takala.
Ndi sendela-vho dzikhoroni dza muvhuso;
Nga ndila i yaho muvhusoni wa tadulu.

hymns.chorus:
I khou penya, I khou penya;
Naledzi thavhani khethwa;
Vhu khou penya, Vhu khou penya,
Vhutshidzi ha Murena washu.

hymns.lyrics:
munwe u do dzhena nga khoro, Zwe’ zwino, zwe’ zwino;
A thetshele vhugala ha hone, Hu nga vha nne? na inwi?
U do tshimbila kha musuku, A vhone madzanga henengei;
O fulufhedziswaho kale, Hu nga vha nne? Kana inwi?

munwe u do rula muhwalo, Zwe’ zwino, zwe’ zwino;
Vha tendaho vha wana khare, Hu nga vha nne? kana inwi?
munwe u do vhona Murena, Matungu a shango o fhela;
U do takala nae tshothe, Hu nga vha nne? kana inwi?

munwe u do wana ho valwa, Zwe’ zwino, zwe’ zwino;
Ipfi la ri: A thi ni divhi.’ Hu nga vha nne? kana inwi?
A vhidzelela a si pfiwe, Vothi la hone li si vulwe;
munwe u do dzinwa malamba, Hu nga vha nne? kana inwi?

munwe u do imba lwa gundo, Zwe’ zwino, zwe’ zwino;
Na mavhuthu o no tshidzwaho, Hu nga vha nne? kana inwi?
munwe u do resha na vhanwe, Vha funwa na vho faho kale;
Vha dzula vhugalani tshothe, Hu nga vha nne? Kana inwi?

Hu na vha no ri li tshi kovhela, vha vha na vhubva;
Hu na vhathuphei musi duvha li tshi kovhela,
vhanwe vha phuphudzika musi duvha li tshi kovhela;
Zwivhuya ri nga ita duvha li tshi kovhela.

Vhubva vhu songo vha hone musi li tshi kovhela;
Khofheni hu penye musi duvha li tshi kovhela,
Hu pfala tshililo tsha muthu o huvhalaho;
Thusa vha waho musi duvha li tshi kovhela.

Lufuno lu vuwe musi duvha li tshi kovhela;
Zwothe ri zwi hangwe musi duvha li tshi kovhela,
Ri zwale mbeu yavhudi, i pakate khula;
Dzi do takadza musi duvha li this kovhela.

Hu na vhuawelo vhunzhi, tsini na Mudzimu;
Tshivhi a tshi nga do dina tsini na Mudzimu.

Phumudzo i difhesaho, tsini na Mudzimu;
Hu re na Mutshidzi washu, tsini na Mudzimu.

Ndi fhethu ha mbofholowo, tshi ni na Mudzimu;
Dakaloni na mulalo tsini na Mudzimu.

tavha mukosi mmbi i tsini, Imela ngoho ya Murena;
Dzhia pfumo u ime u khwathe, U di tike nga ipfi lawe.

Khwatha u tshi tangana na swina, Ri tshi ya phanda he ra livha;
Ri tshi divha hune ra do ya, Tshitangu na tshedza tshihulu.

Mudzimu ri a u vhidzelela, Ri thuse rothe nga tshilidzi;
Musi nndwa yo fhela ro kunda, Ri ambadze khare ya gundo.
